Popup.name: Popup
Popup.brief_description: Base container control for popups and dialogs.
Popup.description: Popup is a base [Control] used to show dialogs and popups. It's a subwindow and modal by default (see [Control]) and has helpers for custom popup behavior.

methods.name: popup
methods.description: Popup (show the control in modal form).

methods.name: popup_centered
methods.description: Popup (show the control in modal form) in the center of the screen, at the current size, or at a size determined by "size".

methods.name: popup_centered_minsize
methods.description: Popup (show the control in modal form) in the center of the screen, ensuring the size is never smaller than [code]minsize[/code].

methods.name: popup_centered_ratio
methods.description: Popup (show the control in modal form) in the center of the screen, scaled at a ratio of size of the screen.

signals.name: about_to_show
signals.description: This signal is emitted when a popup is about to be shown. (often used in [PopupMenu] for clearing the list of options and creating a new one according to the current context).

signals.name: popup_hide
signals.description: This signal is emitted when a popup is hidden.

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_POST_POPUP
constants.description: Notification sent right after the popup is shown.

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_POPUP_HIDE
constants.description: Notification sent right after the popup is hidden.

RectangleShape2D.name: RectangleShape2D
RectangleShape2D.description: Rectangle shape for 2D collisions. This shape is useful for modeling box-like 2D objects.

properties.name: extents
properties.description: The rectangle's half extents. The width and height of this shape is twice the half extents.

Mutex.name: Mutex
Mutex.description: A synchronization Mutex. Element used to synchronize multiple [Thread]s. Basically a binary [Semaphore]. Guarantees that only one thread can ever acquire this lock at a time. Can be used to protect a critical section. Be careful to avoid deadlocks.

methods.name: lock
methods.description: Lock this [code]Mutex[/code], blocks until it is unlocked by the current owner.

methods.name: try_lock
methods.description: Try locking this [code]Mutex[/code], does not block. Returns [OK] on success, [ERR_BUSY] otherwise.

methods.name: unlock
methods.description: Unlock this [code]Mutex[/code], leaving it to other threads.

PlaneMesh.name: PlaneMesh
PlaneMesh.description: Class representing a planar [PrimitiveMesh]. This flat mesh does not have a thickness.

properties.name: size
properties.description: Size of the generated plane. Defaults to (2.0, 2.0).

properties.name: subdivide_depth
properties.description: Number of subdivision along the z-axis. Defaults to 0.

properties.name: subdivide_width
properties.description: Number of subdivision along the x-axis. Defaults to 0.

properties.name: left_to_right
properties.description: Displacement of of the upper edge along the x-axis. 0.0 positions edge straight above the bottome left edge. Defaults to 0.5 (positioned on the midpoint).

properties.name: size
properties.description: Size of the prism. Defaults to (2.0, 2.0, 2.0).

properties.name: subdivide_depth
properties.description: Number of added edge loops along the z-axis. Defaults to 0.

properties.name: subdivide_height
properties.description: Number of added edge loops along the y-axis. Defaults to 0.

properties.name: subdivide_width
properties.description: Number of added edge loops along the x-axis. Defaults to 0.

Material.name: Material
Material.brief_description: Abstract base [Resource] for coloring and shading geometry.
Material.description: Material is a base [Resource] used for coloring and shading geometry. All materials inherit from it and almost all [VisualInstance] derived nodes carry a Material. A few flags and parameters are shared between all material types and are configured here.

Environment.name: Environment
Environment.brief_description: Resource for environment nodes (like [WorldEnvironment]) that define multiple rendering options.
Environment.description:
Resource for environment nodes (like [WorldEnvironment]) that define multiple environment operations (such as background [Sky] or [Color], ambient light, fog, depth-of-field...).	These parameters affect the final render of the scene. The order of these operations is:
 		- DOF Blur
		- Motion Blur
		- Bloom
		- Tonemap (auto exposure)
		- Adjustments

constants.name: BG_KEEP
constants.description: Keep on screen every pixel drawn in the background.

constants.name: BG_CLEAR_COLOR
constants.description: Clear the background using the project's clear color.

constants.name: BG_COLOR
constants.description: Clear the background using a custom clear color.

constants.name: BG_SKY
constants.description: Display a user-defined sky in the background.

constants.name: BG_COLOR_SKY
constants.description: Clear the background using a custom clear color and allows defining a sky for shading and reflection.

constants.name: BG_CANVAS
constants.description: Display a [CanvasLayer] in the background.

constants.name: BG_MAX
constants.description: Helper constant keeping track of the enum's size, has no direct usage in API calls.

constants.name: GLOW_BLEND_MODE_ADDITIVE
constants.description: Additive glow blending mode. Mostly used for particles, glows (bloom), lens flare, bright sources.

constants.name: GLOW_BLEND_MODE_SCREEN
constants.description: Screen glow blending mode. Increases brightness, used frequently with bloom.

constants.name: GLOW_BLEND_MODE_SOFTLIGHT
constants.description: Softlight glow blending mode. Modifies contrast, exposes shadows and highlights, vivid bloom.

constants.name: GLOW_BLEND_MODE_REPLACE
constants.description: Replace glow blending mode. Replaces all pixels' color by the glow value.

constants.name: TONE_MAPPER_LINEAR
constants.description: Linear tonemapper operator. Reads the linear data and performs an exposure adjustment.

constants.name: TONE_MAPPER_REINHARDT
constants.description: Reinhardt tonemapper operator. Performs a variation on rendered pixels' colors by this formula: color = color / (1 + color).

constants.name: TONE_MAPPER_FILMIC
constants.description: Filmic tonemapper operator.

constants.name: TONE_MAPPER_ACES
constants.description: Academy Color Encoding System tonemapper operator.

constants.name: DOF_BLUR_QUALITY_LOW
constants.description: Low depth-of-field blur quality.

constants.name: DOF_BLUR_QUALITY_MEDIUM
constants.description: Medium depth-of-field blur quality.

constants.name: DOF_BLUR_QUALITY_HIGH
constants.description: High depth-of-field blur quality.

properties.name: adjustment_brightness
properties.description: Global brightness value of the rendered scene (default value is 1).

properties.name: adjustment_color_correction
properties.description: Applies the provided [Texture] resource to affect the global color aspect of the rendered scene.

properties.name: adjustment_contrast
properties.description: Global contrast value of the rendered scene (default value is 1).

properties.name: adjustment_enabled
properties.description: Enables the adjustment_* options provided by this resource. If false, adjustments modifications will have no effect on the rendered scene.

properties.name: adjustment_saturation
properties.description: Global color saturation value of the rendered scene (default value is 1).

properties.name: ambient_light_color
properties.description: [Color] of the ambient light.

properties.name: ambient_light_energy
properties.description: Energy of the ambient light. The higher the value, the stronger the light.

properties.name: ambient_light_sky_contribution
properties.description: Defines the amount of light that the sky brings on the scene. A value of 0 means that the sky's light emission has no effect on the scene illumination, thus all ambient illumination is provided by the ambient light. On the contrary, a value of 1 means that all the light that affects the scene is provided by the sky, thus the ambient light parameter has no effect on the scene.

properties.name: auto_exposure_enabled
properties.description: Enables the tonemapping auto exposure mode of the scene renderer. If activated, the renderer will automatically determine the exposure setting to adapt to the illumination of the scene and the observed light.

properties.name: auto_exposure_max_luma
properties.description: Maximum luminance value for the auto exposure.

properties.name: auto_exposure_min_luma
properties.description: Minimum luminance value for the auto exposure.

properties.name: auto_exposure_scale
properties.description: Scale of the auto exposure effect. Affects the intensity of auto exposure.

properties.name: auto_exposure_speed
properties.description: Speed of the auto exposure effect. Affects the time needed for the camera to perform auto exposure.

properties.name: background_canvas_max_layer
properties.description: Maximum layer id (if using Layer background mode).

properties.name: background_color
properties.description: Color displayed for clear areas of the scene (if using Custom color or Color+Sky background modes).

properties.name: background_energy
properties.description: Power of light emitted by the background.

properties.name: background_mode
properties.description: Defines the mode of background.

properties.name: background_sky
properties.description: [Sky] resource defined as background.

properties.name: background_sky_custom_fov
properties.description: [Sky] resource's custom field of view.

properties.name: dof_blur_far_amount
properties.description: Amount of far blur.

properties.name: dof_blur_far_distance
properties.description: Distance from the camera where the far blur effect affects the rendering.

properties.name: dof_blur_far_enabled
properties.description: Enables the far blur effect.

properties.name: dof_blur_far_quality
properties.description: Quality of the far blur quality.

properties.name: dof_blur_far_transition
properties.description: Transition between no-blur area and far blur.

properties.name: dof_blur_near_amount
properties.description: Amount of near blur.

properties.name: dof_blur_near_distance
properties.description: Distance from the camera where the near blur effect affects the rendering.

properties.name: dof_blur_near_enabled
properties.description: Enables the near blur effect.

properties.name: dof_blur_near_quality
properties.description: Quality of the near blur quality.

properties.name: dof_blur_near_transition
properties.description: Transition between near blur and no-blur area.

properties.name: fog_color
properties.description: Fog's [Color].

properties.name: fog_depth_begin
properties.description: Fog's depth starting distance from the camera.

properties.name: fog_depth_curve
properties.description: Value defining the fog depth intensity.

properties.name: fog_depth_enabled
properties.description: Enables the fog depth.

properties.name: fog_enabled
properties.description: Enables the fog. Needs fog_height_enabled and/or for_depth_enabled to actually display fog.

properties.name: fog_height_curve
properties.description: Value defining the fog height intensity.

properties.name: fog_height_enabled
properties.description: Enables the fog height.

properties.name: fog_height_max
properties.description: Maximum height of fog.

properties.name: fog_height_min
properties.description: Minimum height of fog.

properties.name: fog_sun_amount
properties.description: Amount of sun that affects the fog rendering.

properties.name: fog_sun_color
properties.description: Sun [Color].

properties.name: fog_transmit_curve
properties.description: Amount of light that the fog transmits.

properties.name: fog_transmit_enabled
properties.description: Enables fog's light transmission. If enabled, lets reflections light to be transmitted by the fog.

properties.name: glow_blend_mode
properties.description: Glow blending mode.

properties.name: glow_bloom
properties.description: Bloom value (global glow).

properties.name: glow_enabled
properties.description: Enables glow rendering.

properties.name: glow_hdr_scale
properties.description: Bleed scale of the HDR glow.

properties.name: glow_hdr_threshold
properties.description: Bleed threshold of the HDR glow.

properties.name: glow_intensity
properties.description: Glow intensity.

properties.name: glow_levels/1
properties.description: First level of glow (most local).

properties.name: glow_levels/2
properties.description: Second level of glow.

properties.name: glow_levels/3
properties.description: Third level of glow.

properties.name: glow_levels/4
properties.description: Fourth level of glow.

properties.name: glow_levels/5
properties.description: Fifth level of glow.

properties.name: glow_levels/6
properties.description: Sixth level of glow.

properties.name: glow_levels/7
properties.description: Seventh level of glow (most global).

properties.name: glow_strength
properties.description: Glow strength.

properties.name: tonemap_exposure
properties.description: Default exposure for tonemap.

properties.name: tonemap_mode
properties.description: Tonemapping mode.

properties.name: tonemap_white
properties.description: White reference value for tonemap.

Skeleton.name: Skeleton
Skeleton.brief_description: Skeleton for characters and animated objects.
Skeleton.description: Skeleton provides a hierarchical interface for managing bones, including pose, rest and animation (see [Animation]). Skeleton will support rag doll dynamics in the future.

methods.name: add_bone
methods.description: Add a bone, with name "name". [method get_bone_count] will become the bone index.

methods.name: bind_child_node_to_bone
methods.description: Deprecated soon.

methods.name: clear_bones
methods.description: Clear all the bones in this skeleton.

methods.name: find_bone
methods.description: Return the bone index that matches "name" as its name.

methods.name: get_bone_count
methods.description: Return the amount of bones in the skeleton.

methods.name: get_bone_name
methods.description: Return the name of the bone at index "index"

methods.name: get_bone_parent
methods.description: Return the bone index which is the parent of the bone at "bone_idx". If -1, then bone has no parent. Note that the parent bone returned will always be less than "bone_idx".

methods.name: get_bone_pose
methods.description: Return the pose transform for bone "bone_idx".

methods.name: get_bone_rest
methods.description: Return the rest transform for a bone "bone_idx".

methods.name: get_bound_child_nodes_to_bone
methods.description: Deprecated soon.

methods.name: set_bone_parent
methods.description: Set the bone index "parent_idx" as the parent of the bone at "bone_idx". If -1, then bone has no parent. Note: "parent_idx" must be less than "bone_idx".

methods.name: set_bone_pose
methods.description: Return the pose transform for bone "bone_idx".

methods.name: set_bone_rest
methods.description: Set the rest transform for bone "bone_idx"

methods.name: unbind_child_node_from_bone
methods.description: Deprecated soon.

VisualScriptConstructor.name: VisualScriptConstructor
VisualScriptConstructor.brief_description: A Visual Script node which calls a base type constructor.
VisualScriptConstructor.description: A Visual Script node which calls a base type constructor. It can be used for type conversion as well.

Position3D.name: Position3D
Position3D.description: Generic 3D Position hint for editing. It's just like a plain [Spatial] but displays as a cross in the 3D-Editor at all times.

Physics2DDirectBodyState.name: Physics2DDirectBodyState
Physics2DDirectBodyState.brief_description: Direct access object to a physics body in the [Physics2DServer].
Physics2DDirectBodyState.description: Direct access object to a physics body in the [Physics2DServer]. This object is passed via the direct state callback of rigid/character bodies, and is intended for changing the direct state of that body.

methods.name: get_contact_collider
methods.description: Return the [RID] of the collider.

methods.name: get_contact_collider_id
methods.description: Return the object id of the collider.

methods.name: get_contact_collider_object
methods.description: Return the collider object, this depends on how it was created (will return a scene node if such was used to create it).

methods.name: get_contact_collider_position
methods.description: Return the contact position in the collider.

methods.name: get_contact_collider_shape
methods.description: Return the collider shape index.

methods.name: get_contact_collider_shape_metadata
methods.description: Return the metadata of the collided shape. This metadata is different from [method Object.get_meta], and is set with [method Physics2DServer.shape_set_data].

methods.name: get_contact_collider_velocity_at_position
methods.description: Return the linear velocity vector at contact point of the collider.

methods.name: get_contact_count
methods.description: Return the amount of contacts this body has with other bodies. Note that by default this returns 0 unless bodies are configured to log contacts.

methods.name: get_contact_local_normal
methods.description: Return the local normal (of this body) of the contact point.

methods.name: get_contact_local_position
methods.description: Return the local position (of this body) of the contact point.

methods.name: get_contact_local_shape
methods.description: Return the local shape index of the collision.

methods.name: get_space_state
methods.description: Return the current state of space, useful for queries.

methods.name: integrate_forces
methods.description: Call the built-in force integration code.

properties.name: angular_velocity
properties.description: The angular velocity of the body.

properties.name: inverse_inertia
properties.description: The inverse of the inertia of the body.

properties.name: inverse_mass
properties.description: The inverse of the mass of the body.

properties.name: linear_velocity
properties.description: The linear velocity of the body.

properties.name: sleeping
properties.description: [code]true[/code] if this body is currently sleeping (not active).

properties.name: step
properties.description: The timestep (delta) used for the simulation.

properties.name: total_angular_damp
properties.description: The rate at which the body stops rotating, if there are not any other forces moving it.

properties.name: total_gravity
properties.description: The total gravity vector being currently applied to this body.

properties.name: total_linear_damp
properties.description: The rate at which the body stops moving, if there are not any other forces moving it.

properties.name: transform
properties.description: The transformation matrix of the body.

BaseButton.name: BaseButton
BaseButton.brief_description: Base class for different kinds of buttons.
BaseButton.description: BaseButton is the abstract base class for buttons, so it shouldn't be used directly (it doesn't display anything). Other types of buttons inherit from it.

methods.name: _pressed
methods.description: Called when button is pressed.

methods.name: _toggled
methods.description: Called when button is toggled (only if toggle_mode is active).

methods.name: get_draw_mode
methods.description: Return the visual state used to draw the button. This is useful mainly when implementing your own draw code by either overriding _draw() or connecting to "draw" signal. The visual state of the button is defined by the DRAW_* enum.

methods.name: is_hovered
methods.description: Return true if mouse entered the button before it exit.

signals.name: button_down
signals.description: Emitted when the button starts being held down.

signals.name: button_up
signals.description: Emitted when the button stops being held down.

signals.name: pressed
signals.description: This signal is emitted every time the button is toggled or pressed (i.e. activated, so on [code]button_down[/code] if "Click on press" is active and on [code]button_up[/code] otherwise).

signals.name: toggled
signals.description: This signal is emitted when the button was just toggled between pressed and normal states (only if toggle_mode is active). The new state is contained in the [i]pressed[/i] argument.

constants.name: DRAW_NORMAL
constants.description: The normal state (i.e. not pressed, not hovered, not toggled and enabled) of buttons.

constants.name: DRAW_PRESSED
constants.description: The state of buttons are pressed.

constants.name: DRAW_HOVER
constants.description: The state of buttons are hovered.

constants.name: DRAW_DISABLED
constants.description: The state of buttons are disabled.

constants.name: ACTION_MODE_BUTTON_PRESS
constants.description: Require just a press to consider the button clicked.

constants.name: ACTION_MODE_BUTTON_RELEASE
constants.description: Require a press and a subsequent release before considering the button clicked.

properties.name: action_mode
properties.description: Determines when the button is considered clicked, one of the ACTION_MODE_* constants.

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the button is in disabled state and can't be clicked or toggled.

properties.name: enabled_focus_mode
properties.description: Focus access mode to use when switching between enabled/disabled (see [method Control.set_focus_mode] and [member disabled]).

properties.name: group
properties.description: [ButtonGroup] associated to the button.

properties.name: pressed
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the button's state is pressed. Means the button is pressed down or toggled (if toggle_mode is active).

properties.name: shortcut
properties.description: [Shortcut] associated to the button.

properties.name: toggle_mode
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the button is in toggle mode. Makes the button flip state between pressed and unpressed each time its area is clicked.

InputMap.name: InputMap
InputMap.description: Manages all [InputEventAction] which can be created/modified from the project settings menu [code]Project > Project Settings > Input Map[/code] or in code with [method add_action] and [method action_add_event]. See [method Node._input].

methods.name: action_add_event
methods.description: Adds an [InputEvent] to an action. This [InputEvent] will trigger the action.

methods.name: action_erase_event
methods.description: Removes an [InputEvent] from an action.

methods.name: action_has_event
methods.description: Returns [true] if an action has an [InputEvent] associated with it.

methods.name: add_action
methods.description: Adds an (empty) action to the [code]InputMap[/code]. An [InputEvent] can then be added to this action with [method action_add_event].

methods.name: erase_action
methods.description: Removes an action from the [code]InputMap[/code].

methods.name: event_is_action
methods.description: Returns [true] if the given event is part of an existing action. This method ignores keyboard modifiers if the given [InputEvent] is not pressed (for proper release detection). See [method action_has_event] if you don't want this behavior.

methods.name: get_action_list
methods.description: Returns an array of [InputEvent]s associated with a given action.

methods.name: get_actions
methods.description: Returns an array of all actions in the [code]InputMap[/code].

methods.name: has_action
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the [code]InputMap[/code] has a registered action with the given name.

methods.name: load_from_globals
methods.description: Clears all [InputEventAction] in the [code]InputMap[/code] and load it anew from [ProjectSettings].

OS.name: OS
OS.description: Operating System functions. OS Wraps the most common functionality to communicate with the host Operating System, such as: mouse grabbing, mouse cursors, clipboard, video mode, date and time, timers, environment variables, execution of binaries, command line, etc.

methods.name: alert
methods.description: Displays a modal dialog box utilizing the host OS.

methods.name: can_draw
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the host OS allows drawing.

methods.name: can_use_threads
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the current host platform is using multiple threads.

methods.name: delay_msec
methods.description: Delay executing of the current thread by given milliseconds.

methods.name: delay_usec
methods.description: Delay executing of the current thread by given microseconds.

methods.name: dump_memory_to_file
methods.description:
Dumps the memory allocation ringlist to a file (only works in debug).
				Entry format per line: "Address - Size - Description"

methods.name: dump_resources_to_file
methods.description:
Dumps all used resources to file (only works in debug).
				Entry format per line: "Resource Type : Resource Location"
				At the end of the file is a statistic of all used Resource Types.

methods.name: execute
methods.description:
Execute the file at the given path, optionally blocking until it returns.
				Platform path resolution will take place.  The resolved file must exist and be executable.
				Returns a process id.
				For example:
				[codeblock]
				var output = []
				var pid = OS.execute('ls', [], true, output)
				[/codeblock]
				If you wish to access a shell built-in or perform a composite command, a platform specific shell can be invoked.  For example:
				[codeblock]
				var pid = OS.execute('CMD.exe', ['/C', 'cd %TEMP% && dir'], true, output)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: find_scancode_from_string
methods.description: Returns the scancode of the given string (e.g. "Escape")

methods.name: get_cmdline_args
methods.description: Returns the command line arguments passed to the engine.

methods.name: get_date
methods.description: Returns current date as a dictionary of keys: year, month, day, weekday, dst (daylight savings time).

methods.name: get_datetime
methods.description: Returns current datetime as a dictionary of keys: year, month, day, weekday, dst (daylight savings time), hour, minute, second.

methods.name: get_datetime_from_unix_time
methods.description:
Get a dictionary of time values when given epoch time.
				Dictionary Time values will be a union of values from [method get_time] and [method get_date] dictionaries (with the exception of dst = day light standard time, as it cannot be determined from epoch).

methods.name: get_dynamic_memory_usage
methods.description: Returns the total amount of dynamic memory used (only works in debug).

methods.name: get_environment
methods.description: Returns an environment variable.

methods.name: get_executable_path
methods.description: Returns the path to the current engine executable.

methods.name: get_latin_keyboard_variant
methods.description:
Returns the current latin keyboard variant as a String.
				Possible return values are: "QWERTY", "AZERTY", "QZERTY", "DVORAK", "NEO", "COLEMAK" or "ERROR".

methods.name: get_locale
methods.description: Returns the host OS locale.

methods.name: get_model_name
methods.description: Returns the model name of the current device.

methods.name: get_name
methods.description: Returns the name of the host OS. Possible values are: "Android", "Haiku", "iOS", "HTML5", "OSX", "Server", "Windows", "UWP", "X11".

methods.name: get_power_percent_left
methods.description: Returns the amount of battery left in the device as a percentage.

methods.name: get_power_seconds_left
methods.description: Returns the time in seconds before the device runs out of battery.

methods.name: get_power_state
methods.description: Returns the current state of the device regarding battery and power. See [code]POWERSTATE_*[/code] constants.

methods.name: get_process_id
methods.description: Returns the game process ID

methods.name: get_processor_count
methods.description: Returns the number of cores available in the host machine.

methods.name: get_scancode_string
methods.description: Returns the given scancode as a string (e.g. Return values: "Escape", "Shift+Escape").

methods.name: get_screen_count
methods.description: Returns the number of displays attached to the host machine.

methods.name: get_screen_dpi
methods.description:
Returns the dots per inch density of the specified screen.

				On Android Devices, the actual screen densities are grouped into six generalized densities:
					ldpi    - 120 dpi
					mdpi    - 160 dpi
					hdpi    - 240 dpi
					xhdpi   - 320 dpi
					xxhdpi  - 480 dpi
					xxxhdpi - 640 dpi

methods.name: get_screen_position
methods.description: Returns the position of the specified screen by index. If no screen index is provided, the current screen will be used.

methods.name: get_screen_size
methods.description: Returns the dimensions in pixels of the specified screen.

methods.name: get_static_memory_peak_usage
methods.description: Returns the max amount of static memory used (only works in debug).

methods.name: get_static_memory_usage
methods.description: Returns the amount of static memory being used by the program in bytes.

methods.name: get_system_dir
methods.description: Returns the actual path to commonly used folders across different platforms. Available locations are specified in [OS.SystemDir].

methods.name: get_system_time_secs
methods.description: Returns the epoch time of the operating system in seconds.

methods.name: get_ticks_msec
methods.description: Returns the amount of time passed in milliseconds since the engine started.

methods.name: get_time
methods.description: Returns current time as a dictionary of keys: hour, minute, second.

methods.name: get_time_zone_info
methods.description: Returns the current time zone as a dictionary with the keys: bias and name.

methods.name: get_unique_id
methods.description: Returns a string that is unique to the device. Currently only works on Android and iOS. Returns empty string on other platforms.

methods.name: get_unix_time
methods.description: Return	the current unix timestamp.

methods.name: get_unix_time_from_datetime
methods.description:
Get an epoch time value from a dictionary of time values.
				[code]datetime[/code] must be populated with the following keys: year, month, day, hour, minute, second.
				You can pass the output from [method get_datetime_from_unix_time] directly into this function. Daylight savings time (dst), if present, is ignored.

methods.name: get_user_data_dir
methods.description: Returns the absolute directory path where user data is written ([code]user://[/code]).

methods.name: has_environment
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if an environment variable exists.

methods.name: has_touchscreen_ui_hint
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the device has a touchscreen or emulates one.

methods.name: has_virtual_keyboard
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the platform has a virtual keyboard, [code]false[/code] otherwise.

methods.name: hide_virtual_keyboard
methods.description: Hides the virtual keyboard if it is shown, does nothing otherwise.

methods.name: is_debug_build
methods.description:
Returns [code]true[/code] if the build is a debug build.
				Returns [code]true[/code] when running in the editor.
				Returns [code]false[/code] if the build is a release build.

methods.name: is_ok_left_and_cancel_right
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the "Okay" button should appear on the left and "Cancel" on the right.

methods.name: is_scancode_unicode
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the input code has a unicode character.

methods.name: is_stdout_verbose
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the engine was executed with -v (verbose stdout).

methods.name: is_userfs_persistent
methods.description: If [code]true[/code], the [code]user://[/code] file system is persistent, so that its state is the same after a player quits and starts the game again. Relevant to the HTML5 platform, where this persistence may be unavailable.

methods.name: kill
methods.description: Kill a process ID (this method can be used to kill processes that were not spawned by the game).

methods.name: native_video_is_playing
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if native video is playing.

methods.name: native_video_pause
methods.description: Pauses native video playback.

methods.name: native_video_play
methods.description: Plays native video from the specified path, at the given volume and with audio and subtitle tracks.

methods.name: native_video_stop
methods.description: Stops native video playback.

methods.name: native_video_unpause
methods.description: Resumes native video playback.

methods.name: print_all_resources
methods.description: Shows all resources in the game. Optionally the list can be written to a file.

methods.name: print_all_textures_by_size
methods.description: Shows the list of loaded textures sorted by size in memory.

methods.name: print_resources_by_type
methods.description: Shows the number of resources loaded by the game of the given types.

methods.name: print_resources_in_use
methods.description: Shows all resources currently used by the game.

methods.name: request_attention
methods.description: Request the user attention to the window. It'll flash the taskbar button on Windows or bounce the dock icon on OSX.

methods.name: set_icon
methods.description: Sets the game's icon.

methods.name: set_thread_name
methods.description: Sets the name of the current thread.

methods.name: set_use_file_access_save_and_swap
methods.description: Enables backup saves if [code]enabled[/code] is [code]true[/code].

methods.name: set_window_title
methods.description: Sets the window title to the specified string.

methods.name: shell_open
methods.description:
Requests the OS to open a resource with the most appropriate program. For example.
					[code]OS.shell_open("C:\\Users\name\Downloads")[/code] on Windows opens the file explorer at the downloads folders of the user.
					[code]OS.shell_open("http://godotengine.org")[/code] opens the default web browser on the official Godot website.

methods.name: show_virtual_keyboard
methods.description: Shows the virtual keyboard if the platform has one. The [i]existing_text[/i] parameter is useful for implementing your own LineEdit, as it tells the virtual keyboard what text has already been typed (the virtual keyboard uses it for auto-correct and predictions).

properties.name: clipboard
properties.description: The clipboard from the host OS. Might be unavailable on some platforms.

properties.name: current_screen
properties.description: The current screen index (starting from 0).

properties.name: screen_orientation
properties.description: The current screen orientation.

properties.name: window_borderless
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], removes the window frame.

properties.name: window_fullscreen
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], the window is fullscreen.

properties.name: window_maximized
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], the window is maximized.

properties.name: window_minimized
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], the window is minimized.

properties.name: window_position
properties.description: The window position relative to the screen, the origin is the top left corner, +Y axis goes to the bottom and +X axis goes to the right.

properties.name: window_resizable
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], the window is resizable by the user.

properties.name: window_size
properties.description: The size of the window (without counting window manager decorations).

NetworkedMultiplayerENet.name: NetworkedMultiplayerENet
NetworkedMultiplayerENet.brief_description: PacketPeer implementation using the ENet library.
NetworkedMultiplayerENet.description: A connection (or a listening server) that should be passed to [method SceneTree.set_network_peer]. Socket events can be handled by connecting to [SceneTree] signals.

methods.name: create_client
methods.description: Create client that connects to a server at address [code]ip[/code] using specified [code]port[/code].

methods.name: create_server
methods.description: Create server that listens to connections via [code]port[/code].

AudioEffectAmplify.name: AudioEffectAmplify
AudioEffectAmplify.brief_description:
Adds a Amplify audio effect to an Audio bus.
		Increases or decreases the volume of the selected audio bus.
AudioEffectAmplify.description: Increases or decreases the volume being routed through the audio bus.

properties.name: volume_db
properties.description: Amount of amplification. Positive values make the sound louder, negative values make it quieter. Value can range from -80 to 24. Default value: [code]0[/code].

StreamTexture.name: StreamTexture
StreamTexture.description: A texture that is loaded from a .stex file.

properties.name: load_path
properties.description: The StreamTexture's filepath to a .stex file.

InputEventWithModifiers.name: InputEventWithModifiers
InputEventWithModifiers.brief_description: Base class for keys events with modifiers.
InputEventWithModifiers.description: Contains keys events information with modifiers support like [code]SHIFT[/code] or [code]ALT[/code]. See [method Node._input].

properties.name: alt
properties.description: State of the Alt modifier.

properties.name: command
properties.description: State of the Command modifier.

properties.name: control
properties.description: State of the Ctrl modifier.

properties.name: meta
properties.description: State of the Meta modifier.

properties.name: shift
properties.description: State of the Shift modifier.

Reference.name: Reference
Reference.brief_description: Base class for anything that keeps a reference count.
Reference.description: Base class for anything that keeps a reference count. Resource and many other helper objects inherit this. References keep an internal reference counter so they are only released when no longer in use.

methods.name: reference
methods.description: Increase the internal reference counter. Use this only if you really know what you are doing.

methods.name: unreference
methods.description: Decrease the internal reference counter. Use this only if you really know what you are doing.

Light.name: Light
Light.brief_description: Provides a base class for different kinds of light nodes.
Light.description: Light is the abstract base class for light nodes, so it shouldn't be used directly (It can't be instanced). Other types of light nodes inherit from it. Light contains the common variables and parameters used for lighting.

EditorPlugin.name: EditorPlugin
EditorPlugin.brief_description: Used by the editor to extend its functionality.
EditorPlugin.description: Plugins are used by the editor to extend functionality. The most common types of plugins are those which edit a given node or resource type, import plugins and export plugins.

methods.name: add_control_to_bottom_panel
methods.description: Add a control to the bottom panel (together with Output, Debug, Animation, etc). Returns a reference to the button added. It's up to you to hide/show the button when needed. If your plugin is being removed, also make sure to remove your control by calling [method remove_control_from_bottom_panel].

methods.name: add_control_to_container
methods.description:
Add a custom control to a container (see CONTAINER_* enum). There are many locations where custom controls can be added in the editor UI.
				Please remember that you have to manage the visibility of your custom controls yourself (and likely hide it after adding it).
				If your plugin is being removed, also make sure to remove your custom controls too.

methods.name: add_control_to_dock
methods.description:
Add the control to a specific dock slot (see DOCK_* enum for options).
				If the dock is repositioned and as long as the plugin is active, the editor will save the dock position on further sessions.
				If your plugin is being removed, also make sure to remove your control by calling [method remove_control_from_docks].

methods.name: add_custom_type
methods.description:
Add a custom type, which will appear in the list of nodes or resources. An icon can be optionally passed.
				When given node or resource is selected, the base type will be instanced (ie, "Spatial", "Control", "Resource"), then the script will be loaded and set to this object.
				You can use the [method EditorPlugin.handles] to check if your custom object is being edited by checking the script or using 'is' keyword.
				During run-time, this will be a simple object with a script so this function does not need to be called then.

methods.name: apply_changes
methods.description:
This method is called when the editor is about to save the project, switch to another tab, etc. It asks the plugin to apply any pending state changes to ensure consistency.
				This is used, for example, in shader editors to let the plugin know that it must apply the shader code being written by the user to the object.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear all the state and reset the object being edited to zero. This ensures your plugin does not keep editing a currently existing node, or a node from the wrong scene.

methods.name: create_spatial_gizmo
methods.description: This is used for plugins that create gizmos used by the spatial editor. Just check that the node passed in the "for_spatial" argument matches your plugin.

methods.name: edit
methods.description: This function is used for plugins that edit specific object types (nodes or resources). It requests the editor to edit the given object.

methods.name: forward_spatial_gui_input
methods.description:
Implement this function if you are interested in 3D view screen input events. It will be called only if currently selected node is handled by your plugin.
				If you would like to always gets those input events then additionally use [method set_input_forwarding_always_enabled].

methods.name: get_breakpoints
methods.description: This is for editors that edit script based objects. You can return a list of breakpoints in the format (script:line), for example: res://path_to_script.gd:25

methods.name: get_state
methods.description: Get the state of your plugin editor. This is used when saving the scene (so state is kept when opening it again) and for switching tabs (so state can be restored when the tab returns).

methods.name: get_undo_redo
methods.description: Get the undo/redo object. Most actions in the editor can be undoable, so use this object to make sure this happens when it's worth it.

methods.name: get_window_layout
methods.description: Get the GUI layout of the plugin. This is used to save the project's editor layout when the [method EditorPlugin.queue_save_layout] is called or the editor layout was changed(For example changing the position of a dock).

methods.name: handles
methods.description: Implement this function if your plugin edits a specific type of object (Resource or Node). If you return true, then you will get the functions [method EditorPlugin.edit] and [method EditorPlugin.make_visible] called when the editor requests them.

methods.name: has_main_screen
methods.description: Return true if this is a main screen editor plugin (it goes in the main screen selector together with 2D, 3D, Script).

methods.name: make_visible
methods.description:
This function will be called when the editor is requested to become visible. It is used for plugins that edit a specific object type.
				Remember that you have to manage the visibility of all your editor controls manually.

methods.name: queue_save_layout
methods.description: Queue save the project's editor layout.

methods.name: remove_control_from_bottom_panel
methods.description: Remove the control from the bottom panel. Don't forget to call this if you added one, so the editor can remove it cleanly.

methods.name: remove_control_from_docks
methods.description: Remove the control from the dock. Don't forget to call this if you added one, so the editor can save the layout and remove it cleanly.

methods.name: remove_custom_type
methods.description: Remove a custom type added by [method EditorPlugin.add_custom_type]

methods.name: save_external_data
methods.description: This method is called after the editor saves the project or when it's closed. It asks the plugin to save edited external scenes/resources.

methods.name: set_input_event_forwarding_always_enabled
methods.description: Use this method if you always want to receive inputs from 3D view screen inside [method forward_spatial_gui_input]. It might be especially usable if your plugin will want to use raycast in the scene.

methods.name: set_state
methods.description: Restore the state saved by [method EditorPlugin.get_state].

methods.name: set_window_layout
methods.description: Restore the plugin GUI layout saved by [method EditorPlugin.get_window_layout].

signals.name: main_screen_changed
signals.description: Emitted when user change main screen view (2D, 3D, Script, AssetLib). Works also with screens which are defined by plugins.

signals.name: scene_changed
signals.description: Emitted when user change scene. The argument is a root node of freshly opened scene.

signals.name: scene_closed
signals.description: Emitted when user close scene. The argument is file path to a closed scene.

Quat.name: Quat
Quat.description:
A 4-dimensional vector representing a rotation.
		The vector represents a 4 dimensional complex number where multiplication of the basis elements is not commutative (multiplying i with j gives a different result than multiplying j with i).
		Multiplying quaternions reproduces rotation sequences. However quaternions need to be often renormalized, or else they suffer from precision issues.
		It can be used to perform SLERP (spherical-linear interpolation) between two rotations.

methods.name: Quat
methods.description: Returns a quaternion defined by these values.

methods.name: Quat
methods.description: Returns a quaternion that will rotate around the given axis by the specified angle. The axis must be a normalized vector.

methods.name: Quat
methods.description: Returns the rotation matrix corresponding to the given quaternion.

methods.name: cubic_slerp
methods.description: Performs a cubic spherical-linear interpolation with another quaternion.

methods.name: dot
methods.description: Returns the dot product of two quaternions.

methods.name: inverse
methods.description: Returns the inverse of the quaternion.

methods.name: is_normalized
methods.description: Returns whether the quaternion is normalized or not.

methods.name: length
methods.description: Returns the length of the quaternion.

methods.name: length_squared
methods.description: Returns the length of the quaternion, squared.

methods.name: normalized
methods.description: Returns a copy of the quaternion, normalized to unit length.

methods.name: slerp
methods.description: Performs a spherical-linear interpolation with another quaternion.

methods.name: slerpni
methods.description: Performs a spherical-linear interpolation with another quaterion without checking if the rotation path is not bigger than 90.

methods.name: xform
methods.description: Transforms the vector [code]v[/code] by this quaternion.

properties.name: w
properties.description: W component of the quaternion. Default value: [code]1[/code]

properties.name: x
properties.description: X component of the quaternion. Default value: [code]0[/code]

properties.name: y
properties.description: Y component of the quaternion. Default value: [code]0[/code]

properties.name: z
properties.description: Z component of the quaternion. Default value: [code]0[/code]

methods.name: add_filter
methods.description:
Adds a comma-delimited file extension filter option to the [code]EditorFileDialog[/code] with an optional semi-colon-delimited label.
				Example: "*.tscn, *.scn; Scenes", results in filter text "Scenes (*.tscn, *.scn)".

methods.name: clear_filters
methods.description: Removes all filters except for "All Files (*)".

methods.name: get_vbox
methods.description: Returns the [code]VBoxContainer[/code] used to display the file system.

methods.name: invalidate
methods.description: Notify the [code]EditorFileDialog[/code] that its view of the data is no longer accurate. Updates the view contents on next view update.

signals.name: dir_selected
signals.description: Emitted when a directory is selected.

signals.name: file_selected
signals.description: Emitted when a file is selected.

signals.name: files_selected
signals.description: Emitted when multiple files are selected.

constants.name: MODE_OPEN_FILE
constants.description: The [code]EditorFileDialog[/code] can select only one file. Accepting the window will open the file.

constants.name: MODE_OPEN_FILES
constants.description: The [code]EditorFileDialog[/code] can select multiple files. Accepting the window will open all files.

constants.name: MODE_OPEN_DIR
constants.description: The [code]EditorFileDialog[/code] can select only one directory. Accepting the window will open the directory.

constants.name: MODE_OPEN_ANY
constants.description: The [code]EditorFileDialog[/code] can select a file or directory. Accepting the window will open it.

constants.name: MODE_SAVE_FILE
constants.description: The [code]EditorFileDialog[/code] can select only one file. Accepting the window will save the file.

constants.name: ACCESS_RESOURCES
constants.description: The [code]EditorFileDialog[/code] can only view [code]res://[/code] directory contents.

constants.name: ACCESS_USERDATA
constants.description: The [code]EditorFileDialog[/code] can only view [code]user://[/code] directory contents.

constants.name: ACCESS_FILESYSTEM
constants.description: The [code]EditorFileDialog[/code] can view the entire local file system.

constants.name: DISPLAY_THUMBNAILS
constants.description: The [code]EditorFileDialog[/code] displays resources as thumbnails.

constants.name: DISPLAY_LIST
constants.description: The [code]EditorFileDialog[/code] displays resources as a list of filenames.

properties.name: access
properties.description: The location from which the user may select a file, including [code]res://[/code], [code]user://[/code], and the local file system.

properties.name: current_dir
properties.description: The currently occupied directory.

properties.name: current_file
properties.description: The currently selected file.

properties.name: current_path
properties.description: The file system path in the address bar.

properties.name: disable_overwrite_warning
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the [code]EditorFileDialog[/code] will not warn the user before overwriting files.

properties.name: display_mode
properties.description: The view format in which the [code]EditorFileDialog[/code] displays resources to the user.

properties.name: mode
properties.description: The purpose of the [code]EditorFileDialog[/code]. Changes allowed behaviors.

properties.name: show_hidden_files
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] hidden files and directories will be visible in the [code]EditorFileDialog[/code].

YSort.name: YSort
YSort.brief_description: Sort all child nodes based on their Y positions.
YSort.description: Sort all child nodes based on their Y positions. The child node must inherit from [CanvasItem] for it to be sorted. Nodes that have a higher Y position will be drawn later, so they will appear on top of nodes that have a lower Y position.

LineEdit.name: LineEdit
LineEdit.brief_description: Control that provides single line string editing.
LineEdit.description: LineEdit provides a single line string editor, used for text fields.

methods.name: append_at_cursor
methods.description: Adds [code]text[/code] after the cursor. If the resulting value is longer than [member max_length], nothing happens.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Erases the [LineEdit] text.

methods.name: deselect
methods.description: Clears the current selection.

methods.name: get_menu
methods.description: Returns the [PopupMenu] of this [code]LineEdit[/code]. By default, this menu is displayed when right-clicking on the [LineEdit].

methods.name: menu_option
methods.description: Executes a given action as defined in the MENU_* enum.

methods.name: select
methods.description:
Selects characters inside [LineEdit] between [code]from[/code] and [code]to[/code]. By default [code]from[/code] is at the beginning and [code]to[/code] at the end.
				[codeblock]
				text = "Welcome"
				select()     # Welcome
				select(4)    # ome
				select(2, 5) # lco
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: select_all
methods.description: Selects the whole [String].

signals.name: text_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the text changes.

signals.name: text_entered
signals.description: Emitted when the user presses KEY_ENTER on the [code]LineEdit[/code].

constants.name: ALIGN_LEFT
constants.description: Aligns the text on the left hand side of the [LineEdit].

constants.name: ALIGN_CENTER
constants.description: Centers the text in the middle of the [LineEdit].

constants.name: ALIGN_RIGHT
constants.description: Aligns the text on the right hand side of the [LineEdit].

constants.name: ALIGN_FILL
constants.description: Stretches whitespaces to fit the [LineEdit]'s width.

constants.name: MENU_CUT
constants.description: Cuts (Copies and clears) the selected text.

constants.name: MENU_COPY
constants.description: Copies the selected text.

constants.name: MENU_PASTE
constants.description: Pastes the clipboard text over the selected text (or at the cursor's position).

constants.name: MENU_CLEAR
constants.description: Erases the whole [Linedit] text.

constants.name: MENU_SELECT_ALL
constants.description: Selects the whole [Linedit] text.

constants.name: MENU_UNDO
constants.description: Undoes the previous action.

properties.name: align
properties.description: Text alignment as defined in the ALIGN_* enum.

properties.name: caret_blink
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the caret (visual cursor) blinks.

properties.name: caret_blink_speed
properties.description: Duration (in seconds) of a caret's blinking cycle.

properties.name: caret_position
properties.description: The cursor's position inside the [code]LineEdit[/code]. When set, the text may scroll to accommodate it.

properties.name: context_menu_enabled
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the context menu will appear when right clicked.

properties.name: editable
properties.description: If [code]false[/code] existing text cannot be modified and new text cannot be added.

properties.name: expand_to_text_length
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the [LineEdit] width will increase to stay longer than the [member text]. It will [b]not[/b] compress if the [member text] is shortened.

properties.name: focus_mode
properties.description: Defines how the [LineEdit] can grab focus (Keyboard and mouse, only keyboard, or none). See [code]enum FocusMode[/code] in [Control] for details.

properties.name: max_length
properties.description: Maximum amount of characters that can be entered inside the [LineEdit]. If [code]0[/code], there is no limit.

properties.name: placeholder_alpha
properties.description: Opacity of the [member placeholder_text]. From [code]0[/code] to [code]1[/code].

properties.name: placeholder_text
properties.description: Text shown when the [LineEdit] is empty. It is [b]not[/b] the [LineEdit]'s default value (see [member text]).

properties.name: secret
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] every character is shown as "*".

properties.name: text
properties.description: String value of the [LineEdit].

AABB.name: AABB
AABB.description: AABB consists of a position, a size, and several utility functions. It is typically used for fast overlap tests.

methods.name: AABB
methods.description: Optional constructor, accepts position and size.

methods.name: encloses
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if this [code]AABB[/code] completely encloses another one.

methods.name: expand
methods.description: Returns this [code]AABB[/code] expanded to include a given point.

methods.name: get_area
methods.description: Gets the area of the [code]AABB[/code].

methods.name: get_endpoint
methods.description: Gets the position of the 8 endpoints of the [code]AABB[/code] in space.

methods.name: get_longest_axis
methods.description: Returns the normalized longest axis of the [code]AABB[/code].

methods.name: get_longest_axis_index
methods.description: Returns the index of the longest axis of the [code]AABB[/code] (according to [Vector3]::AXIS* enum).

methods.name: get_longest_axis_size
methods.description: Returns the scalar length of the longest axis of the [code]AABB[/code].

methods.name: get_shortest_axis
methods.description: Returns the normalized shortest axis of the [code]AABB[/code].

methods.name: get_shortest_axis_index
methods.description: Returns the index of the shortest axis of the [code]AABB[/code] (according to [Vector3]::AXIS* enum).

methods.name: get_shortest_axis_size
methods.description: Returns the scalar length of the shortest axis of the [code]AABB[/code].

methods.name: get_support
methods.description: Returns the support point in a given direction. This is useful for collision detection algorithms.

methods.name: grow
methods.description: Returns a copy of the [code]AABB[/code] grown a given amount of units towards all the sides.

methods.name: has_no_area
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the [code]AABB[/code] is flat or empty.

methods.name: has_no_surface
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the [code]AABB[/code] is empty.

methods.name: has_point
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the [code]AABB[/code] contains a point.

methods.name: intersection
methods.description: Returns the intersection between two [code]AABB[/code]. An empty AABB (size 0,0,0) is returned on failure.

methods.name: intersects
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the [code]AABB[/code] overlaps with another.

methods.name: intersects_plane
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the [code]AABB[/code] is on both sides of a plane.

methods.name: intersects_segment
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the [code]AABB[/code] intersects the line segment between [code]from[/code] and [code]to[/code].

methods.name: merge
methods.description: Returns a larger AABB that contains this AABB and [code]with[/code].

properties.name: end
properties.description: Ending corner.

properties.name: position
properties.description: Beginning corner.

properties.name: size
properties.description: Size from position to end.

Button.name: Button
Button.description: Button is the standard themed button. It can contain text and an icon, and will display them according to the current [Theme].

constants.name: ALIGN_LEFT
constants.description: Align the text to the left.

constants.name: ALIGN_CENTER
constants.description: Align the text to the center.

constants.name: ALIGN_RIGHT
constants.description: Align the text to the right.

properties.name: align
properties.description: Text alignment policy for the button's text, use one of the ALIGN_* constants.

properties.name: clip_text
properties.description: When this property is enabled, text that is too large to fit the button is clipped, when disabled the Button will always be wide enough to hold the text. This property is disabled by default.

properties.name: flat
properties.description: Flat buttons don't display decoration.

properties.name: icon
properties.description: Button's icon, if text is present the icon will be placed before the text.

properties.name: text
properties.description: The button's text that will be displayed inside the button's area.

properties.name: bottom_radius
properties.description: Bottom radius of the cylinder. Defaults to 1.0.

properties.name: height
properties.description: Full height of the cylinder. Defaults to 2.0.

properties.name: radial_segments
properties.description: Number of radial segments on the cylinder. Defaults to 64.

properties.name: rings
properties.description: Number of edge rings along the height of the cylinder. Defaults to 4.

properties.name: top_radius
properties.description: Top radius of the cylinder. Defaults to 1.0.

Timer.name: Timer
Timer.description: Counts down a specified interval and emits a signal on reaching 0. Can be set to repeat or "one shot" mode.

methods.name: is_stopped
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the timer is stopped.

methods.name: start
methods.description:
Starts the timer. This also resets the remaining time to [code]wait_time[/code].
				Note: this method will not resume a paused timer. See [method set_paused].

methods.name: stop
methods.description: Stop (cancel) the Timer.

signals.name: timeout
signals.description: Emitted when the Timer reaches 0.

constants.name: TIMER_PROCESS_PHYSICS
constants.description: Update the Timer during the physics step at each frame (fixed framerate processing).

constants.name: TIMER_PROCESS_IDLE
constants.description: Update the Timer during the idle time at each frame.

properties.name: autostart
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], Timer will automatically start when entering the scene tree. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: one_shot
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], Timer will stop when reaching 0. If [code]false[/code], it will restart. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: paused
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], the timer is paused and will not process until it is unpaused again, even if [method start] is called.

properties.name: process_mode
properties.description: Processing mode. Uses TIMER_PROCESS_* constants as value.

properties.name: time_left
properties.description: The timer's remaining time in seconds. Returns 0 if the timer is inactive.

properties.name: wait_time
properties.description: Wait time in seconds.

PacketPeerUDP.name: PacketPeerUDP
PacketPeerUDP.description: UDP packet peer. Can be used to send raw UDP packets as well as [Variant]s.

methods.name: close
methods.description: Close the UDP socket the [code]PacketPeerUDP[/code] is currently listening on.

methods.name: get_packet_ip
methods.description: Return the IP of the remote peer that sent the last packet(that was received with [method get_packet] or [method get_var]).

methods.name: get_packet_port
methods.description: Return the port of the remote peer that sent the last packet(that was received with [method get_packet] or [method get_var]).

methods.name: is_listening
methods.description: Return whether this [code]PacketPeerUDP[/code] is listening.

methods.name: listen
methods.description:
Make this [code]PacketPeerUDP[/code] listen on the "port" binding to "bind_address" with a buffer size "recv_buf_size".
				If "bind_address" is set as "*" (default), the peer will listen on all available addresses (both IPv4 and IPv6).
				If "bind_address" is set as "0.0.0.0" (for IPv4) or "::" (for IPv6), the peer will listen on all available addresses matching that IP type.
				If "bind_address" is set to any valid address (e.g. "192.168.1.101", "::1", etc), the peer will only listen on the interface with that addresses (or fail if no interface with the given address exists).

methods.name: set_dest_address
methods.description: Set the destination address and port for sending packets and variables, a hostname will be resolved using if valid.

methods.name: wait
methods.description: Wait for a packet to arrive on the listening port, see [method listen].

Transform.name: Transform
Transform.description: Represents one or many transformations in 3D space such as translation, rotation, or scaling. It consists of a [Basis] "basis" and an [Vector3] "origin". It is similar to a 3x4 matrix.

methods.name: Transform
methods.description: Constructs the Transform from four [Vector3]. Each axis corresponds to local basis vectors (some of which may be scaled).

methods.name: Transform
methods.description: Constructs the Transform from a [Basis] and [Vector3].

methods.name: Transform
methods.description: Constructs the Transform from a [Transform2D].

methods.name: Transform
methods.description: Constructs the Transform from a [Quat]. The origin will be Vector3(0, 0, 0).

methods.name: Transform
methods.description: Constructs the Transform from a [Basis]. The origin will be Vector3(0, 0, 0).

methods.name: affine_inverse
methods.description: Returns the inverse of the transform, under the assumption that the transformation is composed of rotation, scaling and translation.

methods.name: interpolate_with
methods.description: Interpolates the transform to other Transform by weight amount (0-1).

methods.name: inverse
methods.description: Returns the inverse of the transform, under the assumption that the transformation is composed of rotation and translation (no scaling, use affine_inverse for transforms with scaling).

methods.name: looking_at
methods.description: Rotate the transform around the up vector to face the target.

methods.name: orthonormalized
methods.description: Returns the transform with the basis orthogonal (90 degrees), and normalized axis vectors.

methods.name: rotated
methods.description: Rotates the transform around given axis by phi. The axis must be a normalized vector.

methods.name: scaled
methods.description: Scales the transform by the specified 3D scaling factors.

methods.name: translated
methods.description: Translates the transform by the specified offset.

methods.name: xform
methods.description: Transforms the given [Vector3], [Plane], or [AABB] by this transform.

methods.name: xform_inv
methods.description: Inverse-transforms the given [Vector3], [Plane], or [AABB] by this transform.

properties.name: basis
properties.description: The basis is a matrix containing 3 [Vector3] as its columns: X axis, Y axis, and Z axis. These vectors can be interpreted as the basis vectors of local coordinate system traveling with the object.

properties.name: origin
properties.description: The translation offset of the transform.

InputEventKey.name: InputEventKey
InputEventKey.brief_description: Input event type for keyboard events.
InputEventKey.description: Stores key presses on the keyboard. Supports key presses, key releases and [member echo] events.

properties.name: echo
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the key was already pressed before this event. It means the user is holding the key down.

properties.name: pressed
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the key's state is pressed. If [code]false[/code] the key's state is released.

properties.name: scancode
properties.description: Key scancode, one of the [code]KEY_*[/code] constants in [@global Scope].

properties.name: unicode
properties.description: Key unicode identifier when relevant.

VisualScriptIterator.name: VisualScriptIterator
VisualScriptIterator.brief_description: Steps through items in a given input.
VisualScriptIterator.description:
This node steps through each item in a given input. Input can be any sequence data type, such as an [Array] or [String]. When each item has been processed, execution passed out the [code]exit[/code] Sequence port.
		[b]Input Ports:[/b]
		- Sequence: [code]for (elem) in (input)[/code]
		- Data (variant): [code]input[/code]
		[b]Output Ports:[/b]
		- Sequence: [code]each[/code]
		- Sequence: [code]exit[/code]
		- Data (variant): [code]elem[/code]

MultiMesh.name: MultiMesh
MultiMesh.description:
MultiMesh provides low level mesh instancing. If the amount of [Mesh] instances needed goes from hundreds to thousands (and most need to be visible at close proximity) creating such a large amount of [MeshInstance] nodes may affect performance by using too much CPU or video memory.
		For this case a MultiMesh becomes very useful, as it can draw thousands of instances with little API overhead.
		As a drawback, if the instances are too far away of each other, performance may be reduced as every single instance will always rendered (they are spatially indexed as one, for the whole object).
		Since instances may have any behavior, the AABB used for visibility must be provided by the user.

methods.name: get_aabb
methods.description: Return the visibility AABB.

methods.name: get_instance_color
methods.description: Get the color of a specific instance.

methods.name: get_instance_transform
methods.description: Return the transform of a specific instance.

methods.name: set_instance_color
methods.description: Set the color of a specific instance.

methods.name: set_instance_transform
methods.description: Set the transform for a specific instance.

AudioEffectCompressor.name: AudioEffectCompressor
AudioEffectCompressor.brief_description:
Adds a Compressor audio effect to an Audio bus.
		Reduces sounds that exceed a certain threshold level, smooths out the dynamics and increases the overall volume.
AudioEffectCompressor.description:
Dynamic range compressor reduces the level of the sound when the amplitude goes over a certain threshold in Decibels. One of the main uses of a compressor is to increase the dynamic range by clipping as little as possible (when sound goes over 0dB).
		Compressor has many uses in the mix:
		- In the Master bus to compress the whole output (Although a [AudioEffectLimiter] is probably better)
		- In voice channels to ensure they sound as balanced as possible.
		- Sidechained. Sidechained, which can reduce the sound level sidechained with another audio bus for threshold detection.. This technique is very common in video game mixing to download the level of Music/SFX while voices are being heard.
		- Accentuates transients by using a wider attack, making effects sound more punchy.

properties.name: attack_us
properties.description: Compressor's reaction time when the signal exceeds the threshold. Value can range from 20 to 2000. Default value: [code]20ms[/code].

properties.name: gain
properties.description: Gain applied to the output signal.

properties.name: mix
properties.description: Balance between original signal and effect signal. Value can range from 0 (totally dry) to 1 (totally wet). Default value: [code]1[/code].

properties.name: ratio
properties.description: Amount of compression applied to the audio once it passes the threshold level. The higher the ratio the more the loud parts of the audio will be compressed. Value can range from 1 to 48. Default value: [code]4[/code].

properties.name: release_ms
properties.description: Compressor's delay time to stop reducing the signal after the signal level falls below the threshold. Value can range from 20 to 2000. Default value: [code]250ms[/code].

properties.name: sidechain
properties.description: Reduce the sound level using another audio bus for threshold detection.

properties.name: threshold
properties.description: The level above which compression is applied to the audio. Value can range from -60 to 0. Default value: [code]0[/code].

CircleShape2D.name: CircleShape2D
CircleShape2D.description: Circular shape for 2D collisions. This shape is useful for modeling balls or small characters and its collision detection with everything else is very fast.

properties.name: radius
properties.description: The circle's radius.

Particles.name: Particles
Particles.description:
3D particle node used to create a variety of particle systems and effects. [code]Particles[/code] features an emitter that generates some number of particles at a given rate.
		Use the [code]process_material[/code] property to add a [ParticlesMaterial] to configure particle appearance and behavior. Alternatively, you can add a [ShaderMaterial] which will be applied to all particles.

constants.name: DRAW_ORDER_INDEX
constants.description: Particles are drawn in the order emitted.

constants.name: DRAW_ORDER_LIFETIME
constants.description: Particles are drawn in order of remaining lifetime.

constants.name: DRAW_ORDER_VIEW_DEPTH
constants.description: Particles are drawn in order of depth.

properties.name: amount
properties.description: Number of particles to emit.

properties.name: draw_order
properties.description: Particle draw order. Uses [code]DRAW_ORDER_*[/code] values. Default value: [code]DRAW_ORDER_INDEX[/code].

properties.name: emitting
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] particles are being emitted. Default value: [code]true[/code].

properties.name: explosiveness
properties.description: Time ratio between each emission. If [code]0[/code] particles are emitted continuously. If [code]1[/code] all particles are emitted simultaneously. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: lifetime
properties.description: Amount of time each particle will exist. Default value: [code]1[/code].

properties.name: local_coords
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] particles use the parent node's coordinate space. If [code]false[/code] they use global coordinates. Default value: [code]true[/code].

properties.name: one_shot
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] only [code]amount[/code] particles will be emitted. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: process_material
properties.description: [Material] for processing particles. Can be a [ParticlesMaterial] or a [ShaderMaterial].

properties.name: randomness
properties.description: Emission randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: speed_scale
properties.description: Speed scaling ratio. Default value: [code]1[/code].

methods.name: int
methods.description: Cast a [bool] value to an integer value, [code]int(true)[/code] will be equals to 1 and [code]int(false)[/code] will be equals to 0.

methods.name: int
methods.description: Cast a float value to an integer value, this method simply removes the number fractions, so for example [code]int(2.7)[/code] will be equals to 2, [code]int(.1)[/code] will be equals to 0 and [code]int(-2.7)[/code] will be equals to -2.

methods.name: int
methods.description: Cast a [String] value to an integer value, this method is an integer parser from a string, so calling this method with an invalid integer string will return 0, a valid string will be something like [code]'1.7'[/code]. This method will ignore all non-number characters, so calling [code]int('1e3')[/code] will return 13.

ConeTwistJoint.name: ConeTwistJoint
ConeTwistJoint.brief_description: A twist joint between two 3D bodies
ConeTwistJoint.description:
The joint can rotate the bodies across an axis defined by the local x-axes of the [Joint].
		The twist axis is initiated as the x-axis of the [Joint].
		Once the Bodies swing, the twist axis is calculated as the middle of the x-axes of the Joint in the local space of the two Bodies.

constants.name: PARAM_SWING_SPAN
constants.description:
Swing is rotation from side to side, around the axis perpendicular to the twist axis.
			The swing span defines, how much rotation will not get corrected allong the swing axis.
			Could be defined as looseness in the [code]ConeTwistJoint[/code].
			If below 0.05, this behaviour is locked. Default value: [code]PI/4[/code].

constants.name: PARAM_TWIST_SPAN
constants.description:
Twist is the rotation around the twist axis, this value defined how far the joint can twist.
			Twist is locked if below 0.05.

constants.name: PARAM_BIAS
constants.description:
The speed with which the swing or twist will take place.
			The higher, the faster.

constants.name: PARAM_SOFTNESS
constants.description: The ease with which the joint starts to twist. If it's too low, it takes more force to start twisting the joint.

constants.name: PARAM_RELAXATION
constants.description: Defines, how fast the swing- and twist-speed-difference on both sides gets synced.

constants.name: PARAM_MAX
constants.description: End flag of PARAM_* constants, used internally.

properties.name: bias
properties.description:
The speed with which the swing or twist will take place.
			The higher, the faster.

properties.name: relaxation
properties.description: Defines, how fast the swing- and twist-speed-difference on both sides gets synced.

properties.name: softness
properties.description: The ease with which the joint starts to twist. If it's too low, it takes more force to start twisting the joint.

properties.name: swing_span
properties.description:
Swing is rotation from side to side, around the axis perpendicular to the twist axis.
			The swing span defines, how much rotation will not get corrected allong the swing axis.
			Could be defined as looseness in the [code]ConeTwistJoint[/code].
			If below 0.05, this behaviour is locked. Default value: [code]PI/4[/code].

properties.name: twist_span
properties.description:
Twist is the rotation around the twist axis, this value defined how far the joint can twist.
			Twist is locked if below 0.05.

Camera2D.name: Camera2D
Camera2D.description:
Camera node for 2D scenes. It forces the screen (current layer) to scroll following this node. This makes it easier (and faster) to program scrollable scenes than manually changing the position of [CanvasItem] based nodes.
		This node is intended to be a simple helper to get things going quickly and it may happen often that more functionality is desired to change how the camera works. To make your own custom camera node, simply inherit from [Node2D] and change the transform of the canvas by calling get_viewport().set_canvas_transform(m) in [Viewport].

methods.name: align
methods.description: Align the camera to the tracked node

methods.name: clear_current
methods.description: Removes any [code]Camera2D[/code] from the ancestor [Viewport]'s internal currently-assigned camera.

methods.name: force_update_scroll
methods.description: Force the camera to update scroll immediately.

methods.name: get_camera_position
methods.description: Return the camera position.

methods.name: get_camera_screen_center
methods.description: Returns the location of the [code]Camera2D[/code]'s screen-center, relative to the origin.

methods.name: make_current
methods.description: Make this the current 2D camera for the scene (viewport and layer), in case there's many cameras in the scene.

methods.name: reset_smoothing
methods.description:
Set the camera's position immediately to its current smoothing destination.
				This has no effect if smoothing is disabled.

constants.name: ANCHOR_MODE_FIXED_TOP_LEFT
constants.description: The camera's position is fixed so that the top-left corner is always at the origin.

constants.name: ANCHOR_MODE_DRAG_CENTER
constants.description: The camera's position takes into account vertical/horizontal offsets and the screen size.

properties.name: anchor_mode
properties.description: The Camera2D's anchor point. See [code]ANCHOR_MODE_*[/code] constants.

properties.name: current
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the camera is the active camera for the current scene. Only one camera can be current, so setting a different camera [code]current[/code] will disable this one.

properties.name: custom_viewport
properties.description: The custom [Viewport] node attached to the [code]Camera2D[/code]. If null or not a [Viewport], uses the default viewport instead.

properties.name: drag_margin_bottom
properties.description: Bottom margin needed to drag the camera. A value of [code]1[/code] makes the camera move only when reaching the edge of the screen.

properties.name: drag_margin_h_enabled
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the camera only moves when reaching the horizontal drag margins. If [code]false[/code] the camera moves horizontally regardless of margins. Default value: [code]true[/code].

properties.name: drag_margin_left
properties.description: Left margin needed to drag the camera. A value of [code]1[/code] makes the camera move only when reaching the edge of the screen.

properties.name: drag_margin_right
