constants.description: Orthogonal orientation mode.

constants.name: MODE_ISOMETRIC
constants.description: Isometric orientation mode.

constants.name: MODE_CUSTOM
constants.description: Custom orientation mode.

constants.name: HALF_OFFSET_X
constants.description: Half offset on the X coordinate.

constants.name: HALF_OFFSET_Y
constants.description: Half offset on the Y coordinate.

constants.name: HALF_OFFSET_DISABLED
constants.description: Half offset disabled.

constants.name: TILE_ORIGIN_TOP_LEFT
constants.description: Tile origin at its top-left corner.

constants.name: TILE_ORIGIN_CENTER
constants.description: Tile origin at its center.

properties.name: cell_custom_transform
properties.description: The custom [Transform2D] to be applied to the TileMap's cells.

properties.name: cell_half_offset
properties.description: Amount to offset alternating tiles. Uses HALF_OFFSET_* constants. Default value: HALF_OFFSET_DISABLED.

properties.name: cell_quadrant_size
properties.description: The TileMap's quadrant size.  Optimizes drawing by batching, using chunks of this size. Default value: 16.

properties.name: cell_size
properties.description: The TileMap's cell size.

properties.name: cell_tile_origin
properties.description: Position for tile origin. Uses TILE_ORIGIN_* constants. Default value: TILE_ORIGIN_TOP_LEFT.

properties.name: cell_y_sort
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the TileMap's children will be drawn in order of their Y coordinate. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: collision_bounce
properties.description: Bounce value for static body collisions (see [code]collision_use_kinematic[/code]). Default value: 0.

properties.name: collision_friction
properties.description: Friction value for static body collisions (see [code]collision_use_kinematic[/code]). Default value: 1.

properties.name: collision_layer
properties.description: The collision layer(s) for all colliders in the TileMap.

properties.name: collision_mask
properties.description: The collision mask(s) for all colliders in the TileMap.

properties.name: collision_use_kinematic
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] TileMap collisions will be handled as a kinematic body. If [code]false[/code] collisions will be handled as static body. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: mode
properties.description: The TileMap orientation mode. Uses MODE_* constants. Default value: MODE_SQUARE.

properties.name: occluder_light_mask
properties.description: The light mask assigned to all light occluders in the TileMap.  The TileSet's light occluders will cast shadows only from Light2D(s) that have the same light mask(s).

properties.name: tile_set
properties.description: The assigned [TileSet].

methods.description: Return the amount of output [b]sequence[/b] ports.

methods.description: Return the specified [b]sequence[/b] output's name.

methods.description: Return the amount of output value ports.

methods.description: Return the specified output's type. See the TYPE_* enum in [@GlobalScope].

methods.description: Return the custom node's text, which is shown right next to the input [b]sequence[/b] port (if there is none, on the place that is usually taken by it).

methods.name: _get_working_memory_size
methods.description: Return the size of the custom node's working memory. See [method _step] for more details.

methods.name: _has_input_sequence_port
methods.description: Return whether the custom node has an input [b]sequence[/b] port.

methods.name: _step
methods.description:
Execute the custom node's logic, returning the index of the output sequence port to use or a [String] when there is an error.
				
				The [code]inputs[/code] array contains the values of the input ports.
				[code]outputs[/code] is an array whose indices should be set to the respective outputs.
				The [code]start_mode[/code] is usually [code]START_MODE_BEGIN_SEQUENCE[/code], unless you have used the STEP_* constants.
				[code]working_mem[/code] is an array which can be used to persist information between runs of the custom node.
				
				When returning, you can mask the returned value with one of the STEP_* constants.

constants.name: START_MODE_BEGIN_SEQUENCE
constants.description: The start mode used the first time when [method _step] is called.

constants.name: START_MODE_CONTINUE_SEQUENCE
constants.description: The start mode used when [method _step] is called after coming back from a STEP_PUSH_STACK_BIT.

constants.name: START_MODE_RESUME_YIELD
constants.description: The start mode used when [method _step] is called after resuming from STEP_YIELD_BIT.

constants.name: STEP_PUSH_STACK_BIT
constants.description:
Hint used by [method _step] to tell that control should return to it when there is no other node left to execute.
			This is used by [VisualScriptCondition] to redirect the sequence to the "Done" port after the true/false branch has finished execution.

constants.name: STEP_GO_BACK_BIT
constants.description: Hint used by [method _step] to tell that control should return back, either hitting a previous STEP_PUSH_STACK_BIT or exiting the function.

constants.name: STEP_EXIT_FUNCTION_BIT
constants.description: Hint used by [method _step] to tell that control should stop and exit the function.

constants.name: STEP_YIELD_BIT
constants.description:
Hint used by [method _step] to tell that the function should be yielded.
			Using this requires you to have at least one working memory slot, which is used for the [VisualScriptFunctionState].

AnimationTreePlayer.name: AnimationTreePlayer
AnimationTreePlayer.brief_description: Animation Player that uses a node graph for blending Animations.
AnimationTreePlayer.description:
A node graph tool for blending multiple animations bound to an [AnimationPlayer]. Especially useful for animating characters or other skeleton-based rigs. It can combine several animations to form a desired pose.
		It takes [Animation]s from an [AnimationPlayer] node and mixes them depending on the graph.

methods.name: add_node
methods.description: Adds a [code]type[/code] node to the graph with name [code]id[/code].

methods.name: advance
methods.description: Shifts position in the animation timeline. Delta is the time in seconds to shift.

methods.name: animation_node_get_animation
methods.description: Returns the [AnimationPlayer]'s [Animation] bound to the [code]AnimationTreePlayer[/code]'s animation node with name [code]id[/code].

methods.name: animation_node_get_master_animation
methods.description: Returns the name of the [member master_player]'s [Animation] bound to this animation node.

methods.name: animation_node_set_animation
methods.description: Binds a new [Animation] from the [member master_player] to the [code]AnimationTreePlayer[/code]'s animation node with name [code]id[/code].

methods.name: animation_node_set_filter_path
methods.description: If [code]enable[/code] is [code]true[/code], the animation node with ID [code]id[/code] turns off the track modifying the property at [code]path[/code]. The modified node's children continue to animate.

methods.name: animation_node_set_master_animation
methods.description: Binds the [Animation] named [code]source[/code] from [member master_player] to the animation node [code]id[/code]. Recalculates caches.

methods.name: are_nodes_connected
methods.description: Returns whether node [code]id[/code] and [code]dst_id[/code] are connected at the specified slot.

methods.name: blend2_node_get_amount
methods.description: Returns the blend amount of a Blend2 node given its name.

methods.name: blend2_node_set_amount
methods.description:
Sets the blend amount of a Blend2 node given its name and value.
				A Blend2 Node blends two animations with the amount between 0 and 1.
				At 0, Output is input a.
				Towards 1, the influence of a gets lessened, the influence of b gets raised.
				At 1, Output is input b.

methods.name: blend2_node_set_filter_path
methods.description: If [code]enable[/code] is [code]true[/code], the blend2 node with ID [code]id[/code] turns off the track modifying the property at [code]path[/code]. The modified node's children continue to animate.

methods.name: blend3_node_get_amount
methods.description: Returns the blend amount of a Blend3 node given its name.

methods.name: blend3_node_set_amount
methods.description:
Sets the blend amount of a Blend3 node given its name and value.
				A Blend3 Node blends three animations with the amount between -1 and 1.
				At -1, Output is input b-.
				From -1 to 0, the influence of b- gets lessened, the influence of a gets raised and the influence of b+ is 0.
				At 0, Output is input a.
				From 0 to 1, the influence of a gets lessened, the influence of b+ gets raised and the influence of b+ is 0.
				At 1, Output is input b+.

methods.name: blend4_node_get_amount
methods.description: Returns the blend amount of a Blend4 node given its name.

methods.name: blend4_node_set_amount
methods.description:
Sets the blend amount of a Blend4 node given its name and value.
				A Blend4 Node blends two pairs of animations.
				The two pairs are blended like blend2 and then added together.

methods.name: connect_nodes
methods.description: Connects node [code]id[/code] to [code]dst_id[/code] at the specified input slot.

methods.name: disconnect_nodes
methods.description: Disconnects nodes connected to [code]id[/code] at the specified input slot.

methods.name: get_node_list
methods.description: Returns a [PoolStringArray] containing the name of all nodes.

methods.name: mix_node_get_amount
methods.description: Returns mix amount of a Mix node given its name.

methods.name: mix_node_set_amount
methods.description:
Sets mix amount of a Mix node given its name and value.
				A Mix node adds input b to input a by a the amount given by ratio.

methods.name: node_exists
methods.description: Check if a node exists (by name).

methods.name: node_get_input_count
methods.description: Return the input count for a given node. Different types of nodes have different amount of inputs.

methods.name: node_get_input_source
methods.description: Return the input source for a given node input.

methods.name: node_get_position
methods.description: Returns position of a node in the graph given its name.

methods.name: node_get_type
methods.description: Get the node type, will return from NODE_* enum.

methods.name: node_rename
methods.description: Rename a node in the graph.

methods.name: node_set_position
methods.description: Sets position of a node in the graph given its name and position.

methods.name: oneshot_node_get_autorestart_random_delay

methods.name: oneshot_node_set_autorestart_random_delay

methods.description: Sets fade in time of a OneShot node given its name and value in seconds.

methods.name: oneshot_node_set_fadeout_time
methods.description: Sets fade out time of a OneShot node given its name and value in seconds.

methods.name: oneshot_node_set_filter_path
methods.description: If [code]enable[/code] is [code]true[/code], the oneshot node with ID [code]id[/code] turns off the track modifying the property at [code]path[/code]. The modified node's children continue to animate.

methods.name: timescale_node_set_scale
methods.description:
Sets the time scale of the TimeScale node with name [code]id[/code] to [code]scale[/code].
				The timescale node is used to speed [Animation]s up if the scale is above 1 or slow them down if it is below 1.
				If applied after a blend or mix, affects all input animations to that blend or mix.

methods.name: timeseek_node_seek
methods.description:
Sets the time seek value of the TimeSeek node with name [code]id[/code] to [code]seconds[/code]
				This functions as a seek in the [Animation] or the blend or mix of [Animation]s input in it.

methods.name: transition_node_get_input_count
methods.description: Returns the number of inputs for the transition node with name [code]id[/code]. You can add inputs by rightclicking on the transition node.

methods.name: transition_node_get_xfade_time
methods.description: Returns the cross fade time for the transition node with name [code]id[/code].

methods.name: transition_node_has_input_auto_advance
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the input at [code]input_idx[/code] on transition node with name [code]id[/code] is set to automatically advance to the next input upon completion.

methods.name: transition_node_set_current
methods.description: The transition node with name [code]id[/code] sets its current input at [code]input_idx[/code].

methods.name: transition_node_set_input_auto_advance
methods.description: The transition node with name [code]id[/code] advances to its next input automatically when the input at [code]input_idx[/code] completes.

methods.name: transition_node_set_input_count
methods.description: Resizes the number of inputs available for the transition node with name [code]id[/code].

methods.description: The transition node with name [code]id[/code] sets its cross fade time to [code]time_sec[/code].

When you scale the node, it tiles the texture's sides horizontally or vertically, the center on both axes but it doesn't scale or tile the corners.

ConcavePolygonShape2D.name: ConcavePolygonShape2D
ConcavePolygonShape2D.brief_description: Concave polygon 2D shape resource for physics.
ConcavePolygonShape2D.description:
Concave polygon 2D shape resource for physics. It is made out of segments and is very optimal for complex polygonal concave collisions. It is really not advised to use for [RigidBody2D] nodes. A CollisionPolygon2D in convex decomposition mode (solids) or several convex objects are advised for that instead. Otherwise, a concave polygon 2D shape is better for static collisions.
		The main difference between a [ConvexPolygonShape2D] and a [code]ConcavePolygonShape2D[/code] is that a concave polygon assumes it is concave and uses a more complex method of collision detection, and a convex one forces itself to be convex in order to speed up collision detection.

properties.name: segments
