AStar.name: AStar
AStar.brief_description: AStar class representation that uses vectors as edges.
AStar.description:
A* (A star) is a computer algorithm that is widely used in pathfinding and graph traversal, the process of plotting an efficiently directed path between multiple points. It enjoys widespread use due to its performance and accuracy. Godot's A* implementation make use of vectors as points.
		You must add points manually with [method AStar.add_point] and create segments manually with [method AStar.connect_points]. So you can test if there is a path between two points with the [method AStar.are_points_connected] function, get the list of existing ids in the found path with [method AStar.get_id_path], or the points list with [method AStar.get_point_path].

methods.name: _compute_cost
methods.description: Called when computing the cost between two connected points.

methods.name: _estimate_cost
methods.description: Called when estimating the cost between a point and the path's ending point.

methods.name: add_point
methods.description:
Adds a new point at the given position with the given identifier. The algorithm prefers points with lower [code]weight_scale[/code] to form a path. The [code]id[/code] must be 0 or larger, and the [code]weight_scale[/code] must be 1 or larger.
				[codeblock]
				var as = AStar.new()

				as.add_point(1, Vector3(1,0,0), 4) # Adds the point (1,0,0) with weight_scale=4 and id=1
				[/codeblock]
				If there already exists a point for the given id, its position and weight scale are updated to the given values.

methods.name: are_points_connected
methods.description: Returns whether there is a connection/segment between the given points.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clears all the points and segments.

methods.name: connect_points
methods.description:
Creates a segment between the given points.
				[codeblock]
				var as = AStar.new()

				as.add_point(1, Vector3(1,1,0))
				as.add_point(2, Vector3(0,5,0))

				as.connect_points(1, 2, false) # If bidirectional=false it's only possible to go from point 1 to point 2
				                               # and not from point 2 to point 1.
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: disconnect_points
methods.description: Deletes the segment between the given points.

methods.name: get_available_point_id
methods.description: Returns the next available point id with no point associated to it.

methods.name: get_closest_point
methods.description: Returns the id of the closest point to [code]to_position[/code]. Returns -1 if there are no points in the points pool.

methods.name: get_closest_position_in_segment
methods.description:
Returns the closest position to [code]to_position[/code] that resides inside a segment between two connected points.
				[codeblock]
				var as = AStar.new()

				as.add_point(1, Vector3(0,0,0))
				as.add_point(2, Vector3(0,5,0))

				as.connect_points(1, 2)

				var res = as.get_closest_position_in_segment(Vector3(3,3,0)) # returns (0, 3, 0)
				[/codeblock]
				The result is in the segment that goes from [code]y=0[/code] to [code]y=5[/code]. It's the closest position in the segment to the given point.

methods.name: get_id_path
methods.description:
Returns an array with the ids of the points that form the path found by AStar between the given points. The array is ordered from the starting point to the ending point of the path.
				[codeblock]
				var as = AStar.new()

				as.add_point(1, Vector3(0,0,0))
				as.add_point(2, Vector3(0,1,0), 1) # default weight is 1
				as.add_point(3, Vector3(1,1,0))
				as.add_point(4, Vector3(2,0,0))

				as.connect_points(1, 2, false)
				as.connect_points(2, 3, false)
				as.connect_points(4, 3, false)
				as.connect_points(1, 4, false)
				as.connect_points(5, 4, false)

				var res = as.get_id_path(1, 3) # returns [1, 2, 3]
				[/codeblock]
				If you change the 2nd point's weight to 3, then the result will be [code][1, 4, 3][/code] instead, because now even though the distance is longer, it's "easier" to get through point 4 than through point 2.

methods.name: get_point_connections
methods.description:
Returns an array with the ids of the points that form the connect with the given point.
				[codeblock]
				var as = AStar.new()

				as.add_point(1, Vector3(0,0,0))
				as.add_point(2, Vector3(0,1,0))
				as.add_point(3, Vector3(1,1,0))
				as.add_point(4, Vector3(2,0,0))

				as.connect_points(1, 2, true)
				as.connect_points(1, 3, true)

				var neighbors = as.get_point_connections(1) # returns [2, 3]
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: get_point_path
methods.description: Returns an array with the points that are in the path found by AStar between the given points. The array is ordered from the starting point to the ending point of the path.

methods.name: get_point_position
methods.description: Returns the position of the point associated with the given id.

methods.name: get_point_weight_scale
methods.description: Returns the weight scale of the point associated with the given id.

methods.name: get_points
methods.description: Returns an array of all points.

methods.name: has_point
methods.description: Returns whether a point associated with the given id exists.

methods.name: remove_point
methods.description: Removes the point associated with the given id from the points pool.

methods.name: set_point_position
methods.description: Sets the position for the point with the given id.

methods.name: set_point_weight_scale
methods.description: Sets the [code]weight_scale[/code] for the point with the given id.

ColorPickerButton.name: ColorPickerButton
ColorPickerButton.description: Encapsulates a [ColorPicker] making it accesible by pressing a button, pressing the button will toggle the [ColorPicker] visibility

methods.name: get_picker
methods.description: Returns the [code]ColorPicker[/code] that this [code]ColorPickerButton[/code] toggles.

methods.name: get_popup
methods.description: Returns the control's [PopupPanel] which allows you to connect to Popup Signals. This allows you to handle events when the ColorPicker is shown or hidden.

signals.name: color_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the color changes.

properties.name: color
properties.description: The currently selected color.

properties.name: edit_alpha
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the alpha channel in the displayed [ColorPicker] will be visible. Default value: [code]true[/code].

GridContainer.name: GridContainer
GridContainer.brief_description: Grid container used to arrange elements in a grid like layout
GridContainer.description: Grid container will arrange its children in a grid like structure, the grid columns are specified using the [method set_columns] method and the number of rows will be equal to the number of children in the container divided by the number of columns, for example: if the container has 5 children, and 2 columns, there will be 3 rows in the container. Notice that grid layout will preserve the columns and rows for every size of the container.

properties.name: columns
properties.description: The number of columns in the [code]GridContainer[/code]. If modified, [code]GridContainer[/code] reorders its children to accommodate the new layout.

LineShape2D.name: LineShape2D
LineShape2D.description: Line shape for 2D collisions. It works like a 2D plane and will not allow any body to go to the negative side. Not recommended for rigid bodies, and usually not recommended for static bodies either because it forces checks against it on every frame.

properties.name: d
properties.description: The line's distance from the origin.

properties.name: normal
properties.description: The line's normal.

ParallaxLayer.name: ParallaxLayer
ParallaxLayer.brief_description: A parallax scrolling layer to be used with [ParallaxBackground].
ParallaxLayer.description:
A ParallaxLayer must be the child of a [ParallaxBackground] node. Each ParallaxLayer can be set to move at different speeds relative to the camera movement or the [member ParallaxBackground.scroll_offset] value.
		This node's children will be affected by its scroll offset.

properties.name: motion_mirroring
properties.description: The ParallaxLayer's [Texture] mirroring. Useful for creating an infinite scrolling background. If an axis is set to [code]0[/code] the [Texture] will not be mirrored. Default value: [code](0, 0)[/code].

properties.name: motion_offset
properties.description: The ParallaxLayer's offset relative to the parent ParallaxBackground's [member ParallaxBackground.scroll_offset].

properties.name: motion_scale
properties.description: Multiplies the ParallaxLayer's motion. If an axis is set to [code]0[/code] it will not scroll.

JSON.name: JSON
JSON.brief_description: Helper class for parsing JSON data.
JSON.description: Helper class for parsing JSON data. For usage example, see [JSONParseResult].

methods.name: parse
methods.description: Parses a JSON encoded string and returns a [JSONParseResult] containing the result.

methods.name: print
methods.description: Converts a Variant var to JSON text and returns the result. Useful for serializing data to store or send over the network.

CollisionPolygon.name: CollisionPolygon
CollisionPolygon.brief_description: Editor-only class for defining a collision polygon in 3D space.
CollisionPolygon.description: Allows editing a collision polygon's vertices on a selected plane. Can also set a depth perpendicular to that plane. This class is only available in the editor. It will not appear in the scene tree at runtime. Creates a [Shape] for gameplay. Properties modified during gameplay will have no effect.

properties.name: depth
properties.description: Length that the resulting collision extends in either direction perpendicular to its polygon.

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: If true, no collision will be produced.

properties.name: polygon
properties.description: Array of vertices which define the polygon.

EditorSettings.name: EditorSettings
EditorSettings.brief_description: Object that holds the project-independent editor settings.
EditorSettings.description:
Object that holds the project-independent editor settings. These settings are generally visible in the Editor Settings menu.
		Accessing the settings is done by using the regular [Object] API, such as:
		[codeblock]
		settings.set(prop,value)
		settings.get(prop)
		list_of_settings = settings.get_property_list()
		[/codeblock]

methods.name: add_property_info
methods.description:
Add a custom property info to a property. The dictionary must contain: name:[String](the name of the property) and type:[int](see TYPE_* in [@GlobalScope]), and optionally hint:[int](see PROPERTY_HINT_* in [@GlobalScope]), hint_string:[String].
				Example:
				[codeblock]
				editor_settings.set("category/property_name", 0)

				var property_info = {
				    "name": "category/property_name",
				    "type": TYPE_INT,
				    "hint": PROPERTY_HINT_ENUM,
				    "hint_string": "one,two,three"
				}

				editor_settings.add_property_info(property_info)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: erase
methods.description: Erase a given setting (pass full property path).

methods.name: get_favorite_dirs
methods.description: Get the list of favorite directories for this project.

methods.name: get_project_settings_dir
methods.description: Get the specific project settings path. Projects all have a unique sub-directory inside the settings path where project specific settings are saved.

methods.name: get_recent_dirs
methods.description: Get the list of recently visited folders in the file dialog for this project.

methods.name: get_settings_dir
methods.description:
Get the global settings path for the engine. Inside this path you can find some standard paths such as:
				settings/tmp - used for temporary storage of files
				settings/templates - where export templates are located

methods.name: set_favorite_dirs
methods.description: Set the list of favorite directories for this project.

methods.name: set_recent_dirs
methods.description: Set the list of recently visited folders in the file dialog for this project.

Resource.name: Resource
Resource.description: Resource is the base class for all resource types. Resources are primarily data containers. They are reference counted and freed when no longer in use. They are also loaded only once from disk, and further attempts to load the resource will return the same reference (all this in contrast to a [Node], which is not reference counted and can be instanced from disk as many times as desired). Resources can be saved externally on disk or bundled into another object, such as a [Node] or another resource.

methods.name: get_rid
methods.description: Return the RID of the resource (or an empty RID). Many resources (such as [Texture], [Mesh], etc) are high level abstractions of resources stored in a server, so this function will return the original RID.

methods.name: take_over_path
methods.description: Set the path of the resource. Differs from set_path(), if another [code]Resource[/code] exists with "path" it over-takes it, instead of failing.

AnimatedSprite.name: AnimatedSprite
AnimatedSprite.brief_description: Sprite node that can use multiple textures for animation.
AnimatedSprite.description: Animations are created using a [SpriteFrames] resource, which can be configured in the editor via the SpriteFrames panel.

methods.name: is_playing
methods.description: Return true if an animation if currently being played.

methods.name: play
methods.description: Play the animation set in parameter. If no parameter is provided, the current animation is played.

methods.name: stop
methods.description: Stop the current animation (does not reset the frame counter).

signals.name: animation_finished
signals.description: Emitted when the animation is finished (when it plays the last frame). If the animation is looping, this signal is emitted every time the last frame is drawn.

signals.name: frame_changed
signals.description: Emitted when [member frame] changed.

properties.name: animation
properties.description: The current animation from the [code]frames[/code] resource. If this value changes, the [code]frame[/code] counter is reset.

properties.name: centered
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] texture will be centered. Default value: [code]true[/code].

properties.name: flip_h
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] texture is flipped horizontally. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: flip_v
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] texture is flipped vertically. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: frame
properties.description: The displayed animation frame's index.

properties.name: frames
properties.description: The [SpriteFrames] resource containing the animation(s).

properties.name: offset
properties.description: The texture's drawing offset.

properties.name: playing
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the [member animation] is currently playing.

AudioStream.name: AudioStream
AudioStream.description: Base class for audio streams. Audio streams are used for music playback, or other types of streamed sounds that don't fit or require more flexibility than a [Sample].

Viewport.name: Viewport
Viewport.brief_description: Creates a sub-view into the screen.
Viewport.description:
A Viewport creates a different view into the screen, or a sub-view inside another viewport. Children 2D Nodes will display on it, and children Camera 3D nodes will render on it too.
		Optionally, a viewport can have its own 2D or 3D world, so they don't share what they draw with other viewports.
		If a viewport is a child of a [Control], it will automatically take up its same rect and position, otherwise they must be set manually.
		Viewports can also choose to be audio listeners, so they generate positional audio depending on a 2D or 3D camera child of it.
		Also, viewports can be assigned to different screens in case the devices have multiple screens.
		Finally, viewports can also behave as render targets, in which case they will not be visible unless the associated texture is used to draw.

methods.name: find_world
methods.description: Return the 3D world of the viewport, or if no such present, the one of the parent viewport.

methods.name: find_world_2d
methods.description: Return the 2D world of the viewport.

methods.name: get_camera
methods.description: Return the active 3D camera.

methods.name: get_final_transform
methods.description: Get the total transform of the viewport.

methods.name: get_mouse_position
methods.description: Get the mouse position, relative to the viewport.

methods.name: get_size_override
methods.description: Get the size override set with [method set_size_override].

methods.name: get_texture
methods.description: Get the viewport's texture, for use with various objects that you want to texture with the viewport.

methods.name: get_viewport_rid
methods.description: Get the viewport RID from the [VisualServer].

methods.name: get_visible_rect
methods.description: Return the final, visible rect in global screen coordinates.

methods.name: gui_get_drag_data
methods.description: Returns the drag data from the GUI, that was previously returned by [method Control.get_drag_data].

methods.name: gui_has_modal_stack
methods.description: Returns whether there are shown modals on-screen.

methods.name: is_size_override_enabled
methods.description: Get the enabled status of the size override set with [method set_size_override].

methods.name: is_size_override_stretch_enabled
methods.description: Get the enabled status of the size strech override set with [method set_size_override_stretch].

methods.name: set_size_override
methods.description: Set the size override of the viewport. If the enable parameter is true, it would use the override, otherwise it would use the default size. If the size parameter is equal to [code](-1, -1)[/code], it won't update the size.

methods.name: set_size_override_stretch
methods.description: Set whether the size override affects stretch as well.

methods.name: update_worlds
methods.description: Force update of the 2D and 3D worlds.

methods.name: warp_mouse
methods.description: Warp the mouse to a position, relative to the viewport.

signals.name: size_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the size of the viewport is changed, whether by [method set_size_override], resize of window, or some other means.

constants.name: UPDATE_DISABLED
constants.description: Do not update the render target.

constants.name: UPDATE_ONCE
constants.description: Update the render target once, then switch to [code]UPDATE_DISABLED[/code]

constants.name: UPDATE_WHEN_VISIBLE
constants.description: Update the render target only when it is visible. This is the default value.

properties.name: canvas_transform
properties.description: The canvas transform of the viewport, useful for changing the on-screen positions of all child [CanvasItem]s. This is relative to the global canvas transform of the viewport.

properties.name: global_canvas_transform
properties.description: The global canvas transform of the viewport. The canvas transform is relative to this.

SliderJoint.name: SliderJoint
SliderJoint.brief_description: Piston kind of slider between two bodies in 3D.
SliderJoint.description: Slides across the x-axis of the [Pivot] object.

constants.name: PARAM_LINEAR_LIMIT_UPPER
constants.description: The maximum difference between the pivot points on their x-axis before damping happens.

constants.name: PARAM_LINEAR_LIMIT_LOWER
constants.description: The minimum difference between the pivot points on their x-axis before damping happens.

constants.name: PARAM_LINEAR_LIMIT_SOFTNESS
constants.description: A factor applied to the movement across the slider axis once the limits get surpassed. The lower, the slower the movement.

constants.name: PARAM_LINEAR_LIMIT_RESTITUTION
constants.description: The amount of restitution once the limits are surpassed. The lower, the more velocityenergy gets lost.

constants.name: PARAM_LINEAR_LIMIT_DAMPING
constants.description: The amount of damping once the slider limits are surpassed.

constants.name: PARAM_LINEAR_MOTION_SOFTNESS
constants.description: A factor applied to the movement across the slider axis as long as the slider is in the limits. The lower, the slower the movement.

constants.name: PARAM_LINEAR_MOTION_RESTITUTION
constants.description: The amount of restitution inside the slider limits.

constants.name: PARAM_LINEAR_MOTION_DAMPING
constants.description: The amount of damping inside the slider limits.

constants.name: PARAM_LINEAR_ORTHOGONAL_SOFTNESS
constants.description: A factor applied to the movement across axes orthogonal to the slider.

constants.name: PARAM_LINEAR_ORTHOGONAL_RESTITUTION
constants.description: The amount of restitution when movement is across axes orthogonal to the slider.

constants.name: PARAM_LINEAR_ORTHOGONAL_DAMPING
constants.description: The amount of damping when movement is across axes orthogonal to the slider.

constants.name: PARAM_ANGULAR_LIMIT_UPPER
constants.description: The upper limit of rotation in the slider.

constants.name: PARAM_ANGULAR_LIMIT_LOWER
constants.description: The lower limit of rotation in the slider.

constants.name: PARAM_ANGULAR_LIMIT_SOFTNESS
constants.description: A factor applied to the all rotation once the limit is surpassed.

constants.name: PARAM_ANGULAR_LIMIT_RESTITUTION
constants.description: The amount of restitution of the rotation when the limit is surpassed.

constants.name: PARAM_ANGULAR_LIMIT_DAMPING
constants.description: The amount of damping of the rotation when the limit is surpassed.

constants.name: PARAM_ANGULAR_MOTION_SOFTNESS
constants.description: A factor applied to the all rotation in the limits.

constants.name: PARAM_ANGULAR_MOTION_RESTITUTION
constants.description: The amount of restitution of the rotation in the limits.

constants.name: PARAM_ANGULAR_MOTION_DAMPING
constants.description: The amount of damping of the rotation in the limits.

constants.name: PARAM_ANGULAR_ORTHOGONAL_SOFTNESS
constants.description: A factor applied to the all rotation across axes orthogonal to the slider.

constants.name: PARAM_ANGULAR_ORTHOGONAL_RESTITUTION
constants.description: The amount of restitution of the rotation across axes orthogonal to the slider.

constants.name: PARAM_ANGULAR_ORTHOGONAL_DAMPING
constants.description: The amount of damping of the rotation across axes orthogonal to the slider.

constants.name: PARAM_MAX
constants.description: End flag of PARAM_* constants, used internally.

properties.name: angular_limit/damping
properties.description:
The amount of damping of the rotation when the limit is surpassed.
			A lower damping value allows a rotation initiated by body A to travel to body B slower.

properties.name: angular_limit/lower_angle
properties.description: The lower limit of rotation in the slider.

properties.name: angular_limit/restitution
properties.description:
The amount of restitution of the rotation when the limit is surpassed.
			Does not affect damping.

properties.name: angular_limit/softness
properties.description:
A factor applied to the all rotation once the limit is surpassed.
			Makes all rotation slower when between 0 and 1.

properties.name: angular_limit/upper_angle
properties.description: The upper limit of rotation in the slider.

properties.name: angular_motion/damping
properties.description: The amount of damping of the rotation in the limits.

properties.name: angular_motion/restitution
properties.description: The amount of restitution of the rotation in the limits.

properties.name: angular_motion/softness
properties.description: A factor applied to the all rotation in the limits.

properties.name: angular_ortho/damping
properties.description: The amount of damping of the rotation across axes orthogonal to the slider.

properties.name: angular_ortho/restitution
properties.description: The amount of restitution of the rotation across axes orthogonal to the slider.

properties.name: angular_ortho/softness
properties.description: A factor applied to the all rotation across axes orthogonal to the slider.

properties.name: linear_limit/damping
properties.description: The amount of damping that happens once the limit defined by [member linear_limit/lower_distance] and [member linear_limit/upper_distance] is surpassed.

properties.name: linear_limit/lower_distance
properties.description: The minimum difference between the pivot points on their x-axis before damping happens.

properties.name: linear_limit/restitution
properties.description: The amount of restitution once the limits are surpassed. The lower, the more velocity-energy gets lost.

properties.name: linear_limit/softness
properties.description: A factor applied to the movement across the slider axis once the limits get surpassed. The lower, the slower the movement.

properties.name: linear_limit/upper_distance
properties.description: The maximum difference between the pivot points on their x-axis before damping happens.

properties.name: linear_motion/damping
properties.description: The amount of damping inside the slider limits.

properties.name: linear_motion/restitution
properties.description: The amount of restitution inside the slider limits.

properties.name: linear_motion/softness
properties.description: A factor applied to the movement across the slider axis as long as the slider is in the limits. The lower, the slower the movement.

properties.name: linear_ortho/damping
properties.description: The amount of damping when movement is across axes orthogonal to the slider.

properties.name: linear_ortho/restitution
properties.description: The amount of restitution when movement is across axes orthogonal to the slider.

properties.name: linear_ortho/softness
properties.description: A factor applied to the movement across axes orthogonal to the slider.

methods.name: build_box_planes
methods.description: Returns an array with 6 [Plane]s that describe the sides of a box centered at the origin. The box size is defined by [code]extents[/code], which represents one (positive) corner of the box (i.e. half its actual size).

methods.name: build_capsule_planes
methods.description: Returns an array of [Plane]s closely bounding a faceted capsule centered at the origin with radius [code]radius[/code] and height [code]height[/code]. The parameter [code]sides[/code] defines how many planes will be generated for the side part of the capsule, whereas [code]lats[/code] gives the number of latitudinal steps at the bottom and top of the capsule. The parameter [code]axis[/code] describes the axis along which the capsule is oriented (0 for X, 1 for Y, 2 for Z).

methods.name: build_cylinder_planes
methods.description: Returns an array of [Plane]s closely bounding a faceted cylinder centered at the origin with radius [code]radius[/code] and height [code]height[/code]. The parameter [code]sides[/code] defines how many planes will be generated for the round part of the cylinder. The parameter [code]axis[/code] describes the axis along which the cylinder is oriented (0 for X, 1 for Y, 2 for Z).

methods.name: clip_polygon
methods.description: Clips the polygon defined by the points in [code]points[/code] against the [code]plane[/code] and returns the points of the clipped polygon.

methods.name: convex_hull_2d
methods.description: Given an array of [Vector2]s, returns the convex hull as a list of points in counter-clockwise order. The last point is the same as the first one.

methods.name: get_closest_point_to_segment
methods.description: Returns the 3d point on the 3d segment ([code]s1[/code], [code]s2[/code]) that is closest to [code]point[/code]. The returned point will always be inside the specified segment.

methods.name: get_closest_point_to_segment_2d
methods.description: Returns the 2d point on the 2d segment ([code]s1[/code], [code]s2[/code]) that is closest to [code]point[/code]. The returned point will always be inside the specified segment.

methods.name: get_closest_point_to_segment_uncapped
methods.description: Returns the 3d point on the 3d line defined by ([code]s1[/code], [code]s2[/code]) that is closest to [code]point[/code]. The returned point can be inside the segment ([code]s1[/code], [code]s2[/code]) or outside of it, i.e. somewhere on the line extending from the segment.

methods.name: get_closest_point_to_segment_uncapped_2d
methods.description: Returns the 2d point on the 2d line defined by ([code]s1[/code], [code]s2[/code]) that is closest to [code]point[/code]. The returned point can be inside the segment ([code]s1[/code], [code]s2[/code]) or outside of it, i.e. somewhere on the line extending from the segment.

methods.name: get_closest_points_between_segments
methods.description: Given the two 3d segments ([code]p1[/code], [code]p2[/code]) and ([code]q1[/code], [code]q2[/code]), finds those two points on the two segments that are closest to each other. Returns a [PoolVector3Array] that contains this point on ([code]p1[/code], [code]p2[/code]) as well the accompanying point on ([code]q1[/code], [code]q2[/code]).

methods.name: get_closest_points_between_segments_2d
methods.description: Given the two 2d segments ([code]p1[/code], [code]p2[/code]) and ([code]q1[/code], [code]q2[/code]), finds those two points on the two segments that are closest to each other. Returns a [PoolVector2Array] that contains this point on ([code]p1[/code], [code]p2[/code]) as well the accompanying point on ([code]q1[/code], [code]q2[/code]).

methods.name: make_atlas
methods.description: Given an array of [Vector2]s representing tiles, builds an atlas. The returned dictionary has two keys: [code]points[/code] is a vector of [Vector2] that specifies the positions of each tile, [code]size[/code] contains the overall size of the whole atlas as [Vector2].

methods.name: point_is_inside_triangle
methods.description: Returns if [code]point[/code] is inside the triangle specified by [code]a[/code], [code]b[/code] and [code]c[/code].

methods.name: ray_intersects_triangle
methods.description: Tests if the 3d ray starting at [code]from[/code] with the direction of [code]dir[/code] intersects the triangle specified by [code]a[/code], [code]b[/code] and [code]c[/code]. If yes, returns the point of intersection as [Vector3]. If no intersection takes place, an empty [Variant] is returned.

methods.name: segment_intersects_circle
methods.description: Given the 2d segment ([code]segment_from[/code], [code]segment_to[/code]), returns the position on the segment (as a number between 0 and 1) at which the segment hits the circle that is located at position [code]circle_position[/code] and has radius [code]circle_radius[/code]. If the segment does not intersect the circle, -1 is returned (this is also the case if the line extending the segment would intersect the circle, but the segment does not).

methods.name: segment_intersects_convex
methods.description: Given a convex hull defined though the [Plane]s in the array [code]planes[/code], tests if the segment ([code]from[/code], [code]to[/code]) intersects with that hull. If an intersection is found, returns a [PoolVector3Array] containing the point the intersection and the hull's normal. If no intersecion is found, an the returned array is empty.

methods.name: segment_intersects_cylinder
methods.description: Checks if the segment ([code]from[/code], [code]to[/code]) intersects the cylinder with height [code]height[/code] that is centered at the origin and has radius [code]radius[/code]. If no, returns an empty [PoolVector3Array]. If an intersection takes place, the returned array contains the point of intersection and the cylinder's normal at the point of intersection.

methods.name: segment_intersects_segment_2d
methods.description: Checks if the two segments ([code]from_a[/code], [code]to_a[/code]) and ([code]from_b[/code], [code]to_b[/code]) intersect. If yes, return the point of intersection as [Vector2]. If no intersection takes place, returns an empty [Variant].

methods.name: segment_intersects_sphere
methods.description: Checks if the segment ([code]from[/code], [code]to[/code]) intersects the sphere that is located at [code]sphere_position[/code] and has radius [code]sphere_radius[/code]. If no, returns an empty [PoolVector3Array]. If yes, returns a [PoolVector3Array] containing the point of intersection and the sphere's normal at the point of intersection.

methods.name: segment_intersects_triangle
methods.description: Tests if the segment ([code]from[/code], [code]to[/code]) intersects the triangle [code]a[/code], [code]b[/code], [code]c[/code]. If yes, returns the point of intersection as [Vector3]. If no intersection takes place, an empty [Variant] is returned.

methods.name: triangulate_polygon
methods.description: Triangulates the polygon specified by the points in [code]polygon[/code]. Returns a [PoolIntArray] where each triangle consists of three consecutive point indices into [code]polygon[/code] (i.e. the returned array will have [code]n * 3[/code] elements, with [code]n[/code] being the number of found triangles). If the triangulation did not succeed, an empty [PoolIntArray] is returned.

VisualScriptNode.name: VisualScriptNode
VisualScriptNode.brief_description: A node which is part of a [VisualScript].
VisualScriptNode.description: A node which is part of a [VisualScript]. Not to be confused with [Node], which is a part of a [SceneTree].

methods.name: get_default_input_value
methods.description: Returns the default value of a given port. The default value is used when nothing is connected to the port.

methods.name: get_visual_script
methods.description: Returns the [VisualScript] instance the node is bound to.

methods.name: ports_changed_notify
methods.description: Notify that the node's ports have changed. Usually used in conjunction with [VisualScriptCustomNode] .

methods.name: set_default_input_value
methods.description: Change the default value of a given port.

signals.name: ports_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the available input/output ports are changed.

RegEx.name: RegEx
RegEx.brief_description: Class for searching text for patterns using regular expressions.
RegEx.description:
Regular Expression (or regex) is a compact programming language that can be used to recognise strings that follow a specific pattern, such as URLs, email addresses, complete sentences, etc. For instance, a regex of [code]ab[0-9][/code] would find any string that is [code]ab[/code] followed by any number from [code]0[/code] to [code]9[/code]. For a more in-depth look, you can easily find various tutorials and detailed explainations on the Internet.
		To begin, the RegEx object needs to be compiled with the search pattern using [method compile] before it can be used.
		[codeblock]
		var regex = RegEx.new()
		regex.compile("\\w-(\\d+)")
		[/codeblock]
		The search pattern must be escaped first for gdscript before it is escaped for the expression. For example, [code]compile("\\d+")[/code] would be read by RegEx as [code]\d+[/code]. Similarly, [code]compile("\"(?:\\\\.|[^\"])*\"")[/code] would be read as [code]"(?:\\.|[^"])*"[/code]
		Using [method search] you can find the pattern within the given text. If a pattern is found, [RegExMatch] is returned and you can retrieve details of the results using fuctions such as [method RegExMatch.get_string] and [method RegExMatch.get_start].
		[codeblock]
		var regex = RegEx.new()
		regex.compile("\\w-(\\d+)")
		var result = regex.search("abc n-0123")
		if result:
		    print(result.get_string()) # Would print n-0123
		[/codeblock]
		The results of capturing groups [code]()[/code] can be retrieved by passing the group number to the various functions in [RegExMatch]. Group 0 is the default and would always refer to the entire pattern. In the above example, calling [code]result.get_string(1)[/code] would give you [code]0123[/code].
		This version of RegEx also supports named capturing groups, and the names can be used to retrieve the results. If two or more groups have the same name, the name would only refer to the first one with a match.
		[codeblock]
		var regex = RegEx.new()
		regex.compile("d(?<digit>[0-9]+)|x(?<digit>[0-9a-f]+)")
		var result = regex.search("the number is x2f")
		if result:
		    print(result.get_string("digit")) # Would print 2f
		[/codeblock]
		If you need to process multiple results, [method search_all] generates a list of all non-overlapping results. This can be combined with a for-loop for convenience.
		[codeblock]
		for result in regex.search_all("d01, d03, d0c, x3f and x42"):
		    print(result.get_string("digit"))
		# Would print 01 03 3f 42
		# Note that d0c would not match
		[/codeblock]

methods.name: clear
methods.description: This method resets the state of the object, as it was freshly created. Namely, it unassigns the regular expression of this object.

methods.name: compile
methods.description: Compiles and assign the search pattern to use. Returns OK if the compilation is successful. If an error is encountered the details are printed to STDOUT and FAILED is returned.

methods.name: get_group_count
methods.description: Returns the number of capturing groups in compiled pattern.

methods.name: get_names
methods.description: Returns an array of names of named capturing groups in the compiled pattern. They are ordered by appearance.

methods.name: get_pattern
methods.description: Returns the original search pattern that was compiled.

methods.name: is_valid
methods.description: Returns whether this object has a valid search pattern assigned.

methods.name: search
methods.description: Searches the text for the compiled pattern. Returns a [RegExMatch] container of the first matching result if found, otherwise null. The region to search within can be specified without modifying where the start and end anchor would be.

methods.name: search_all
methods.description: Searches the text for the compiled pattern. Returns an array of [RegExMatch] containers for each non-overlapping result. If no results were found an empty array is returned instead. The region to search within can be specified without modifying where the start and end anchor would be.

methods.name: sub
methods.description: Searches the text for the compiled pattern and replaces it with the specified string. Escapes and backreferences such as [code]\1[/code] and [code]\g<name>[/code] expanded and resolved. By default only the first instance is replaced but it can be changed for all instances (global replacement). The region to search within can be specified without modifying where the start and end anchor would be.

Transform2D.name: Transform2D
Transform2D.description: Represents one or many transformations in 2D space such as translation, rotation, or scaling. It consists of a two [Vector2] x, y and [Vector2] "origin". It is similar to a 3x2 matrix.

methods.name: Transform2D
methods.description: Constructs the transform from a 3D [Transform].

methods.name: Transform2D
methods.description: Constructs the transform from 3 [Vector2]s representing x, y, and origin.

methods.name: Transform2D
methods.description: Constructs the transform from a given angle (in radians) and position.

methods.name: affine_inverse
methods.description: Returns the inverse of the matrix.

methods.name: basis_xform
methods.description: Transforms the given vector by this transform's basis (no translation).

methods.name: basis_xform_inv
methods.description: Inverse-transforms the given vector by this transform's basis (no translation).

methods.name: get_origin
methods.description: Returns the transform's origin (translation).

methods.name: get_rotation
methods.description: Returns the transform's rotation (in radians).

methods.name: get_scale
methods.description: Returns the scale.

methods.name: interpolate_with
methods.description: Returns a transform interpolated between this transform and another by a given weight (0-1).

methods.name: inverse
methods.description: Returns the inverse of the transform, under the assumption that the transformation is composed of rotation and translation (no scaling, use affine_inverse for transforms with scaling).

methods.name: orthonormalized
methods.description: Returns the transform with the basis orthogonal (90 degrees), and normalized axis vectors.

methods.name: rotated
methods.description: Rotates the transform by the given angle (in radians).

methods.name: scaled
methods.description: Scales the transform by the given factor.

methods.name: translated
methods.description: Translates the transform by the given offset.

methods.name: xform
methods.description: Transforms the given [Vector2] or [Rect2] by this transform.

methods.name: xform_inv
methods.description: Inverse-transforms the given [Vector2] or [Rect2] by this transform.

properties.name: origin
properties.description: The transform's translation offset.

properties.name: x
properties.description: The X axis of 2x2 basis matrix containing 2 [Vector2]s as its columns: X axis and Y axis. These vectors can be interpreted as the basis vectors of local coordinate system traveling with the object.

properties.name: y
properties.description: The Y axis of 2x2 basis matrix containing 2 [Vector2]s as its columns: X axis and Y axis. These vectors can be interpreted as the basis vectors of local coordinate system traveling with the object.

XMLParser.name: XMLParser
XMLParser.brief_description: Low-level class for creating parsers for XML files.
XMLParser.description: This class can serve as base to make custom XML parsers. Since XML is a very flexible standard, this interface is low level so it can be applied to any possible schema.

methods.name: get_attribute_count
methods.description: Get the amount of attributes in the current element.

methods.name: get_attribute_name
methods.description: Get the name of the attribute specified by the index in [code]idx[/code] argument.

methods.name: get_attribute_value
methods.description: Get the value of the attribute specified by the index in [code]idx[/code] argument.

methods.name: get_current_line
methods.description: Get the current line in the parsed file (currently not implemented).

methods.name: get_named_attribute_value
methods.description: Get the value of a certain attribute of the current element by name. This will raise an error if the element has no such attribute.

methods.name: get_named_attribute_value_safe
methods.description: Get the value of a certain attribute of the current element by name. This will return an empty [String] if the attribute is not found.

methods.name: get_node_data
methods.description: Get the contents of a text node. This will raise an error in any other type of node.

methods.name: get_node_name
methods.description: Get the name of the current element node. This will raise an error if the current node type is not [code]NODE_ELEMENT[/code] nor [code]NODE_ELEMENT_END[/code]

methods.name: get_node_offset
methods.description: Get the byte offset of the current node since the beginning of the file or buffer.

methods.name: get_node_type
methods.description: Get the type of the current node. Compare with [code]NODE_*[/code] constants.

methods.name: has_attribute
methods.description: Check whether or not the current element has a certain attribute.

methods.name: is_empty
methods.description: Check whether the current element is empty (this only works for completely empty tags, e.g. <element \>).

methods.name: open
methods.description: Open a XML file for parsing. This returns an error code.

methods.name: open_buffer
methods.description: Open a XML raw buffer for parsing. This returns an error code.

methods.name: read
methods.description: Read the next node of the file. This returns an error code.

methods.name: seek
methods.description: Move the buffer cursor to a certain offset (since the beginning) and read the next node there. This returns an error code.

methods.name: skip_section
methods.description: Skips the current section. If the node contains other elements, they will be ignored and the cursor will go to the closing of the current element.

constants.name: NODE_NONE
constants.description: There's no node (no file or buffer opened)

constants.name: NODE_ELEMENT
constants.description: Element (tag)

constants.name: NODE_ELEMENT_END
constants.description: End of element

constants.name: NODE_TEXT
constants.description: Text node

constants.name: NODE_COMMENT
constants.description: Comment node

constants.name: NODE_CDATA
constants.description: CDATA content

constants.name: NODE_UNKNOWN
constants.description: Unknown node

VisibilityEnabler.name: VisibilityEnabler
VisibilityEnabler.brief_description: Enable certain nodes only when visible.
VisibilityEnabler.description: The VisibilityEnabler will disable [RigidBody] and [AnimationPlayer] nodes when they are not visible. It will only affect other nodes within the same scene as the VisibilityEnabler itself.

constants.name: ENABLER_PAUSE_ANIMATIONS
constants.description: This enabler will pause [AnimationPlayer] nodes.

constants.name: ENABLER_FREEZE_BODIES
constants.description: This enabler will freeze [RigidBody] nodes.

CubeMap.name: CubeMap
CubeMap.brief_description: A CubeMap is a 6 sided 3D texture.
CubeMap.description: A 6-sided 3D texture typically used for faking reflections. It can be used to make an object look as if it's reflecting its surroundings. This usually delivers much better performance than other reflection methods.

methods.name: get_height
methods.description: Returns the [code]CubeMap[/code]'s height.

methods.name: get_side
methods.description: Returns an [Image] for a side of the [code]CubeMap[/code] using one of the [code]SIDE_*[/code] constants or an integer 0-5.

methods.name: get_width
methods.description: Returns the [code]CubeMap[/code]'s width.

methods.name: set_side
methods.description: Sets an [Image] for a side of the [code]CubeMap[/code] using one of the [code]SIDE_*[/code] constants or an integer 0-5.

constants.name: STORAGE_RAW
constants.description: Store the [code]CubeMap[/code] without any compression.

constants.name: STORAGE_COMPRESS_LOSSY
constants.description: Store the [code]CubeMap[/code] with strong compression that reduces image quality.

constants.name: STORAGE_COMPRESS_LOSSLESS
constants.description: Store the [code]CubeMap[/code] with moderate compression that doesn't reduce image quality.

constants.name: SIDE_LEFT
constants.description: Identifier for the left face of the [code]CubeMap[/code].

constants.name: SIDE_RIGHT
constants.description: Identifier for the right face of the [code]CubeMap[/code].

constants.name: SIDE_BOTTOM
constants.description: Identifier for the bottom face of the [code]CubeMap[/code].

constants.name: SIDE_TOP
constants.description: Identifier for the top face of the [code]CubeMap[/code].

constants.name: SIDE_FRONT
constants.description: Identifier for the front face of the [code]CubeMap[/code].

constants.name: SIDE_BACK
constants.description: Identifier for the back face of the [code]CubeMap[/code].

constants.name: FLAG_MIPMAPS
constants.description: Generate mipmaps, to enable smooth zooming out of the texture.

constants.name: FLAG_REPEAT
constants.description: Repeat (instead of clamp to edge).

constants.name: FLAG_FILTER
constants.description: Turn on magnifying filter, to enable smooth zooming in of the texture.

constants.name: FLAGS_DEFAULT
constants.description: Default flags. Generate mipmaps, repeat, and filter are enabled.

properties.name: flags
properties.description: The render flags for the [code]CubeMap[/code]. See the [code]FLAG_*[/code] constants for details.

properties.name: lossy_storage_quality
properties.description: The lossy storage quality of the [code]CubeMap[/code] if the storage mode is set to STORAGE_COMPRESS_LOSSY.

properties.name: storage_mode
properties.description: The [code]CubeMap[/code]'s storage mode. See [code]STORAGE_*[/code] constants.

properties.name: height
properties.description: The capsule's height.

properties.name: radius
properties.description: The capsules's radius.

KinematicCollision2D.name: KinematicCollision2D
KinematicCollision2D.description:
Contains collision data for KinematicBody2D collisions. When a [KinematicBody2D] is moved using [method KinematicBody2D.move_and_collide], it stops if it detects a collision with another body. If a collision is detected, a KinematicCollision2D object is returned.
		This object contains information about the collision, including the colliding object, the remaining motion, and the collision position. This information can be used to calculate a collision response.

properties.name: collider
properties.description: The colliding body.

properties.name: collider_id
properties.description: The colliding body's unique [RID].

properties.name: collider_metadata
properties.description: The colliding body's metadata. See [Object].

properties.name: collider_shape
properties.description: The colliding body's shape.

properties.name: collider_shape_index
properties.description: The colliding shape's index. See [CollisionObject2D].

properties.name: collider_velocity
properties.description: The colliding object's velocity.

properties.name: local_shape
properties.description: The moving object's colliding shape.

properties.name: normal
properties.description: The colliding body's shape's normal at the point of collision.

properties.name: position
properties.description: The point of collision.

properties.name: remainder
properties.description: The moving object's remaining movement vector.

properties.name: travel
properties.description: The distance the moving object traveled before collision.

Shape2D.name: Shape2D
Shape2D.description: Base class for all 2D Shapes. All 2D shape types inherit from this.

methods.name: collide
methods.description:
Return whether this shape is colliding with another.
				This method needs the transformation matrix for this shape ([code]local_xform[/code]), the shape to check collisions with ([code]with_shape[/code]), and the transformation matrix of that shape ([code]shape_xform[/code]).

methods.name: collide_and_get_contacts
methods.description:
Return a list of the points where this shape touches another. If there are no collisions, the list is empty.
				This method needs the transformation matrix for this shape ([code]local_xform[/code]), the shape to check collisions with ([code]with_shape[/code]), and the transformation matrix of that shape ([code]shape_xform[/code]).

methods.name: collide_with_motion
methods.description:
Return whether this shape would collide with another, if a given movement was applied.
				This method needs the transformation matrix for this shape ([code]local_xform[/code]), the movement to test on this shape ([code]local_motion[/code]), the shape to check collisions with ([code]with_shape[/code]), the transformation matrix of that shape ([code]shape_xform[/code]), and the movement to test onto the other object ([code]shape_motion[/code]).

methods.name: collide_with_motion_and_get_contacts
methods.description:
Return a list of the points where this shape would touch another, if a given movement was applied. If there are no collisions, the list is empty.
				This method needs the transformation matrix for this shape ([code]local_xform[/code]), the movement to test on this shape ([code]local_motion[/code]), the shape to check collisions with ([code]with_shape[/code]), the transformation matrix of that shape ([code]shape_xform[/code]), and the movement to test onto the other object ([code]shape_motion[/code]).

AudioStreamPlayback.name: AudioStreamPlayback
AudioStreamPlayback.brief_description: Meta class for playing back audio.
AudioStreamPlayback.description: Can play, loop, pause a scroll through Audio. See [AudioStream] and [AudioStreamOGGVorbis] for usage.

SphereShape.name: SphereShape
SphereShape.description: Sphere shape for 3D collisions, which can be set into a [PhysicsBody] or [Area]. This shape is useful for modeling sphere-like 3D objects.

properties.name: radius
properties.description: The sphere's radius. The shape's diameter is double the radius.

LargeTexture.name: LargeTexture
LargeTexture.brief_description: A Texture capable of storing many smaller Textures with offsets.
LargeTexture.description:
A Texture capable of storing many smaller Textures with offsets.
		You can dynamically add pieces([Texture]) to this [code]LargeTexture[/code] using different offsets.

methods.name: add_piece
methods.description: Add another [Texture] to this [code]LargeTexture[/code], starting on offset "ofs".

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clears the [code]LargeTexture[/code].

methods.name: get_piece_count
methods.description: Returns the number of pieces currently in this [code]LargeTexture[/code].

methods.name: get_piece_offset
methods.description: Returns the offset of the piece with index "idx".

methods.name: get_piece_texture
methods.description: Returns the [Texture] of the piece with index "idx".

methods.name: set_piece_offset
methods.description: Sets the offset of the piece with index "idx" to "ofs".

methods.name: set_piece_texture
methods.description: Sets the [Texture] of the piece with index "idx" to  "ofs".

methods.name: set_size
methods.description: Sets the size of this [code]LargeTexture[/code].

AudioStreamRandomPitch.name: AudioStreamRandomPitch
AudioStreamRandomPitch.brief_description: Plays audio with random pitch tweaking.
AudioStreamRandomPitch.description: Randomly varies pitch on each start.

properties.name: audio_stream
properties.description: The current [AudioStream].

properties.name: random_pitch
properties.description: The intensity of random pitch variation.

VScrollBar.name: VScrollBar
VScrollBar.brief_description: Vertical version of [ScrollBar], which goes from left (min) to right (max).

RigidBody.name: RigidBody
RigidBody.brief_description: Physics Body whose position is determined through physics simulation in 3D space.
RigidBody.description:
This is the node that implements full 3D physics. This means that you do not control a RigidBody directly. Instead you can apply forces to it (gravity, impulses, etc.), and the physics simulation will calculate the resulting movement, collision, bouncing, rotating, etc.
		This node can use custom force integration, for writing complex physics motion behavior per node.
		This node can shift state between regular Rigid body, Kinematic, Character or Static.
		Character mode forbids this node from being rotated.
		As a warning, don't change RigidBody's position every frame or very often. Sporadic changes work fine, but physics runs at a different granularity (fixed hz) than usual rendering (process callback) and maybe even in a separate thread, so changing this from a process loop will yield strange behavior.

methods.name: _integrate_forces
methods.description: Called during physics processing, allowing you to read and safely modify the simulation state for the object. By default it works in addition to the usual physics behavior, but [method set_use_custom_integrator] allows you to disable the default behavior and do fully custom force integration for a body.

methods.name: apply_impulse
methods.description: Apply a positioned impulse (which will be affected by the body mass and shape). This is the equivalent of hitting a billiard ball with a cue: a force that is applied once, and only once. Both the impulse and the position are in global coordinates, and the position is relative to the object's origin.

methods.name: get_colliding_bodies
methods.description: Return a list of the bodies colliding with this one. By default, number of max contacts reported is at 0 , see [method set_max_contacts_reported] to increase it.  Note that the result of this test is not immediate after moving objects. For performance, list of collisions is updated once per frame and before the physics step. Consider using signals instead.

methods.name: set_axis_velocity
methods.description: Set an axis velocity. The velocity in the given vector axis will be set as the given vector length. This is useful for jumping behavior.

signals.name: body_entered
signals.description: Emitted when a body enters into contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.

signals.name: body_exited
signals.description: Emitted when a body shape exits contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.

signals.name: body_shape_entered
signals.description:
Emitted when a body enters into contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.
				This signal not only receives the body that collided with this one, but also its [RID] (body_id), the shape index from the colliding body (body_shape), and the shape index from this body (local_shape) the other body collided with.

signals.name: body_shape_exited
signals.description:
Emitted when a body shape exits contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.
				This signal not only receives the body that stopped colliding with this one, but also its [RID] (body_id), the shape index from the colliding body (body_shape), and the shape index from this body (local_shape) the other body stopped colliding with.

signals.name: sleeping_state_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the body changes its sleeping state. Either by sleeping or waking up.

constants.name: MODE_RIGID
constants.description: Rigid body. This is the "natural" state of a rigid body. It is affected by forces, and can move, rotate, and be affected by user code.

constants.name: MODE_STATIC
constants.description: Static mode. The body behaves like a [StaticBody], and can only move by user code.

constants.name: MODE_CHARACTER
constants.description: Character body. This behaves like a rigid body, but can not rotate.

constants.name: MODE_KINEMATIC
constants.description: Kinematic body. The body behaves like a [KinematicBody], and can only move by user code.

properties.name: angular_damp
properties.description: Damps RigidBody's rotational forces.

properties.name: angular_velocity
properties.description: RigidBody's rotational velocity.

properties.name: bounce
properties.description: RigidBody's bounciness.

properties.name: can_sleep
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the RigidBody will not calculate forces and will act as a static body while there is no movement. It will wake up when forces are applied through other collisions or when the [code]apply_impulse[/code] method is used.

properties.name: contact_monitor
properties.description: If true, the RigidBody will emit signals when it collides with another RigidBody.

properties.name: contacts_reported
properties.description: The maximum contacts to report. Bodies can keep a log of the contacts with other bodies, this is enabled by setting the maximum amount of contacts reported to a number greater than 0.

properties.name: continuous_cd
properties.description:
If [code]true[/code] continuous collision detection is used.
			Continuous collision detection tries to predict where a moving body will collide, instead of moving it and correcting its movement if it collided. Continuous collision detection is more precise, and misses less impacts by small, fast-moving objects. Not using continuous collision detection is faster to compute, but can miss small, fast-moving objects.

properties.name: custom_integrator
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] internal force integration will be disabled (like gravity or air friction) for this body. Other than collision response, the body will only move as determined by the [method _integrate_forces] function, if defined.

properties.name: friction
properties.description: The body friction, from 0 (frictionless) to 1 (max friction).

properties.name: gravity_scale
properties.description: This is multiplied by the global 3D gravity setting found in "Project > Project Settings > Physics > 3d" to produce RigidBody's gravity. E.g. a value of 1 will be normal gravity, 2 will apply double gravity, and 0.5 will apply half gravity to this object.

properties.name: linear_damp
properties.description: RigidBody's linear damp. Default value: -1, cannot be less than -1. If this value is different from -1, any linear damp derived from the world or areas will be overridden.

properties.name: linear_velocity
properties.description: RigidBody's linear velocity. Can be used sporadically, but [b]DON'T SET THIS IN EVERY FRAME[/b], because physics may run in another thread and runs at a different granularity. Use [method _integrate_forces] as your process loop for precise control of the body state.

properties.name: mass
properties.description: RigidBody's mass.

properties.name: mode
properties.description: The body mode from the MODE_* enum. Modes include: MODE_STATIC, MODE_KINEMATIC, MODE_RIGID, and MODE_CHARACTER.

properties.name: sleeping
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] RigidBody is sleeping and will not calculate forces until woken up by a collision or the [code]apply_impulse[/code] method.

properties.name: weight
properties.description: RigidBody's weight based on its mass and the global 3D gravity. Global values are set in "Project > Project Settings > Physics > 3d".

AudioEffectLimiter.name: AudioEffectLimiter
AudioEffectLimiter.brief_description: Adds a soft clip Limiter audio effect to an Audio bus.
AudioEffectLimiter.description:
A limiter is similar to a compressor, but its less flexible and designed to disallow sound going over a given dB threshold. Adding one in the Master Bus is always recommended to reduce the effects of clipping.
		Soft clipping starts to reduce the peaks a little below the threshold level and progressively increases its effect as the input level increases such that the threshold is never exceeded.

properties.name: ceiling_db
properties.description: The waveform's maximum allowed value. Value can range from -20 to -0.1. Default value: [code]-0.1dB[/code].

properties.name: soft_clip_db
properties.description: Applies a gain to the limited waves. Value can range from 0 to 6. Default value: [code]2dB[/code].

properties.name: threshold_db
properties.description: Threshold from which the limiter begins to be active. Value can range from -30 to 0. Default value: [code]0dB[/code].

PinJoint2D.name: PinJoint2D
PinJoint2D.description: Pin Joint for 2D Rigid Bodies. It pins 2 bodies (rigid or static) together, or a single body to a fixed position in space.

properties.name: softness
properties.description: The higher this value, the more the bond to the pinned partner can flex.

properties.name: size
properties.description: Size of the cuboid mesh. Defaults to (2, 2, 2).

properties.name: subdivide_depth
properties.description: Number of extra edge loops inserted along the z-axis. Defaults to 0.

properties.name: subdivide_height
properties.description: Number of extra edge loops inserted along the y-axis. Defaults to 0.

properties.name: subdivide_width
properties.description: Number of extra edge loops inserted along the x-axis. Defaults to 0.

InputEvent.name: InputEvent
InputEvent.description: Base class of all sort of input event. See [method Node._input].

methods.name: action_match
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if this event matches [code]event[/code].

methods.name: as_text
methods.description: Returns a [String] representation of the event.

methods.name: is_action
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if this input event matches a pre-defined action of any type.

methods.name: is_action_pressed
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the given action is being pressed (and is not an echo event for KEY events). Not relevant for the event types [code]MOUSE_MOTION[/code], [code]SCREEN_DRAG[/code] or [code]NONE[/code].

methods.name: is_action_released
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the given action is released (i.e. not pressed). Not relevant for the event types [code]MOUSE_MOTION[/code], [code]SCREEN_DRAG[/code] or [code]NONE[/code].

methods.name: is_action_type
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if this input event's type is one of the [code]InputEvent[/code] constants.

methods.name: is_echo
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if this input event is an echo event (only for events of type KEY).

methods.name: is_pressed
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if this input event is pressed. Not relevant for the event types [code]MOUSE_MOTION[/code], [code]SCREEN_DRAG[/code] or [code]NONE[/code].

properties.name: device
properties.description: The event's device ID.

AudioEffectEQ21.name: AudioEffectEQ21
AudioEffectEQ21.brief_description:
Adds a 21-band equalizer audio effect to an Audio bus. Gives you control over frequencies from 22 Hz to 22000 Hz.
		Each frequency can be modulated between -60/+24 dB.
AudioEffectEQ21.description:
Frequency bands :
		Band 1 : 22 Hz
		Band 2 : 32 Hz
		Band 3 : 44 Hz
		Band 4 : 63 Hz
		Band 5 : 90 Hz
		Band 6 : 125 Hz
		Band 7 : 175 Hz
		Band 8 : 250 Hz
		Band 9 : 350 Hz
		Band 10 : 500 Hz
		Band 11 : 700 Hz
		Band 12 : 1000 Hz
		Band 13 : 1400 Hz
		Band 14 : 2000 Hz
		Band 15 : 2800 Hz
		Band 16 : 4000 Hz
		Band 17 : 5600 Hz
		Band 18 : 8000 Hz
		Band 19 : 11000 Hz
		Band 20 : 16000 Hz
		Band 21 : 22000 Hz

		See also [AudioEffectEQ], [AudioEffectEQ6], [AudioEffectEQ10].

DampedSpringJoint2D.name: DampedSpringJoint2D
DampedSpringJoint2D.description: Damped spring constraint for 2D physics. This resembles a spring joint that always wants to go back to a given length.

properties.name: damping
properties.description: The spring joint's damping ratio. A value between [code]0[/code] and [code]1[/code]. When the two bodies move into different directions the system tries to align them to the spring axis again. A high [code]damping[/code] value forces the attached bodies to align faster. Default value: [code]1[/code]

properties.name: length
properties.description: The spring joint's maximum length. The two attached bodies cannot stretch it past this value. Default value: [code]50[/code]

properties.name: rest_length
properties.description: When the bodies attached to the spring joint move they stretch or squash it. The joint always tries to resize towards this length. Default value: [code]0[/code]

properties.name: stiffness
properties.description: The higher the value, the less the bodies attached to the joint will deform it. The joint applies an opposing force to the bodies, the product of the stiffness multiplied by the size difference from its resting length. Default value: [code]20[/code]

Shape.name: Shape
Shape.brief_description: Base class for all 3D shape resources.
Shape.description: Base class for all 3D shape resources. All 3D shapes that inherit from this can be set into a [PhysicsBody] or [Area].

InputEventMouseButton.name: InputEventMouseButton
InputEventMouseButton.brief_description: Input event type for mouse button events.
InputEventMouseButton.description: Contains mouse click information. See [method Node._input].

properties.name: button_index
properties.description: Mouse button identifier, one of the BUTTON_* or BUTTON_WHEEL_* constants in [@GlobalScope].

properties.name: doubleclick
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the mouse button's state is a double-click. If [code]false[/code] the mouse button's state is released.

properties.name: factor
properties.description: TO TALK in PR, reduz said : i think it's used for apple touch but i don't remember what it does

properties.name: pressed
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the mouse button's state is pressed. If [code]false[/code] the mouse button's state is released.

Panel.name: Panel
Panel.brief_description: Provides an opaque background for [Control] children.
Panel.description: Panel is a [Control] that displays an opaque background. It's commonly used as a parent and container for other types of [Control] nodes.

WindowDialog.name: WindowDialog
WindowDialog.description: Windowdialog is the base class for all window-based dialogs. It's a by-default toplevel [Control] that draws a window decoration and allows motion and resizing.

methods.name: get_close_button
methods.description: Return the close [TextureButton].

properties.name: resizable
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the user can resize the window. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: window_title
properties.description: The text displayed in the window's title bar. Default value: "Save a File".

MultiMeshInstance.name: MultiMeshInstance
MultiMeshInstance.description:
[code]MultiMeshInstance[/code] is a specialized node to instance [GeometryInstance]s based on a [MultiMesh] resource.
		This is useful to optimize the rendering of a high amount of instances of a given mesh (for example tree in a forest or grass strands).

properties.name: multimesh
properties.description: The [MultiMesh] resource that will be used and shared among all instances of the [code]MultiMeshInstance[/code].

TextureRect.name: TextureRect
TextureRect.brief_description: Draws a sprite or a texture inside a User Interface. The texture can tile or not.
TextureRect.description: Use TextureRect to draw icons and sprites in your User Interfaces. To create panels and menu boxes, take a look at [NinePatchFrame]. Its Stretch Mode property controls the texture's scale and placement. It can scale, tile and stay centered inside its bounding rectangle. TextureRect is one of the 5 most common nodes to create game UI.

constants.name: STRETCH_SCALE_ON_EXPAND
constants.description: Scale to fit the node's bounding rectangle, only if [code]expand[/code] is [code]true[/code]. Default [code]stretch_mode[/code], for backwards compatibility. Until you set [code]expand[/code] to [code]true[/code], the texture will behave like [code]STRETCH_KEEP[/code].

constants.name: STRETCH_SCALE
constants.description: Scale to fit the node's bounding rectangle.

constants.name: STRETCH_TILE
constants.description: Tile inside the node's bounding rectangle.

constants.name: STRETCH_KEEP
constants.description: The texture keeps its original size and stays in the bounding rectangle's top-left corner.

constants.name: STRETCH_KEEP_CENTERED
constants.description: The texture keeps its original size and stays centered in the node's bounding rectangle.

constants.name: STRETCH_KEEP_ASPECT
constants.description: Scale the texture to fit the node's bounding rectangle, but maintain the texture's aspect ratio.

constants.name: STRETCH_KEEP_ASPECT_CENTERED
constants.description: Scale the texture to fit the node's bounding rectangle, center it and maintain its aspect ratio.

constants.name: STRETCH_KEEP_ASPECT_COVERED
constants.description: Scale the texture so that the shorter side fits the bounding rectangle. The other side clips to the node's limits.

properties.name: expand
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], the texture scales to fit its bounding rectangle. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: stretch_mode
properties.description: Controls the texture's behavior when you resize the node's bounding rectangle. Set it to one of the [code]STRETCH_*[/code] constants. See the constants to learn more.

properties.name: texture
properties.description: The node's [Texture] resource.

Animation.name: Animation
Animation.brief_description: Contains data used to animate everything in the engine.
Animation.description:
An Animation resource contains data used to animate everything in the engine. Animations are divided into tracks, and each track must be linked to a node. The state of that node can be changed through time, by adding timed keys (events) to the track.
		Animations are just data containers, and must be added to odes such as an [AnimationPlayer] or [AnimationTreePlayer] to be played back.

methods.name: add_track
methods.description: Add a track to the Animation. The track type must be specified as any of the values in the TYPE_* enumeration.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear the animation (clear all tracks and reset all).

methods.name: copy_track
methods.description: Adds a new track that is a copy of the given track from [code]to_animation[/code].

methods.name: find_track
methods.description: Return the index of the specified track. If the track is not found, return -1.

methods.name: get_track_count
methods.description: Return the amount of tracks in the animation.

methods.name: method_track_get_key_indices
methods.description: Return all the key indices of a method track, given a position and delta time.

methods.name: method_track_get_name
methods.description: Return the method name of a method track.

methods.name: method_track_get_params
methods.description: Return the arguments values to be called on a method track for a given key in a given track.

methods.name: remove_track
methods.description: Remove a track by specifying the track index.

methods.name: track_find_key
methods.description: Find the key index by time in a given track. Optionally, only find it if the exact time is given.

methods.name: track_get_interpolation_loop_wrap
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the track at [code]idx[/code] wraps the interpolation loop. Default value: [code]true[/code].

methods.name: track_get_interpolation_type
methods.description: Return the interpolation type of a given track, from the INTERPOLATION_* enum.

methods.name: track_get_key_count
methods.description: Return the amount of keys in a given track.

methods.name: track_get_key_time
methods.description: Return the time at which the key is located.

methods.name: track_get_key_transition
methods.description: Return the transition curve (easing) for a specific key (see built-in math function "ease").

methods.name: track_get_key_value
methods.description: Return the value of a given key in a given track.

methods.name: track_get_path
methods.description: Get the path of a track. for more information on the path format, see [method track_set_path]

methods.name: track_get_type
methods.description: Get the type of a track.

methods.name: track_insert_key
methods.description: Insert a generic key in a given track.

methods.name: track_is_enabled
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the track at index [code]idx[/code] is enabled.

methods.name: track_is_imported
methods.description: Return true if the given track is imported. Else, return false.

methods.name: track_move_down
methods.description: Move a track down.

methods.name: track_move_up
methods.description: Move a track up.

methods.name: track_remove_key
methods.description: Remove a key by index in a given track.

methods.name: track_remove_key_at_position
methods.description: Remove a key by position (seconds) in a given track.

methods.name: track_set_enabled
methods.description: Enables/disables the given track. Tracks are enabled by default.

methods.name: track_set_imported
methods.description: Set the given track as imported or not.

methods.name: track_set_interpolation_loop_wrap
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the track at [code]idx[/code] wraps the interpolation loop.

methods.name: track_set_interpolation_type
methods.description: Set the interpolation type of a given track, from the INTERPOLATION_* enum.

methods.name: track_set_key_transition
methods.description: Set the transition curve (easing) for a specific key (see built-in math function "ease").

methods.name: track_set_key_value
methods.description: Set the value of an existing key.

methods.name: track_set_path
methods.description: Set the path of a track. Paths must be valid scene-tree paths to a node, and must be specified starting from the parent node of the node that will reproduce the animation. Tracks that control properties or bones must append their name after the path, separated by ":". Example: "character/skeleton:ankle" or "character/mesh:transform/local"

methods.name: transform_track_insert_key
methods.description: Insert a transform key for a transform track.

methods.name: transform_track_interpolate
methods.description: Return the interpolated value of a transform track at a given time (in seconds). An array consisting of 3 elements: position ([Vector3]), rotation ([Quat]) and scale ([Vector3]).

methods.name: value_track_get_key_indices
methods.description: Return all the key indices of a value track, given a position and delta time.

methods.name: value_track_get_update_mode
methods.description: Return the update mode of a value track.

methods.name: value_track_set_update_mode
methods.description: Set the update mode (UPDATE_*) of a value track.

constants.name: TYPE_VALUE
constants.description: Value tracks set values in node properties, but only those which can be Interpolated.

constants.name: TYPE_TRANSFORM
constants.description: Transform tracks are used to change node local transforms or skeleton pose bones. Transitions are Interpolated.

constants.name: TYPE_METHOD
constants.description: Method tracks call functions with given arguments per key.

constants.name: INTERPOLATION_NEAREST
constants.description: No interpolation (nearest value).

constants.name: INTERPOLATION_LINEAR
constants.description: Linear interpolation.

constants.name: INTERPOLATION_CUBIC
constants.description: Cubic interpolation.

constants.name: UPDATE_CONTINUOUS
constants.description: Update between keyframes.

constants.name: UPDATE_DISCRETE
constants.description: Update at the keyframes and hold the value.

constants.name: UPDATE_TRIGGER
constants.description: Update at the keyframes.

properties.name: length
properties.description: The total length of the animation (in seconds). Note that length is not delimited by the last key, as this one may be before or after the end to ensure correct interpolation and looping.

properties.name: loop
properties.description: A flag indicating that the animation must loop. This is uses for correct interpolation of animation cycles, and for hinting the player that it must restart the animation.

properties.name: step
properties.description: The animation step value.

RemoteTransform leads the [Transform] of another [Spatial] derived Node (called the remote node) in the scene.
		It can be set to track another Node's position, rotation and/or scale. It can update using either global or local coordinates.

properties.name: use_global_coordinates

PoolVector2Array.name: PoolVector2Array
PoolVector2Array.description: An Array specifically designed to hold Vector2.

methods.name: PoolVector2Array
methods.description: Construct a new [code]PoolVector2Array[/code]. Optionally, you can pass in an Array that will be converted.

methods.name: append
methods.description: Append an element at the end of the array (alias of [method push_back]).

methods.name: append_array
methods.description: Append an [code]PoolVector2Array[/code] at the end of this array.

methods.name: insert
methods.description: Insert a new element at a given position in the array. The position must be valid, or at the end of the array (pos==size()).

methods.name: invert

methods.name: push_back

methods.name: resize

methods.name: size
