AudioEffectBandLimitFilter.name: AudioEffectBandLimitFilter
AudioEffectBandLimitFilter.brief_description: Adds a band limit filter to the Audio Bus.
AudioEffectBandLimitFilter.description: Limits the frequencies in a range around the [member cutoff_hz] and allows frequencies outside of this range to pass.

ConvexPolygonShape2D.name: ConvexPolygonShape2D
ConvexPolygonShape2D.description:
Convex Polygon Shape for 2D physics. A convex polygon, whatever its shape, is internally decomposed into as many convex polygons as needed to ensure all collision checks against it are always done on convex polygons (which are faster to check).
		The main difference between a [code]ConvexPolygonShape2D[/code] and a [ConcavePolygonShape2D] is that a concave polygon assumes it is concave and uses a more complex method of collision detection, and a convex one forces itself to be convex in order to speed up collision detection.

methods.name: set_point_cloud
methods.description: Currently, this method does nothing.

properties.name: points
properties.description: The polygon's list of vertices. Can be in either clockwise or counterclockwise order.

RigidBody2D.name: RigidBody2D
RigidBody2D.brief_description: A body that is controlled by the 2D physics engine.
RigidBody2D.description:
This node implements simulated 2D physics. You do not control a RigidBody2D directly. Instead you apply forces to it (gravity, impulses, etc.) and the physics simulation calculates the resulting movement based on its mass, friction, and other physical properties.
		A RigidBody2D has 4 behavior modes (see [member mode]):
		- [b]Rigid[/b]: The body behaves as a physical object. It collides with other bodies and responds to forces applied to it. This is the default mode.
		- [b]Static[/b]: The body behaves like a [StaticBody2D] and does not move.
		- [b]Character[/b]: Similar to [code]Rigid[/code] mode, but the body can not rotate.
		- [b]Kinematic[/b]: The body behaves like a [KinematicBody2D], and must be moved by code.
		[b]Note:[/b] You should not change a RigidBody2D's [code]position[/code] or [code]linear_velocity[/code] every frame or even very often. If you need to directly affect the body's state, use [method _integrate_forces], which allows you to directly access the physics state.
		If you need to override the default physics behavior, you can write a custom force integration. See [member custom_integrator].

methods.name: _integrate_forces
methods.description: Allows you to read and safely modify the simulation state for the object. Use this instead of [Node._physics_process] if you need to directly change the body's [code]position[/code] or other physics properties. By default it works in addition to the usual physics behavior, but [member custom_integrator] allows you to disable the default behavior and write custom force integration for a body.

methods.name: add_force
methods.description: Adds a positioned force to the body. Both the force and the offset from the body origin are in global coordinates.

methods.name: apply_impulse
methods.description: Applies a positioned impulse to the body (which will be affected by the body mass and shape). This is the equivalent of hitting a billiard ball with a cue: a force that is applied instantaneously. Both the impulse and the offset from the body origin are in global coordinates.

methods.name: get_colliding_bodies
methods.description: Returns a list of the bodies colliding with this one. Use [member contacts_reported] to set the maximum number reported. You must also set [member contact_monitor] to [code]true[/code]. Note that the result of this test is not immediate after moving objects. For performance, list of collisions is updated once per frame and before the physics step. Consider using signals instead.

methods.name: set_axis_velocity
methods.description: Sets the body's velocity on the given axis. The velocity in the given vector axis will be set as the given vector length. This is useful for jumping behavior.

methods.name: test_motion
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if a collision would result from moving in the given vector. [code]margin[/code] increases the size of the shapes involved in the collision detection, and [code]result[/code] is an object of type [Physics2DTestMotionResult], which contains additional information about the collision (should there be one).

signals.name: body_entered
signals.description: Emitted when a body enters into contact with this one. [member contact_monitor] must be [code]true[/code] and [member contacts_reported] greater than [code]0[/code].

signals.name: body_exited
signals.description: Emitted when a body exits contact with this one. [member contact_monitor] must be [code]true[/code] and [member contacts_reported] greater than [code]0[/code].

signals.name: body_shape_entered
signals.description: Emitted when a body enters into contact with this one. Reports colliding shape information. See [CollisionObject2D] for shape index information. [member contact_monitor] must be [code]true[/code] and [member contacts_reported] greater than [code]0[/code].

signals.name: body_shape_exited
signals.description: Emitted when a body shape exits contact with this one. Reports colliding shape information. See [CollisionObject2D] for shape index information. [member contact_monitor] must be [code]true[/code] and [member contacts_reported] greater than [code]0[/code].

signals.name: sleeping_state_changed
signals.description: Emitted when [member sleeping] changes.

constants.name: MODE_RIGID
constants.description: Rigid mode. The body behaves as a physical object. It collides with other bodies and responds to forces applied to it. This is the default mode.

constants.name: MODE_STATIC
constants.description: Static mode. The body behaves like a [StaticBody2D] and does not move.

constants.name: MODE_CHARACTER
constants.description: Character mode. Similar to [code]MODE_RIGID[/code], but the body can not rotate.

constants.name: MODE_KINEMATIC
constants.description: Kinematic mode. The body behaves like a [KinematicBody2D], and must be moved by code.

constants.name: CCD_MODE_DISABLED
constants.description: Continuous collision detection disabled. This is the fastest way to detect body collisions, but can miss small, fast-moving objects.

constants.name: CCD_MODE_CAST_RAY
constants.description: Continuous collision detection enabled using raycasting. This is faster than shapecasting but less precise.

constants.name: CCD_MODE_CAST_SHAPE
constants.description: Continuous collision detection enabled using shapecasting. This is the slowest CCD method and the most precise.

properties.name: angular_damp
properties.description: Damps the body's [member angular_velocity]. If [code]-1[/code] the body will use the "Default Angular Damp" in "Project > Project Settings > Physics > 2d". Default value: [code]-1[/code].

properties.name: angular_velocity
properties.description: The body's rotational velocity.

properties.name: applied_force
properties.description: The body's total applied force.

properties.name: applied_torque
properties.description: The body's total applied torque.

properties.name: bounce
properties.description: The body's bounciness. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: can_sleep
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the body will not calculate forces and will act as a static body if there is no movement. The body will wake up when other forces are applied via collisions or by using [method apply_impulse] or [method add_force]. Default value: [code]true[/code].

properties.name: contact_monitor
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the body will emit signals when it collides with another RigidBody2D. See also [member contacts_reported]. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: contacts_reported
properties.description: The maximum number of contacts to report. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: continuous_cd
properties.description:
Continuous collision detection mode. Default value: [code]CCD_MODE_DISABLED[/code].
			Continuous collision detection tries to predict where a moving body will collide instead of moving it and correcting its movement after collision. Continuous collision detection is slower, but more precise and misses fewer collisions with small, fast-moving objects. Raycasting and shapecasting methods are available. See [code]CCD_MODE_[/code] constants for details.

properties.name: custom_integrator
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] internal force integration is disabled for this body. Aside from collision response, the body will only move as determined by the [method _integrate_forces] function.

properties.name: friction
properties.description: The body's friction. Values range from [code]0[/code] (frictionless) to [code]1[/code] (maximum friction). Default value: [code]1[/code].

properties.name: gravity_scale
properties.description: Multiplies the gravity applied to the body. The body's gravity is calculated from the "Default Gravity" value in "Project > Project Settings > Physics > 2d" and/or any additional gravity vector applied by [Area2D]s. Default value: [code]1[/code].

properties.name: inertia
properties.description: The body's moment of inertia. This is like mass, but for rotation: it determines how much torque it takes to rotate the body. The moment of inertia is usually computed automatically from the mass and the shapes, but this function allows you to set a custom value. Set 0 (or negative) inertia to return to automatically computing it.

properties.name: linear_damp
properties.description: Damps the body's [member linear_velocity]. If [code]-1[/code] the body will use the "Default Linear Damp" in "Project > Project Settings > Physics > 2d". Default value: [code]-1[/code].

properties.name: linear_velocity
properties.description: The body's linear velocity.

properties.name: mass
properties.description: The body's mass. Default value: [code]1[/code].

properties.name: mode
properties.description: The body's mode. See [code]MODE_*[/code] constants. Default value: [code]MODE_RIGID[/code].

properties.name: sleeping
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the body is sleeping and will not calculate forces until woken up by a collision or by using [method apply_impulse] or [method add_force].

properties.name: weight
properties.description: The body's weight based on its mass and the "Default Gravity" value in "Project > Project Settings > Physics > 2d".

RayCast2D.name: RayCast2D
RayCast2D.brief_description: Query the closest object intersecting a ray.
RayCast2D.description:
A RayCast represents a line from its origin to its destination position, [code]cast_to[/code]. It is used to query the 2D space in order to find the closest object along the path of the ray.
		RayCast2D can ignore some objects by adding them to the exception list via [code]add_exception[/code], by setting proper filtering with collision layers, or by filtering object types with type masks.
		Only enabled raycasts will be able to query the space and report collisions.
		RayCast2D calculates intersection every physics frame (see [Node]), and the result is cached so it can be used later until the next frame. If multiple queries are required between physics frames (or during the same frame) use [method force_raycast_update] after adjusting the raycast.

methods.name: add_exception
methods.description: Adds a collision exception so the ray does not report collisions with the specified node.

methods.name: add_exception_rid
methods.description: Adds a collision exception so the ray does not report collisions with the specified [RID].

methods.name: clear_exceptions
methods.description: Removes all collision exceptions for this ray.

methods.name: force_raycast_update
methods.description: Updates the collision information for the ray.  Use this method to update the collision information immediately instead of waiting for the next [code]_physics_process[/code] call, for example if the ray or its parent has changed state. Note: [code]enabled == true[/code] is not required for this to work.

methods.name: get_collider
get_collider_shape
get_collision_mask_bit
methods.description: Return an individual bit on the collision mask.

methods.name: get_collision_normal
methods.description: Returns the normal of the intersecting object's shape at the collision point.

methods.name: get_collision_point
methods.description: Returns the collision point at which the ray intersects the closest object. Note: this point is in the [b]global[/b] coordinate system.

methods.name: is_colliding
methods.description: Return whether the closest object the ray is pointing to is colliding with the vector (considering the vector length).

methods.name: remove_exception
methods.description: Removes a collision exception so the ray does report collisions with the specified node.

methods.name: remove_exception_rid
methods.description: Removes a collision exception so the ray does report collisions with the specified [RID].

methods.name: set_collision_mask_bit
methods.description: Set/clear individual bits on the collision mask. This makes selecting the areas scanned easier.

properties.name: cast_to
properties.description: The ray's destination point, relative to the RayCast's [code]position[/code].

properties.name: collision_mask
properties.description: The ray's collision mask. Only objects in at least one collision layer enabled in the mask will be detected.

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], collisions will be reported. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: exclude_parent
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], the parent node will be excluded from collision detection. Default value: [code]true[/code].

constants.name: RADIANCE_SIZE_32
constants.description: Radiance texture size is 32x32 pixels.

constants.name: RADIANCE_SIZE_64
constants.description: Radiance texture size is 64x64 pixels.

constants.name: RADIANCE_SIZE_128
constants.description: Radiance texture size is 128x128 pixels.

constants.name: RADIANCE_SIZE_256
constants.description: Radiance texture size is 256x256 pixels.

constants.name: RADIANCE_SIZE_512
constants.description: Radiance texture size is 512x512 pixels.

constants.name: RADIANCE_SIZE_1024
constants.description: Radiance texture size is 1024x1024 pixels.

constants.name: RADIANCE_SIZE_2048
constants.description: Radiance texture size is 2048x2048 pixels.

constants.name: RADIANCE_SIZE_MAX
constants.description: Radiance texture size is the largest size it can be.

properties.name: radiance_size
properties.description:
The Sky's radiance map size.
			The higher the radiance map size, the more detailed the lighting from the Sky will be.
			See RADIANCE_SIZE_* constants for values. Default size is RADIANCE_SIZE_512.

Color.name: Color
Color.brief_description: Color in RGBA format with some support for ARGB format.
Color.description:
A color is represented as red, green and blue (r,g,b) components. Additionally, "a" represents the alpha component, often used for transparency. Values are in floating point and usually range from 0 to 1.  Some methods (such as set_modulate(color)) may accept values > 1.
		You can also create a color from standardised color names with [method @GDScript.ColorN].

methods.name: Color
methods.description:
Constructs a color from an RGBA profile using values between 0 and 1 (float).
				[codeblock]
				var c = Color(0.2, 1.0, .7, .8) # a color of an RGBA(51, 255, 178, 204)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: Color
methods.description:
Constructs a color from an RGB profile using values between 0 and 1 (float). Alpha will always be 1.
				[codeblock]
				var c = Color(0.2, 1.0, .7) # a color of an RGBA(51, 255, 178, 255)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: Color
methods.description:
Constructs a color from a 32-bit integer (each byte represents a component of the RGBA profile).
				[codeblock]
				var c = Color(274) # a color of an RGBA(0, 0, 1, 18)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: Color
methods.description:
Constructs a color from an HTML hexadecimal color string in ARGB or RGB format. See also [method @GDScript.ColorN].
				The following string formats are supported:
					[code]"#ff00ff00"[/code] - ARGB format with '#'
					[code]"ff00ff00"[/code] - ARGB format
					[code]"#ff00ff"[/code] - RGB format with '#'
					[code]"ff00ff"[/code] - RGB format
				[codeblock]
				# The following code creates the same color of an RGBA(178, 217, 10, 255)
				var c1 = Color("#ffb2d90a") # ARGB format with '#'
				var c2 = Color("ffb2d90a")  # ARGB format
				var c3 = Color("#b2d90a")   # RGB format with '#'
				var c4 = Color("b2d90a")    # RGB format
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: blend
methods.description:
Returns a new color resulting from blending this color over another color. If the color is opaque, the result would also be opaque. The other color could then take a range of values with different alpha values.
				[codeblock]
				var bg = Color(0.0, 1.0, 0.0, 0.5) # Green with alpha of 50%
				var fg = Color(1.0, 0.0, 0.0, .5) # Red with alpha of 50%
				var blendedColor = bg.blend(fg) # Brown with alpha of 75%
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: contrasted
darkened
methods.description:
Returns a new color resulting from making this color darker by the specified percentage (0-1).
				[codeblock]
				var green = Color(0.0, 1.0, 0.0)
				var darkgreen = green.darkened(0.2) # 20% darker than regular green
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: gray
methods.description:
Returns the color's grayscale.
				The gray is calculated by (r + g + b) / 3.
				[codeblock]
				var c = Color(0.2, 0.45, 0.82)
				var gray = c.gray() # a value of 0.466667
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: inverted
lightened
methods.description:
Returns a new color resulting from making this color lighter by the specified percentage (0-1).
				[codeblock]
				var green = Color(0.0, 1.0, 0.0)
				var lightgreen = green.lightened(0.2) # 20% lighter than regular green
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: linear_interpolate
to_argb32
methods.description:
Returns the color's 32-bit integer in ARGB format (each byte represents a component of the ARGB profile). More compatible with DirectX.
				[codeblock]
				var c = Color(1, .5, .2)
				print(str(c.to_32())) # prints 4294934323
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: to_html
methods.description:
Returns the color's HTML hexadecimal color string in ARGB format (ex: [code]ff34f822[/code]).
				Optionally flag 'false' to not include alpha in hexadecimal string.
				[codeblock]
				var c = Color(1, 1, 1, .5)
				var s1 = c.to_html() # Results "7fffffff"
				var s2 = c.to_html(false) # Results 'ffffff'
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: to_rgba32
methods.description:
Returns the color's 32-bit integer in ARGB format (each byte represents a component of the ARGB profile).
				[codeblock]
				var c = Color(1, .5, .2)
				print(str(c.to_32())) # prints 4294934323
				[/codeblock]
				[i]This is same as [method to_argb32] but may be changed later to support RGBA format instead[/i].

properties.name: a
properties.description: Alpha (0 to 1)

properties.name: a8
properties.description: Alpha (0 to 255)

properties.name: b
properties.description: Blue (0 to 1)

properties.name: b8
properties.description: Blue (0 to 255)

properties.name: g
properties.description: Green (0 to 1)

properties.name: g8
properties.description: Green (0 to 255)

properties.name: h
properties.description: Hue (0 to 1)

properties.name: r
properties.description: Red (0 to 1)

properties.name: r8
properties.description: Red (0 to 255)

properties.name: s
properties.description: Saturation (0 to 1)

properties.name: v
properties.description: Value (0 to 1)

CollisionObject.name: CollisionObject
CollisionObject.description: CollisionObject is the base class for physics objects. It can hold any number of collision [Shape]s. Each shape must be assigned to a [i]shape owner[/i]. The CollisionObject can have any number of shape owners. Shape owners are not nodes and do not appear in the editor, but are accessible through code using the [code]shape_owner_*[/code] methods.

methods.name: _input_event
methods.description: Accepts unhandled [InputEvent]s. [code]click_position[/code] is the clicked location in world space and [code]click_normal[/code] is the normal vector extending from the clicked surface of the [Shape] at [code]shape_idx[/code]. Connect to the [code]input_event[/code] signal to easily pick up these events.

methods.name: create_shape_owner
methods.description: Creates a new shape owner for the given object. Returns [code]owner_id[/code] of the new owner for future reference.

methods.name: get_rid
methods.description: Returns the object's [RID].

methods.name: get_shape_owners
methods.description: Returns an [Array] of [code]owner_id[/code] identifiers. You can use these ids in other methods that take [code]owner_id[/code] as an argument.

methods.name: is_shape_owner_disabled
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the shape owner and its shapes are disabled.

methods.name: remove_shape_owner
methods.description: Removes the given shape owner.

methods.name: shape_find_owner
methods.description: Returns the [code]owner_id[/code] of the given shape.

methods.name: shape_owner_add_shape
methods.description: Adds a [Shape] to the shape owner.

methods.name: shape_owner_clear_shapes
methods.description: Removes all shapes from the shape owner.

methods.name: shape_owner_get_owner
methods.description: Returns the parent object of the given shape owner.

methods.name: shape_owner_get_shape
methods.description: Returns the [Shape] with the given id from the given shape owner.

methods.name: shape_owner_get_shape_count
methods.description: Returns the number of shapes the given shape owner contains.

methods.name: shape_owner_get_shape_index
methods.description: Returns the child index of the [Shape] with the given id from the given shape owner.

methods.name: shape_owner_get_transform
methods.description: Returns the shape owner's [Transform].

methods.name: shape_owner_remove_shape
methods.description: Removes a shape from the given shape owner.

methods.name: shape_owner_set_disabled
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] disables the given shape owner.

methods.name: shape_owner_set_transform
methods.description: Sets the [Transform] of the given shape owner.

signals.name: input_event
signals.description: Emitted when [method _input_event] receives an event. See its description for details.

signals.name: mouse_entered
signals.description: Emitted when the mouse pointer enters any of this object's shapes.

signals.name: mouse_exited
signals.description: Emitted when the mouse pointer exits all this object's shapes.

properties.name: input_capture_on_drag
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the [code]CollisionObject[/code] will continue to receive input events as the mouse is dragged across its shapes. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: input_ray_pickable
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the [CollisionObject]'s shapes will respond to [RayCast]s. Default value: [code]true[/code].

ParallaxBackground.name: ParallaxBackground
ParallaxBackground.brief_description: A node used to create a parallax scrolling background.
ParallaxBackground.description: A ParallaxBackground uses one or more [ParallaxLayer] child nodes to create a parallax effect. Each [ParallaxLayer] can move at a different speed using [member ParallaxLayer.motion_offset]. This creates an illusion of depth in a 2D game. If not used with a [Camera2D], you must manually calculate the [member scroll_offset].

properties.name: scroll_base_offset
properties.description: Base position offset of all [ParallaxLayer] children.

properties.name: scroll_base_scale
properties.description: Base motion scale of all [ParallaxLayer] children.

properties.name: scroll_ignore_camera_zoom
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] elements in [ParallaxLayer] child aren't affected by the zoom level of the camera.

properties.name: scroll_limit_begin
properties.description: Top left limits for scrolling to begin. If the camera is outside of this limit the background will stop scrolling. Must be lower than [member scroll_limit_end] to work.

properties.name: scroll_limit_end
properties.description: Right bottom limits for scrolling to end. If the camera is outside of this limit the background will stop scrolling. Must be higher than [member scroll_limit_begin] to work.

properties.name: scroll_offset
properties.description: The ParallaxBackground's scroll value. Calculated automatically when using a [Camera2D], but can be used to manually manage scrolling when no camera is present.

InputEventMouseMotion.name: InputEventMouseMotion
InputEventMouseMotion.brief_description: Input event type for mouse motion events.
InputEventMouseMotion.description: Contains mouse motion information. Supports relative, absolute positions and speed. See [method Node._input].

properties.name: relative
properties.description: Mouse position relative to the previous position (position at the last frame).

properties.name: speed
properties.description: Mouse speed.

ColorPicker.name: ColorPicker
ColorPicker.description: This is a simple color picker [Control]. It's useful for selecting a color from an RGB/RGBA colorspace.

methods.name: add_preset
methods.description: Adds the current selected to color to a list of colors (presets), the presets will be displayed in the color picker and the user will be able to select them, notice that the presets list is only for this color picker.

signals.name: color_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the color is changed.

properties.name: color
properties.description: The currently selected color.

properties.name: edit_alpha
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], shows an alpha channel slider (transparency).

properties.name: raw_mode
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], allows the color R, G, B component values to go beyond 1.0, which can be used for certain special operations that require it (like tinting without darkening or rendering sprites in HDR).

Marshalls.name: Marshalls
Marshalls.description: Provides data transformation and encoding utility functions.

methods.name: base64_to_raw
methods.description: Return [PoolByteArray] of a given base64 encoded String.

methods.name: base64_to_utf8
methods.description: Return utf8 String of a given base64 encoded String.

methods.name: base64_to_variant
methods.description: Return [Variant] of a given base64 encoded String.

methods.name: raw_to_base64
methods.description: Return base64 encoded String of a given [PoolByteArray].

methods.name: utf8_to_base64
methods.description: Return base64 encoded String of a given utf8 String.

methods.name: variant_to_base64
methods.description: Return base64 encoded String of a given [Variant].

InputEventJoypadMotion.name: InputEventJoypadMotion
InputEventJoypadMotion.brief_description: Input event type for gamepad joysticks and other motions. For buttons see [code]InputEventJoypadMotion[/code].
InputEventJoypadMotion.description: Stores information about joystick motions. One [code]InputEventJoypadMotion[/code] represents one axis at a time.

properties.name: axis
properties.description: Axis identifier. Use one of the [code]JOY_AXIS_*[/code] constants in [@global Scope].

properties.name: axis_value
properties.description: Current position of the joystick on the given axis. The value ranges from [code]-1.0[/code] to [code]1.0[/code]. A value of [code]0[/code] means the axis is in its resting position.

AudioEffectNotchFilter.name: AudioEffectNotchFilter
AudioEffectNotchFilter.brief_description: Adds a notch filter to the Audio Bus.
AudioEffectNotchFilter.description: Attenuates frequencies in a narrow band around the [member cutoff_hz] and cuts frequencies outside of this range.

Navigation.name: Navigation
Navigation.brief_description: A collection of [code]NavigationMesh[/code] resources and methods used for pathfinding.
Navigation.description: The Navigation node is used for basic or advanced navigation. By default it will automatically collect all child [code]NavigationMesh[/code] resources, but they can also be added on the fly through scripting. It can be used for generating a simple path between two points or it can be used to ensure that a navigation agent is angled perfectly to the terrain it is navigating.

methods.name: get_closest_point
methods.description: Returns the closest navigation point to the point passed.

methods.name: get_closest_point_normal
methods.description: Returns the surface normal of the navigation mesh at the point passed. For instance, if the point passed was at a 45 degree slope it would return something like (0.5,0.5,0). This is useful for rotating a navigation agent in accordance with the [code]NavigationMesh[/code].

methods.name: get_closest_point_owner
methods.description: Returns the nearest [code]NavigationMeshInstance[/code] to the point passed.

methods.name: get_closest_point_to_segment
methods.description: Returns the nearest point to the line segment passed. The third optional parameter takes collisions into account.

methods.name: get_simple_path
methods.description: Returns a path of points as a [code]PoolVector3Array[/code]. If [code]optimize[/code] is false the [code]NavigationMesh[/code] agent properties will be taken into account, otherwise it will return the nearest path and ignore agent radius, height, etc.

methods.name: navmesh_add
methods.description: Adds a [code]NavigationMesh[/code] to the list of NavigationMesh's in this node. Returns an id. Its position, rotation and scale are associated with the [code]Transform[/code] passed. The [code]Node[/code] (or [code]Object[/code]) that owns this node is an optional parameter.

methods.name: navmesh_remove
methods.description: Removes a [code]NavigationMesh[/code] from the list of NavigationMesh's in this node.

methods.name: navmesh_set_transform
methods.description: Associates a [code]NavigationMesh[/code]'s id with a [code]Transform[/code]. Its position, rotation and scale are based on the [code]Transform[/code] passed.

properties.name: up_vector
properties.description: Defines which direction is up. The default defines 0,1,0 as up which is the world up direction. To make this a ceiling use 0,-1,0 to define down as up.

GraphNode.name: GraphNode
GraphNode.brief_description: A GraphNode is a container with several input and output slots allowing connections between GraphNodes. Slots can have different, incompatible types.
GraphNode.description: A GraphNode is a container defined by a title. It can have 1 or more input and output slots, which can be enabled (shown) or disabled (not shown) and have different (incompatible) types. Colors can also be assigned to slots. A tuple of input and output slots is defined for each GUI element included in the GraphNode. Input and output connections are left and right slots, but only enabled slots are counted as connections.

methods.name: clear_all_slots
methods.description: Disable all input and output slots of the GraphNode.

methods.name: clear_slot
methods.description: Disable input and output slot whose index is 'idx'.

methods.name: get_connection_input_color
methods.description: Return the color of the input connection 'idx'.

methods.name: get_connection_input_count
methods.description: Return the number of enabled input slots (connections) to the GraphNode.

methods.name: get_connection_input_position
methods.description: Return the position of the input connection 'idx'.

methods.name: get_connection_input_type
methods.description: Return the type of the input connection 'idx'.

methods.name: get_connection_output_color
methods.description: Return the color of the output connection 'idx'.

methods.name: get_connection_output_count
methods.description: Return the number of enabled output slots (connections) of the GraphNode.

methods.name: get_connection_output_position
methods.description: Return the position of the output connection 'idx'.

methods.name: get_connection_output_type
methods.description: Return the type of the output connection 'idx'.

methods.name: get_slot_color_left
methods.description: Return the color set to 'idx' left (input) slot.

methods.name: get_slot_color_right
methods.description: Return the color set to 'idx' right (output) slot.

methods.name: get_slot_type_left
methods.description: Return the (integer) type of left (input) 'idx' slot.

methods.name: get_slot_type_right
methods.description: Return the (integer) type of right (output) 'idx' slot.

methods.name: is_slot_enabled_left
methods.description: Return true if left (input) slot 'idx' is enabled. False otherwise.

methods.name: is_slot_enabled_right
methods.description: Return true if right (output) slot 'idx' is enabled. False otherwise.

signals.name: close_request
signals.description: Signal sent on closing the GraphNode.

signals.name: dragged
signals.description: Signal sent when the GraphNode is dragged.

signals.name: offset_changed
signals.description: Signal sent when the GraphNode is moved.

signals.name: raise_request
signals.description: Signal sent when the GraphNode is requested to be displayed over other ones. Happens on focusing (clicking into) the GraphNode.

properties.name: offset
properties.description: The offset of the GraphNode, relative to the scroll offset of the [GraphEdit]. Note that you cannot use position directly, as [GraphEdit] is a [Container].

CollisionPolygon2D.name: CollisionPolygon2D
CollisionPolygon2D.description: Provides a 2D collision polygon to a [CollisionObject2D] parent. Polygon can be drawn in the editor or specified by a list of vertices.

constants.name: BUILD_SOLIDS
constants.description: Collisions will include the polygon and its contained area.

constants.name: BUILD_SEGMENTS
constants.description: Collisions will only include the polygon edges.

properties.name: build_mode
properties.description: Collision build mode. Use one of the [code]BUILD_*[/code] constants. Default value: [code]BUILD_SOLIDS[/code].

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] no collisions will be detected.

properties.name: one_way_collision
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] only edges that face up, relative to CollisionPolygon2D's rotation, will collide with other objects.

properties.name: polygon
properties.description: The polygon's list of vertices. The final point will be connected to the first.

CurveTexture.name: CurveTexture
CurveTexture.brief_description: A texture that shows a curve.
CurveTexture.description: Renders a given [Curve] provided to it. Simplifies the task of drawing curves and/or saving them as image files.

properties.name: curve
properties.description: The [code]curve[/code] rendered onto the texture.

properties.name: width
properties.description: The width of the texture.

StyleBoxFlat.name: StyleBoxFlat
StyleBoxFlat.brief_description: Customizable Stylebox with a given set of parameters. (no texture required)
StyleBoxFlat.description:
This stylebox can be used to achieve all kinds of looks without the need of a texture. Those properties are customizable:
		 - Color
		 - Border width (individual width for each border)
		 - Rounded corners (individual radius for each corner)
		 - Shadow
		 About corner radius:
		 	Setting corner radius to high values is allowed. As soon as corners would overlap the stylebox will switch to a relative system. Example:
			[codeblock]
			height = 30
			corner_radius_top_left = 50
			corner_radius_bottom_left = 100
			[/codeblock]
			The relative system now would take the 1:2 ratio of the two left corners to calculate the actual corner width. Both corners added will [b]never[/b] be more than the height. Result:
			[codeblock]
			corner_radius_top_left: 10
			corner_radius_bottom_left: 20
			[/codeblock]

properties.name: anti_aliasing
properties.description: Anti Aliasing draws a small ring around edges. This ring fades to transparent. As a result edges look much smoother. This is only noticeable when using rounded corners.

properties.name: anti_aliasing_size
properties.description: This changes the size of the faded ring. Higher values can be used to achieve a "blurry" effect.

properties.name: bg_color
properties.description: The background color of the stylebox.

properties.name: border_blend
properties.description: When set to true, the border will fade into the background color.

properties.name: border_color
properties.description: Sets the color of the border.

properties.name: border_width_bottom

properties.description: Border width for the left border.

properties.name: border_width_right

properties.name: border_width_top

properties.name: corner_detail
properties.description:
This sets the amount of vertices used for each corner. Higher values result in rounder corners but take more processing power to compute. When choosing a value you should take the corner radius ([method set_corner_radius]) into account.
			For corner radius smaller than 10: 4-5 should be enough
			For corner radius smaller than 30: 8-12 should be enough ...

properties.name: corner_radius_bottom_left
properties.description: The corner radius of the bottom left corner. When set to 0 the corner is not rounded.

properties.name: corner_radius_bottom_right
properties.description: The corner radius of the bottom right corner. When set to 0 the corner is not rounded.

properties.name: corner_radius_top_left
properties.description: The corner radius of the top left corner. When set to 0 the corner is not rounded.

properties.name: corner_radius_top_right
properties.description: The corner radius of the top right corner. When set to 0 the corner is not rounded.

properties.name: draw_center
properties.description: Toggels drawing of the inner part of the stylebox.

properties.name: expand_margin_bottom
properties.description: Expands the stylebox outside of the control rect on the bottom edge. Useful in combination with border_width_bottom. To draw a border outside the control rect.

properties.name: expand_margin_left

properties.name: expand_margin_right
properties.description: Expands the stylebox outside of the control rect on the right edge. Useful in combination with border_width_right. To draw a border outside the control rect.

properties.name: expand_margin_top
properties.description: Expands the stylebox outside of the control rect on the top edge. Useful in combination with border_width_top. To draw a border outside the control rect.

properties.name: shadow_color
properties.description: The color of the shadow. (This has no effect when shadow_size < 1)

properties.name: shadow_size
properties.description: The shadow size in pixels.

GDScriptFunctionState.name: GDScriptFunctionState
GDScriptFunctionState.brief_description: State of a function call after yielding.
GDScriptFunctionState.description: Calling [method @GDScript.yield] within a function will cause that function to yield and return its current state as an object of this type. The yielded function call can then be resumed later by calling [method resume] on this state object.

methods.name: is_valid
methods.description:
Check whether the function call may be resumed. This is not the case if the function state was already resumed.
				If [code]extended_check[/code] is enabled, it also checks if the associated script and object still exist. The extended check is done in debug mode as part of [method GDScriptFunctionState.resume], but you can use this if you know you may be trying to resume without knowing for sure the object and/or script have survived up to that point.

methods.name: resume
methods.description:
Resume execution of the yielded function call.
				If handed an argument, return the argument from the [method @GDScript.yield] call in the yielded function call. You can pass e.g. an [Array] to hand multiple arguments.
				This function returns what the resumed function call returns, possibly another function state if yielded again.

PhysicsServer.name: PhysicsServer
PhysicsServer.brief_description: Server interface for low level physics access.

methods.name: area_add_shape
methods.description: Adds a shape to the area, along with a transform matrix. Shapes are usually referenced by their index, so you should track which shape has a given index.

methods.name: area_attach_object_instance_id
methods.description: Assigns the area to a descendant of [Object], so it can exist in the node tree.

methods.name: area_clear_shapes
methods.description: Removes all shapes from an area. It does not delete the shapes, so they can be reassigned later.

methods.name: area_create
methods.description: Creates an [Area].

methods.name: area_get_object_instance_id
methods.description: Gets the instance ID of the object the area is assigned to.

methods.name: area_get_param

methods.name: area_get_shape

methods.name: area_get_shape_count
methods.description: Returns the number of shapes assigned to an area.

methods.description: Returns the transform matrix of a shape within an area.

methods.description: Returns the space assigned to the area.

methods.description: Returns the space override mode for the area.

methods.name: area_get_transform
methods.description: Returns the transform matrix for an area.

methods.name: area_is_ray_pickable
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] area collides with rays.

methods.name: area_remove_shape
methods.description: Removes a shape from an area. It does not delete the shape, so it can be reassigned later.

methods.name: area_set_collision_layer
methods.description: Assigns the area to one or many physics layers.

methods.name: area_set_collision_mask
methods.description: Sets which physics layers the area will monitor.

methods.name: area_set_monitor_callback
methods.description:
Sets the function to call when any body/area enters or exits the area. This callback will be called for any object interacting with the area, and takes five parameters:
				1: AREA_BODY_ADDED or AREA_BODY_REMOVED, depending on whether the object entered or exited the area.
				2: [RID] of the object that entered/exited the area.
				3: Instance ID of the object that entered/exited the area.
				4: The shape index of the object that entered/exited the area.
				5: The shape index of the area where the object entered/exited.

methods.name: area_set_param

methods.name: area_set_ray_pickable

methods.name: area_set_shape_transform

methods.name: area_set_space
methods.description: Assigns a space to the area.

methods.name: area_set_transform

methods.name: body_clear_shapes

methods.name: body_get_mode

methods.name: body_get_object_instance_id
methods.description: Gets the instance ID of the object the area is assigned to.

methods.name: body_get_param

methods.name: body_get_shape

methods.name: body_get_shape_count

methods.name: body_is_ray_pickable

methods.name: body_remove_collision_exception

Removes a body from the list of bodies exempt from collisions.
				Continuous collision detection tries to predict where a moving body will collide, instead of moving it and correcting its movement if it collided.

methods.name: body_remove_shape
methods.description: Removes a shape from a body. The shape is not deleted, so it can be reused afterwards.

methods.name: body_set_axis_velocity
methods.description: Sets an axis velocity. The velocity in the given vector axis will be set as the given vector length. This is useful for jumping behavior.

methods.name: body_set_collision_layer

methods.name: body_set_collision_mask
methods.description: Sets the physics layer or layers a body can collide with.

methods.name: body_set_enable_continuous_collision_detection
methods.description:
If [code]true[/code] the continuous collision detection mode is enabled.
				Continuous collision detection tries to predict where a moving body will collide, instead of moving it and correcting its movement if it collided.

methods.name: body_set_force_integration_callback

methods.name: body_set_max_contacts_reported
methods.description: Sets the maximum contacts to report. Bodies can keep a log of the contacts with other bodies, this is enabled by setting the maximum amount of contacts reported to a number greater than 0.

methods.name: body_set_omit_force_integration

methods.name: body_set_ray_pickable

constants.description:
The strength with which the pinned objects try to stay in positional relation to each other.
			The higher, the stronger.

constants.name: PIN_JOINT_DAMPING

The strength with which the pinned objects try to stay in velocity relation to each other.
			The higher, the stronger.

constants.description: If above 0, this value is the maximum value for an impulse that this Joint puts on it's ends.

constants.name: HINGE_JOINT_BIAS
constants.description: The speed with which the two bodies get pulled together when they move in different directions.

constants.name: HINGE_JOINT_LIMIT_UPPER
constants.description: The maximum rotation across the Hinge.

constants.name: HINGE_JOINT_LIMIT_LOWER
constants.description: The minimum rotation across the Hinge.

constants.name: HINGE_JOINT_LIMIT_RELAXATION
constants.description: The lower this value, the more the rotation gets slowed down.

constants.name: SLIDER_JOINT_LINEAR_LIMIT_UPPER
constants.description: The maximum difference between the pivot points on their x-axis before damping happens.

constants.name: SLIDER_JOINT_LINEAR_LIMIT_LOWER
constants.description: The minimum difference between the pivot points on their x-axis before damping happens.

constants.name: SLIDER_JOINT_LINEAR_LIMIT_SOFTNESS
constants.description: A factor applied to the movement across the slider axis once the limits get surpassed. The lower, the slower the movement.

constants.name: SLIDER_JOINT_LINEAR_LIMIT_RESTITUTION
constants.description: The amount of restitution once the limits are surpassed. The lower, the more velocityenergy gets lost.

constants.description: The amount of damping once the slider limits are surpassed.

constants.name: SLIDER_JOINT_LINEAR_MOTION_SOFTNESS
constants.description: A factor applied to the movement across the slider axis as long as the slider is in the limits. The lower, the slower the movement.

constants.name: SLIDER_JOINT_LINEAR_MOTION_RESTITUTION
constants.description: The amount of restitution inside the slider limits.

constants.name: SLIDER_JOINT_LINEAR_MOTION_DAMPING
constants.description: The amount of damping inside the slider limits.

constants.name: SLIDER_JOINT_LINEAR_ORTHOGONAL_SOFTNESS
constants.description: A factor applied to the movement across axes orthogonal to the slider.

constants.name: SLIDER_JOINT_LINEAR_ORTHOGONAL_RESTITUTION
constants.description: The amount of restitution when movement is across axes orthogonal to the slider.

constants.name: SLIDER_JOINT_LINEAR_ORTHOGONAL_DAMPING
constants.description: The amount of damping when movement is across axes orthogonal to the slider.

constants.description: The lower limit of rotation in the slider.

constants.name: SLIDER_JOINT_ANGULAR_ORTHOGONAL_RESTITUTION

constants.name: CONE_TWIST_JOINT_SWING_SPAN
constants.description:
Swing is rotation from side to side, around the axis perpendicular to the twist axis.
			The swing span defines, how much rotation will not get corrected allong the swing axis.
			Could be defined as looseness in the [ConeTwistJoint].
			If below 0.05, this behaviour is locked. Default value: [code]PI/4[/code].

constants.name: CONE_TWIST_JOINT_TWIST_SPAN
constants.description:
Twist is the rotation around the twist axis, this value defined how far the joint can twist.
			Twist is locked if below 0.05.

constants.name: CONE_TWIST_JOINT_BIAS
constants.description:
The speed with which the swing or twist will take place.
			The higher, the faster.

constants.name: CONE_TWIST_JOINT_SOFTNESS
constants.description: The ease with which the Joint twists, if it's too low, it takes more force to twist the joint.

constants.name: CONE_TWIST_JOINT_RELAXATION
constants.description: Defines, how fast the swing- and twist-speed-difference on both sides gets synced.

constants.name: G6DOF_JOINT_LINEAR_LOWER_LIMIT
constants.description: The minimum difference between the pivot points' axes.

constants.name: G6DOF_JOINT_LINEAR_UPPER_LIMIT
constants.description: The maximum difference between the pivot points' axes.

constants.name: G6DOF_JOINT_LINEAR_LIMIT_SOFTNESS
constants.description: A factor that gets applied to the movement across the axes. The lower, the slower the movement.

constants.name: G6DOF_JOINT_LINEAR_RESTITUTION
constants.description: The amount of restitution on the axes movement. The lower, the more velocity-energy gets lost.

constants.name: G6DOF_JOINT_LINEAR_DAMPING
constants.description: The amount of damping that happens at the linear motion across the axes.

constants.name: G6DOF_JOINT_ANGULAR_LOWER_LIMIT
constants.description: The minimum rotation in negative direction to break loose and rotate around the axes.

constants.name: G6DOF_JOINT_ANGULAR_UPPER_LIMIT
constants.description: The minimum rotation in positive direction to break loose and rotate around the axes.

constants.name: G6DOF_JOINT_ANGULAR_LIMIT_SOFTNESS
constants.description: A factor that gets multiplied onto all rotations across the axes.

constants.name: G6DOF_JOINT_ANGULAR_DAMPING
constants.description: The amount of rotational damping across the axes. The lower, the more dampening occurs.

constants.name: G6DOF_JOINT_ANGULAR_RESTITUTION
constants.description: The amount of rotational restitution across the axes. The lower, the more restitution occurs.

constants.name: G6DOF_JOINT_ANGULAR_FORCE_LIMIT
constants.description: The maximum amount of force that can occur, when rotating around the axes.

constants.name: G6DOF_JOINT_ANGULAR_ERP
constants.description: When correcting the crossing of limits in rotation across the axes, this error tolerance factor defines how much the correction gets slowed down. The lower, the slower.

constants.name: G6DOF_JOINT_ANGULAR_MOTOR_TARGET_VELOCITY
constants.description: Target speed for the motor at the axes.

constants.name: G6DOF_JOINT_ANGULAR_MOTOR_FORCE_LIMIT
constants.description: Maximum acceleration for the motor at the axes.

constants.description: If [code]set[/code] there is linear motion possible within the given limits.

constants.description: If [code]set[/code] there is a rotational motor across these axes.
