constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_DISTANCE_SCALE
constants.description: Constant to set/get the falloff factor for point gravity of an area. The greater this value is, the faster the strength of gravity decreases with the square of distance.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_POINT_ATTENUATION
constants.description: This constant was used to set/get the falloff factor for point gravity. It has been superseded by AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_DISTANCE_SCALE.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_LINEAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get the linear dampening factor of an area.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_ANGULAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get the angular dampening factor of an area.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_PRIORITY
constants.description: Constant to set/get the priority (order of processing) of an area.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_DISABLED
constants.description: This area does not affect gravity/damp. These are generally areas that exist only to detect collisions, and objects entering or exiting them.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_COMBINE
constants.description: This area adds its gravity/damp values to whatever has been calculated so far. This way, many overlapping areas can combine their physics to make interesting effects.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_COMBINE_REPLACE
constants.description: This area adds its gravity/damp values to whatever has been calculated so far. Then stops taking into account the rest of the areas, even the default one.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_REPLACE
constants.description: This area replaces any gravity/damp, even the default one, and stops taking into account the rest of the areas.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_REPLACE_COMBINE
constants.description: This area replaces any gravity/damp calculated so far, but keeps calculating the rest of the areas, down to the default one.

constants.name: BODY_MODE_STATIC
constants.description: Constant for static bodies.

constants.name: BODY_MODE_KINEMATIC
constants.description: Constant for kinematic bodies.

constants.name: BODY_MODE_RIGID
constants.description: Constant for rigid bodies.

constants.name: BODY_MODE_CHARACTER
constants.description: Constant for rigid bodies in character mode. In this mode, a body can not rotate, and only its linear velocity is affected by physics.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_BOUNCE
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's bounce factor.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_FRICTION
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's friction.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_MASS
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's mass.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_GRAVITY_SCALE
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's gravity multiplier.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_LINEAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's linear dampening factor.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_ANGULAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's angular dampening factor.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_MAX
constants.description: This is the last ID for body parameters. Any attempt to set this property is ignored. Any attempt to get it returns 0.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_TRANSFORM
constants.description: Constant to set/get the current transform matrix of the body.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_LINEAR_VELOCITY
constants.description: Constant to set/get the current linear velocity of the body.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_ANGULAR_VELOCITY
constants.description: Constant to set/get the current angular velocity of the body.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_SLEEPING
constants.description: Constant to sleep/wake up a body, or to get whether it is sleeping.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_CAN_SLEEP
constants.description: Constant to set/get whether the body can sleep.

constants.name: AREA_BODY_ADDED
constants.description: The value of the first parameter and area callback function receives, when an object enters one of its shapes.

constants.name: AREA_BODY_REMOVED
constants.description: The value of the first parameter and area callback function receives, when an object exits one of its shapes.

constants.name: INFO_ACTIVE_OBJECTS
constants.description: Constant to get the number of objects that are not sleeping.

constants.name: INFO_COLLISION_PAIRS
constants.description: Constant to get the number of possible collisions.

constants.name: INFO_ISLAND_COUNT
constants.description: Constant to get the number of space regions where a collision could occur.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_CONTACT_RECYCLE_RADIUS
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum distance a pair of bodies has to move before their collision status has to be recalculated.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_CONTACT_MAX_SEPARATION
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum distance a shape can be from another before they are considered separated.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_BODY_MAX_ALLOWED_PENETRATION
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum distance a shape can penetrate another shape before it is considered a collision.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_BODY_LINEAR_VELOCITY_SLEEP_THRESHOLD
constants.description: Constant to set/get the threshold linear velocity of activity. A body marked as potentially inactive for both linear and angular velocity will be put to sleep after the time given.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_BODY_ANGULAR_VELOCITY_SLEEP_THRESHOLD
constants.description: Constant to set/get the threshold angular velocity of activity. A body marked as potentially inactive for both linear and angular velocity will be put to sleep after the time given.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_BODY_TIME_TO_SLEEP
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum time of activity. A body marked as potentially inactive for both linear and angular velocity will be put to sleep after this time.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_CONSTRAINT_DEFAULT_BIAS
constants.description: Constant to set/get the default solver bias for all physics constraints. A solver bias is a factor controlling how much two objects "rebound", after violating a constraint, to avoid leaving them in that state because of numerical imprecision.

Physics2DDirectSpaceState.name: Physics2DDirectSpaceState
Physics2DDirectSpaceState.brief_description: Direct access object to a space in the [Physics2DServer].
Physics2DDirectSpaceState.description: Direct access object to a space in the [Physics2DServer]. It's used mainly to do queries against objects and areas residing in a given space.

methods.name: cast_motion
methods.description:
Checks how far the shape can travel toward a point. Note that both the shape and the motion are supplied through a [Physics2DShapeQueryParameters] object. The method will return an array with two floats between 0 and 1, both representing a fraction of [code]motion[/code]. The first is how far the shape can move without triggering a collision, and the second is the point at which a collision will occur. If no collision is detected, the returned array will be [1, 1].
				If the shape can not move, the array will be empty ([code]dir.empty()==true[/code]).

methods.name: collide_shape
methods.description: Checks the intersections of a shape, given through a [Physics2DShapeQueryParameters] object, against the space. The resulting array contains a list of points where the shape intersects another. Like with [method intersect_shape], the number of returned results can be limited to save processing time.

methods.name: get_rest_info
methods.description:
Checks the intersections of a shape, given through a [Physics2DShapeQueryParameters] object, against the space. If it collides with more than one shape, the nearest one is selected. Note that this method does not take into account the [code]motion[/code] property of the object. The returned object is a dictionary containing the following fields:
				[code]collider_id[/code]: The colliding object's ID.
				[code]linear_velocity[/code]: The colliding object's velocity [Vector2]. If the object is an [Area2D], the result is [code](0, 0)[/code].
				[code]metadata[/code]: The intersecting shape's metadata. This metadata is different from [method Object.get_meta], and is set with [method Physics2DServer.shape_set_data].
				[code]normal[/code]: The object's surface normal at the intersection point.
				[code]point[/code]: The intersection point.
				[code]rid[/code]: The intersecting object's [RID].
				[code]shape[/code]: The shape index of the colliding shape.
				If the shape did not intersect anything, then an empty dictionary ([code]dir.empty()==true[/code]) is returned instead.

methods.name: intersect_point
methods.description:
Checks whether a point is inside any shape. The shapes the point is inside of are returned in an array containing dictionaries with the following fields:
				[code]collider[/code]: The colliding object.
				[code]collider_id[/code]: The colliding object's ID.
				[code]metadata[/code]: The intersecting shape's metadata. This metadata is different from [method Object.get_meta], and is set with [method Physics2DServer.shape_set_data].
				[code]rid[/code]: The intersecting object's [RID].
				[code]shape[/code]: The shape index of the colliding shape.
				Additionally, the method can take an array of objects or [RID]s that are to be excluded from collisions, or a bitmask representing the physics layers to check in.

methods.name: intersect_ray
methods.description:
Intersects a ray in a given space. The returned object is a dictionary with the following fields:
				[code]collider[/code]: The colliding object.
				[code]collider_id[/code]: The colliding object's ID.
				[code]metadata[/code]: The intersecting shape's metadata. This metadata is different from [method Object.get_meta], and is set with [method Physics2DServer.shape_set_data].
				[code]normal[/code]: The object's surface normal at the intersection point.
				[code]position[/code]: The intersection point.
				[code]rid[/code]: The intersecting object's [RID].
				[code]shape[/code]: The shape index of the colliding shape.
				If the ray did not intersect anything, then an empty dictionary ([code]dir.empty()==true[/code]) is returned instead.
				Additionally, the method can take an array of objects or [RID]s that are to be excluded from collisions, or a bitmask representing the physics layers to check in.

methods.name: intersect_shape
methods.description:
Checks the intersections of a shape, given through a [Physics2DShapeQueryParameters] object, against the space. Note that this method does not take into account the [code]motion[/code] property of the object. The intersected shapes are returned in an array containing dictionaries with the following fields:
				[code]collider[/code]: The colliding object.
				[code]collider_id[/code]: The colliding object's ID.
				[code]metadata[/code]: The intersecting shape's metadata. This metadata is different from [method Object.get_meta], and is set with [method Physics2DServer.shape_set_data].
				[code]rid[/code]: The intersecting object's [RID].
				[code]shape[/code]: The shape index of the colliding shape.
				The number of intersections can be limited with the second parameter, to reduce the processing time.

StaticBody.name: StaticBody
StaticBody.description:
Static body for 3D Physics. A static body is a simple body that is not intended to move. They don't consume any CPU resources in contrast to a [RigidBody3D] so they are great for scenario collision.
		A static body can also be animated by using simulated motion mode. This is useful for implementing functionalities such as moving platforms. When this mode is active the body can be animated and automatically computes linear and angular velocity to apply in that frame and to influence other bodies.
		Alternatively, a constant linear or angular velocity can be set for the static body, so even if it doesn't move, it affects other bodies as if it was moving (this is useful for simulating conveyor belts or conveyor wheels).

properties.name: bounce
properties.description: The body bounciness.

properties.name: constant_angular_velocity
properties.description: The constant angular velocity for the body. This does not rotate the body, but affects other bodies that touch it, as if it was in a state of rotation.

properties.name: constant_linear_velocity
properties.description: The constant linear velocity for the body. This does not move the body, but affects other bodies that touch it, as if it was in a state of movement.

properties.name: friction
properties.description: The body friction, from 0 (frictionless) to 1 (full friction).

StreamPeerSSL.name: StreamPeerSSL
StreamPeerSSL.description: SSL Stream peer. This object can be used to connect to SSL servers.

methods.name: connect_to_stream
methods.description: Connect to a peer using an underlying [StreamPeer] "stream", when "validate_certs" is true, [code]StreamPeerSSL[/code] will validate that the certificate presented by the peer matches the "for_hostname".

methods.name: disconnect_from_stream
methods.description: Disconnect from host.

methods.name: get_status
methods.description: Return the status of the connection, one of STATUS_* enum.

constants.name: STATUS_DISCONNECTED
constants.description: A status representing a [code]StreamPeerSSL[/code] that is disconnected.

constants.name: STATUS_CONNECTED
constants.description: A status representing a [code]StreamPeerSSL[/code] that is connected to a host.

constants.name: STATUS_ERROR_NO_CERTIFICATE
constants.description: An errot status that shows the peer did not present a SSL certificate and validation was requested.

constants.name: STATUS_ERROR_HOSTNAME_MISMATCH
constants.description: An error status that shows a mismatch in the SSL certificate domain presented by the host and the domain requested for validation.

ResourceInteractiveLoader.name: ResourceInteractiveLoader
ResourceInteractiveLoader.description: Interactive Resource Loader. This object is returned by ResourceLoader when performing an interactive load. It allows to load with high granularity, so this is mainly useful for displaying load bars/percentages.

methods.name: get_resource
methods.description: Return the loaded resource (only if loaded). Otherwise, returns null.

methods.name: get_stage
methods.description: Return the load stage. The total amount of stages can be queried with [method get_stage_count]

methods.name: get_stage_count
methods.description: Return the total amount of stages (calls to [method poll]) needed to completely load this resource.

methods.name: poll
methods.description: Poll the load. If OK is returned, this means poll will have to be called again. If ERR_FILE_EOF is returned, them the load has finished and the resource can be obtained by calling [method get_resource].

MeshLibrary.name: MeshLibrary
MeshLibrary.description: Library of meshes. Contains a list of [Mesh] resources, each with name and ID. Useful for GridMap or painting Terrain.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear the library.

methods.name: create_item
methods.description: Create a new item in the library, supplied an id.

methods.name: get_item_list
methods.description: Return the list of items.

methods.name: get_item_mesh
methods.description: Return the mesh of the item.

methods.name: get_item_name
methods.description: Return the name of the item.

methods.name: get_last_unused_item_id
methods.description: Get an unused id for a new item.

methods.name: remove_item
methods.description: Remove the item.

methods.name: set_item_mesh
methods.description: Set the mesh of the item.

methods.name: set_item_name
methods.description: Set the name of the item.

Image.name: Image
Image.description: Native image datatype. Contains image data, which can be converted to a [Texture], and several functions to interact with it. The maximum width and height for an [code]Image[/code] is 16384 pixels.

methods.name: blend_rect
methods.description: Alpha-blends [code]src_rect[/code] from [code]src[/code] image to this image at coordinates [code]dest[/code].

methods.name: blend_rect_mask
methods.description: Alpha-blends [code]src_rect[/code] from [code]src[/code] image to this image using [code]mask[/code] image at coordinates [code]dst[/code]. Alpha channels are required for both [code]src[/code] and [code]mask[/code]. [code]dst[/code] pixels and [code]src[/code] pixels will blend if the corresponding mask pixel's alpha value is not 0. [code]src[/code] image and [code]mask[/code] image [b]must[/b] have the same size (width and height) but they can have different formats.

methods.name: blit_rect
methods.description: Copies [code]src_rect[/code] from [code]src[/code] image to this image at coordinates [code]dst[/code].

methods.name: blit_rect_mask
methods.description: Blits [code]src_rect[/code] area from [code]src[/code] image to this image at the coordinates given by [code]dst[/code]. [code]src[/code] pixel is copied onto [code]dst[/code] if the corresponding [code]mask[/code] pixel's alpha value is not 0. [code]src[/code] image and [code]mask[/code] image [b]must[/b] have the same size (width and height) but they can have different formats.

methods.name: clear_mipmaps
methods.description: Removes the image's mipmaps.

methods.name: compress
methods.description: Compresses the image to use less memory. Can not directly access pixel data while the image is compressed. Returns error if the chosen compression mode is not available. See [code]COMPRESS_*[/code] constants.

methods.name: convert
methods.description: Converts the image's format. See [code]FORMAT_*[/code] constants.

methods.name: copy_from
methods.description: Copies [code]src[/code] image to this image.

methods.name: create
methods.description: Creates an empty image of given size and format. See [code]FORMAT_*[/code] constants. If [code]use_mipmaps[/code] is true then generate mipmaps for this image. See the [code]generate_mipmaps[/code] method.

methods.name: create_from_data
methods.description: Creates a new image of given size and format. See [code]FORMAT_*[/code] constants. Fills the image with the given raw data. If [code]use_mipmaps[/code] is true then generate mipmaps for this image. See the [code]generate_mipmaps[/code] method.

methods.name: crop
methods.description: Crops the image to the given [code]width[/code] and [code]height[/code]. If the specified size is larger than the current size, the extra area is filled with black pixels.

methods.name: decompress
methods.description: Decompresses the image if it is compressed. Returns an error if decompress function is not available.

methods.name: detect_alpha
methods.description: Returns ALPHA_BLEND if the image has data for alpha values. Returns ALPHA_BIT if all the alpha values are below a certain threshold or the maximum value. Returns ALPHA_NONE if no data for alpha values is found.

methods.name: expand_x2_hq2x
methods.description: Stretches the image and enlarges it by a factor of 2. No interpolation is done.

methods.name: fill
methods.description: Fills the image with a given [Color].

methods.name: fix_alpha_edges
methods.description: Blends low-alpha pixels with nearby pixels.

methods.name: flip_x
methods.description: Flips the image horizontally.

methods.name: flip_y
methods.description: Flips the image vertically.

methods.name: generate_mipmaps
methods.description: Generates mipmaps for the image. Mipmaps are pre-calculated and lower resolution copies of the image. Mipmaps are automatically used if the image needs to be scaled down when rendered. This improves image quality and the performance of the rendering. Returns an error if the image is compressed, in a custom format or if the image's width/height is 0.

methods.name: get_data
methods.description: Returns the image's raw data.

methods.name: get_format
methods.description: Returns the image's raw data.

methods.name: get_height
methods.description: Returns the image's height.

methods.name: get_mipmap_offset
methods.description: Returns the offset where the image's mipmap with index [code]mipmap[/code] is stored in the [code]data[/code] dictionary.

methods.name: get_pixel
methods.description: Returns the color of the pixel at [code](x, y)[/code] if the image is locked. If the image is unlocked it always returns a [Color] with the value [code](0, 0, 0, 1.0)[/code].

methods.name: get_rect
methods.description: Returns a new image that is a copy of the image's area specified with [code]rect[/code].

methods.name: get_size
methods.description: Returns the image's size (width and height).

methods.name: get_used_rect
methods.description: Returns a [Rect2] enclosing the visible portion of the image.

methods.name: get_width
methods.description: Returns the image's width.

methods.name: has_mipmaps
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the image has generated mipmaps.

methods.name: is_compressed
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the image is compressed.

methods.name: is_empty
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the image has no data.

methods.name: is_invisible
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if all the image's pixels have an alpha value of 0. Returns [code]false[/code] if any pixel has an alpha value higher than 0.

methods.name: load
methods.description: Loads an image from file [code]path[/code].

methods.name: lock
methods.description: Locks the data for writing access.

methods.name: normalmap_to_xy
methods.description: Converts the image's data to represent coordinates on a 3D plane. This is used when the image represents a normalmap. A normalmap can add lots of detail to a 3D surface without increasing the polygon count.

methods.name: premultiply_alpha
methods.description: Multiplies color values with alpha values. Resulting color values for a pixel are [code](color * alpha)/256[/code].

methods.name: resize
methods.description: Resizes the image to the given [code]width[/code] and [code]height[/code]. New pixels are calculated using [code]interpolation[/code]. See [code]interpolation[/code] constants.

methods.name: resize_to_po2
methods.description: Resizes the image to the nearest power of 2 for the width and height. If [code]square[/code] is [code]true[/code] then set width and height to be the same.

methods.name: save_png
methods.description: Saves the image as a PNG file to [code]path[/code].

methods.name: set_pixel
methods.description:
Sets the [Color] of the pixel at [code](x, y)[/code] if the image is locked. Example:
				[codeblock]
				var img = Image.new()
				img.create(img_width, img_height, false, Image.FORMAT_RGBA8)
				img.lock()
				img.set_pixel(x, y, color) # Works
				img.unlock()
				img.set_pixel(x, y, color) # Does not have an effect
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: shrink_x2
methods.description: Shrinks the image by a factor of 2.

methods.name: srgb_to_linear
methods.description: Converts the raw data from the sRGB colorspace to a linear scale.

methods.name: unlock
methods.description: Unlocks the data and prevents changes.

properties.name: data
properties.description: Holds all of the image's color data in a given format. See [code]FORMAT_*[/code] constants.

Physics2DShapeQueryParameters.name: Physics2DShapeQueryParameters
Physics2DShapeQueryParameters.brief_description: Parameters to be sent to a 2D shape physics query.
Physics2DShapeQueryParameters.description: This class contains the shape and other parameters for intersection/collision queries.

methods.name: set_shape
methods.description: Set the [Shape2D] that will be used for collision/intersection queries.

properties.name: collision_layer
properties.description: The physics layer the query should be made on.

properties.name: exclude
properties.description: The list of objects or object [RID]s, that will be excluded from collisions.

properties.name: margin
properties.description: The collision margin for the shape.

properties.name: motion
properties.description: The motion of the shape being queried for.

properties.name: shape_rid
properties.description: The [RID] of the queried shape. See [method set_shape] also.

properties.name: transform
properties.description: the transform matrix of the queried shape.

TextEdit.name: TextEdit
TextEdit.description: TextEdit is meant for editing large, multiline text. It also has facilities for editing code, such as syntax highlighting support and multiple levels of undo/redo.

methods.name: add_color_region
methods.description: Add color region (given the delimiters) and its colors.

methods.name: add_keyword_color
methods.description: Add a keyword and its color.

methods.name: clear_colors
methods.description: Clear all the syntax coloring information.

methods.name: clear_undo_history
methods.description: Clear the undo history.

methods.name: copy
methods.description: Copy the current selection.

methods.name: cursor_get_column
methods.description: Return the column the editing cursor is at.

methods.name: cursor_get_line
methods.description: Return the line the editing cursor is at.

methods.name: cut
methods.description: Cut the current selection.

methods.name: deselect
methods.description: Clears the current selection.

methods.name: get_line
methods.description: Return the text of a specific line.

methods.name: get_line_count
methods.description: Return the amount of total lines in the text.

methods.name: get_selection_from_column
methods.description: Return the selection begin column.

methods.name: get_selection_from_line
methods.description: Return the selection begin line.

methods.name: get_selection_text
methods.description: Return the text inside the selection.

methods.name: get_selection_to_column
methods.description: Return the selection end column.

methods.name: get_selection_to_line
methods.description: Return the selection end line.

methods.name: insert_text_at_cursor
methods.description: Insert a given text at the cursor position.

methods.name: is_selection_active
methods.description: Return true if the selection is active.

methods.name: paste
methods.description: Paste the current selection.

methods.name: redo
methods.description: Perform redo operation.

methods.name: search
methods.description: Perform a search inside the text. Search flags can be specified in the SEARCH_* enum.

methods.name: select
methods.description: Perform selection, from line/column to line/column.

methods.name: select_all
methods.description: Select all the text.

methods.name: toggle_fold_line
methods.description: Toggle the folding of the code block at the given line.

methods.name: undo
methods.description: Perform undo operation.

signals.name: breakpoint_toggled
signals.description: Emitted when a breakpoint is placed via the breakpoint gutter.

signals.name: cursor_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the cursor changes.

signals.name: text_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the text changes.

constants.name: SEARCH_MATCH_CASE
constants.description: Match case when searching.

constants.name: SEARCH_WHOLE_WORDS
constants.description: Match whole words when searching.

constants.name: SEARCH_BACKWARDS
constants.description: Search from end to beginning.

constants.name: MENU_CUT
constants.description: Cuts (Copies and clears) the selected text.

constants.name: MENU_COPY
constants.description: Copies the selected text.

constants.name: MENU_PASTE
constants.description: Pastes the clipboard text over the selected text (or at the cursor's position).

constants.name: MENU_CLEAR
constants.description: Erases the whole [TextEdit] text.

constants.name: MENU_SELECT_ALL
constants.description: Selects the whole [TextEdit] text.

constants.name: MENU_UNDO
constants.description: Undoes the previous action.

properties.name: caret_blink
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the caret (visual cursor) blinks.

properties.name: caret_blink_speed
properties.description: Duration (in seconds) of a caret's blinking cycle.

properties.name: caret_block_mode
properties.description:
If [code]true[/code] the caret displays as a rectangle.
			If [code]false[/code] the caret displays as a bar.

properties.name: caret_moving_by_right_click
properties.description:
If [code]true[/code] a right click moves the cursor at the mouse position before displaying the context menu.
			If [code]false[/code] the context menu disregards mouse location.

properties.name: context_menu_enabled
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] a right click displays the context menu.

properties.name: highlight_current_line
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the line containing the cursor is highlighted.

properties.name: readonly
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] read-only mode is enabled. Existing text cannot be modified and new text cannot be added.

properties.name: show_line_numbers
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] line numbers are displayed to the left of the text.

properties.name: text
properties.description: String value of the [TextEdit].

properties.name: v_scroll_speed
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], enables text wrapping when it goes beyond he edge of what is visible.

EditorFileSystem.name: EditorFileSystem
EditorFileSystem.brief_description: Resource filesystem, as the editor sees it.
EditorFileSystem.description: This object holds information of all resources in the filesystem, their types, etc.

methods.name: get_file_type
methods.description: Get the type of the file, given the full path.

methods.name: get_filesystem
methods.description: Get the root directory object.

methods.name: get_filesystem_path
methods.description: Returns a view into the filesystem at [code]path[/code].

methods.name: get_scanning_progress
methods.description: Return the scan progress for 0 to 1 if the FS is being scanned.

methods.name: is_scanning
methods.description: Return true of the filesystem is being scanned.

methods.name: scan
methods.description: Scan the filesystem for changes.

methods.name: scan_sources
methods.description: Check if the source of any imported resource changed.

methods.name: update_file
methods.description: Update a file information. Call this if an external program (not Godot) modified the file.

signals.name: filesystem_changed
signals.description: Emitted if the filesystem changed.

signals.name: resources_reimported
signals.description: Remitted if a resource is reimported.

signals.name: sources_changed

Curve3D.name: Curve3D
Curve3D.brief_description: Describes a Bezier curve in 3D space.
Curve3D.description:
This class describes a Bezier curve in 3D space. It is mainly used to give a shape to a [Path], but can be manually sampled for other purposes.
		It keeps a cache of precalculated points along the curve, to speed further calculations up.

methods.name: add_point
methods.description:
Adds a point to a curve, at "position", with control points "in" and "out".
				If "at_position" is given, the point is inserted before the point number "at_position", moving that point (and every point after) after the inserted point. If "at_position" is not given, or is an illegal value (at_position <0 or at_position >= [method get_point_count]), the point will be appended at the end of the point list.

methods.name: clear_points
methods.description: Removes all points from the curve.

methods.name: get_baked_length
methods.description: Returns the total length of the curve, based on the cached points. Given enough density (see [method set_bake_interval]), it should be approximate enough.

methods.name: get_baked_points
methods.description: Returns the cache of points as a [PoolVector3Array].

methods.name: get_baked_tilts
methods.description: Returns the cache of tilts as a [RealArray].

methods.name: get_point_count
methods.description: Returns the number of points describing the curve.

methods.name: get_point_in
methods.description: Returns the position of the control point leading to the vertex "idx". If the index is out of bounds, the function sends an error to the console, and returns (0, 0, 0).

methods.name: get_point_out
methods.description: Returns the position of the control point leading out of the vertex "idx". If the index is out of bounds, the function sends an error to the console, and returns (0, 0, 0).

methods.name: get_point_position
methods.description: Returns the position of the vertex "idx". If the index is out of bounds, the function sends an error to the console, and returns (0, 0, 0).

methods.name: get_point_tilt
methods.description: Returns the tilt angle in radians for the point "idx". If the index is out of bounds, the function sends an error to the console, and returns 0.

methods.name: interpolate
methods.description:
Returns the position between the vertex "idx" and the vertex "idx"+1, where "t" controls if the point is the first vertex (t = 0.0), the last vertex (t = 1.0), or in between. Values of "t" outside the range (0.0 >= t  <=1) give strange, but predictable results.
				If "idx" is out of bounds it is truncated to the first or last vertex, and "t" is ignored. If the curve has no points, the function sends an error to the console, and returns (0, 0, 0).

methods.name: interpolate_baked
methods.description:
Returns a point within the curve at position "offset", where "offset" is measured as a distance in 3D units along the curve.
				To do that, it finds the two cached points where the "offset" lies between, then interpolates the values. This interpolation is cubic if "cubic" is set to true, or linear if set to false.
				Cubic interpolation tends to follow the curves better, but linear is faster (and often, precise enough).

methods.name: interpolatef
methods.description: Returns the position at the vertex "fofs". It calls [method interpolate] using the integer part of fofs as "idx", and its fractional part as "t".

methods.name: remove_point
methods.description: Deletes the point "idx" from the curve. Sends an error to the console if "idx" is out of bounds.

methods.name: set_point_in
methods.description: Sets the position of the control point leading to the vertex "idx". If the index is out of bounds, the function sends an error to the console.

methods.name: set_point_out
methods.description: Sets the position of the control point leading out of the vertex "idx". If the index is out of bounds, the function sends an error to the console.

methods.name: set_point_position
methods.description: Sets the position for the vertex "idx". If the index is out of bounds, the function sends an error to the console.

methods.name: set_point_tilt
methods.description:
Sets the tilt angle in radians for the point "idx". If the index is out of bounds, the function sends an error to the console.
				The tilt controls the rotation along the look-at axis an object traveling the path would have. In the case of a curve controlling a [PathFollow], this tilt is an offset over the natural tilt the PathFollow calculates.

methods.name: tessellate
methods.description:
Returns a list of points along the curve, with a curvature controlled point density. That is, the curvier parts will have more points than the straighter parts.
				This approximation makes straight segments between each point, then subdivides those segments until the resulting shape is similar enough.
				"max_stages" controls how many subdivisions a curve segment may face before it is considered approximate enough. Each subdivision splits the segment in half, so the default 5 stages may mean up to 32 subdivisions per curve segment. Increase with care!
				"tolerance_degrees" controls how many degrees the midpoint of a segment may deviate from the real curve, before the segment has to be subdivided.

properties.name: bake_interval
properties.description: The distance in meters between two adjacent cached points. Changing it forces the cache to be recomputed the next time the [method get_baked_points] or [method get_baked_length] function is called. The smaller the distance, the more points in the cache and the more memory it will consume, so use with care.

PathFollow.name: PathFollow
PathFollow.description:
This node takes its parent [Path], and returns the coordinates of a point within it, given a distance from the first vertex.
		It is useful for making other nodes follow a path, without coding the movement pattern. For that, the nodes must be descendants of this node. Then, when setting an offset in this node, the descendant nodes will move accordingly.

constants.name: ROTATION_NONE
constants.description: Forbids the PathFollow to rotate.

constants.name: ROTATION_Y
constants.description: Allows the PathFollow to rotate in the Y axis only.

constants.name: ROTATION_XY
constants.description: Allows the PathFollow to rotate in both the X, and Y axes.

constants.name: ROTATION_XYZ
constants.description: Allows the PathFollow to rotate in any axis.

properties.name: cubic_interp
properties.description:
If [code]true[/code] the position between two cached points is interpolated cubically, and linearly otherwise.
			The points along the [Curve3D] of the [Path] are precomputed before use, for faster calculations. The point at the requested offset is then calculated interpolating between two adjacent cached points. This may present a problem if the curve makes sharp turns, as the cached points may not follow the curve closely enough.
			There are two answers to this problem: Either increase the number of cached points and increase memory consumption, or make a cubic interpolation between two points at the cost of (slightly) slower calculations.

properties.name: h_offset
properties.description: The node's offset along the curve.

properties.name: loop
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], any offset outside the path's length will wrap around, instead of stopping at the ends. Use it for cyclic paths.

properties.name: offset
properties.description: The distance from the first vertex, measured in 3D units along the path. This sets this node's position to a point within the path.

properties.name: rotation_mode
properties.description: Allows or forbids rotation on one or more axes, depending on the constants being used.

properties.name: unit_offset
properties.description: The distance from the first vertex, considering 0.0 as the first vertex and 1.0 as the last. This is just another way of expressing the offset within the path, as the offset supplied is multiplied internally by the path's length.

properties.name: v_offset
properties.description: The node's offset perpendicular to the curve.

Curve.name: Curve
Curve.description: A curve that can be saved and re-used for other objects. By default it ranges between [code]0[/code] and [code]1[/code] on the y-axis and positions points relative to the [code]0.5[/code] y-position.

methods.name: add_point
methods.description: Adds a point to the curve. For each side, if the [code]*_mode[/code] is [code]TANGENT_LINEAR[/code], the [code]*_tangent[/code] angle (in degrees) uses the slope of the curve halfway to the adjacent point. Allows custom assignments to the [code]*_tangent[/code] angle if [code]*_mode[/code] is set to [code]TANGENT_FREE[/code].

methods.name: bake
methods.description: Recomputes the baked cache of points for the curve.

methods.name: clean_dupes
methods.description: Removes points that are closer than [code]CMP_EPSILON[/code] (0.00001) units to their neighbor on the curve.

methods.name: clear_points
methods.description: Removes all points from the curve.

methods.name: get_point_left_mode
methods.description: Returns the left [code]TangentMode[/code] for the point at [code]index[/code].

methods.name: get_point_left_tangent
methods.description: Returns the left tangent angle (in degrees) for the point at [code]index[/code].

methods.name: get_point_position
methods.description: Returns the curve coordinates for the point at [code]index[/code].

methods.name: get_point_right_mode
methods.description: Returns the right [code]TangentMode[/code] for the point at [code]index[/code].

methods.name: get_point_right_tangent
methods.description: Returns the right tangent angle (in degrees) for the point at [code]index[/code].

methods.name: interpolate
methods.description: Returns the y value for the point that would exist at x-position [code]offset[/code] along the curve.

methods.name: interpolate_baked
methods.description: Returns the y value for the point that would exist at x-position [code]offset[/code] along the curve using the baked cache. Bakes the curve's points if not already baked.

methods.name: remove_point
methods.description: Removes the point at [code]index[/code] from the curve.

methods.name: set_point_left_mode
methods.description: Sets the left [code]TangentMode[/code] for the point at [code]index[/code] to [code]mode[/code].

methods.name: set_point_left_tangent
methods.description: Sets the left tangent angle for the point at [code]index[/code] to [code]tangent[/code].

methods.name: set_point_offset
methods.description: Sets the offset from [code]0.5[/code]

methods.name: set_point_right_mode
methods.description: Sets the right [code]TangentMode[/code] for the point at [code]index[/code] to [code]mode[/code].

methods.name: set_point_right_tangent
methods.description: Sets the right tangent angle for the point at [code]index[/code] to [code]tangent[/code].

methods.name: set_point_value
methods.description: Assigns the vertical position [code]y[/code] to the point at [code]index[/code].

signals.name: range_changed
signals.description: Emitted when [member max_value] or [member min_value] is changed.

constants.name: TANGENT_FREE
constants.description: The tangent on this side of the point is user-defined.

constants.name: TANGENT_LINEAR
constants.description: The curve calculates the tangent on this side of the point as the slope halfway towards the adjacent point.

constants.name: TANGENT_MODE_COUNT
constants.description: The total number of available tangent modes.

properties.name: bake_resolution
properties.description: The number of points to include in the baked (i.e. cached) curve data.

properties.name: max_value
properties.description: The maximum value the curve can reach. Default value: [code]1[/code].

properties.name: min_value
properties.description: The minimum value the curve can reach. Default value: [code]0[/code].

SurfaceTool.name: SurfaceTool
SurfaceTool.description:
The [code]SurfaceTool[/code] is used to construct a [Mesh] by specifying vertex attributes individually. It can be used to construct a [Mesh] from script. All properties except index need to be added before a call to [method add_vertex]. For example adding vertex colors and UVs looks like
		[codeblock]
		var st = SurfaceTool.new()
		st.begin(Mesh.PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLES)
		st.add_color(Color(1, 0, 0))
		st.add_uv(Vector2(0, 0))
		st.add_vertex(Vector3(0, 0, 0))
		[/codeblock]
		The [code]SurfaceTool[/code] now contains one vertex of a triangle which has a UV coordinate and a specified [Color]. If another vertex were added without calls to [method add_uv] or [method add_color] then the last values would be used.
		It is very important that vertex attributes are passed [b]before[/b] the call to [method add_vertex], failure to do this will result in an error when committing the vertex information to a mesh.

methods.name: add_bones
methods.description: Add an array of bones for the next Vertex to use.

methods.name: add_color
methods.description: Specify a [Color] for the next Vertex to use.

methods.name: add_index
methods.description: Adds an index to index array if you are using indexed Vertices. Does not need to be called before adding Vertex.

methods.name: add_normal
methods.description: Specify a normal for the next Vertex to use.

methods.name: add_smooth_group
methods.description: Specify whether current Vertex (if using only Vertex arrays) or current index (if also using index arrays) should utilize smooth normals for normal calculation.

methods.name: add_tangent
methods.description: Specify a Tangent for the next Vertex to use.

methods.name: add_triangle_fan
methods.description: Insert a triangle fan made of array data into [Mesh] being constructed.

methods.name: add_uv
methods.description: Specify UV Coordinate for next Vertex to use.

methods.name: add_uv2
methods.description: Specify an optional second set of UV coordinates for next Vertex to use.

methods.name: add_vertex
methods.description: Specify position of current Vertex. Should be called after specifying other vertex properties (e.g. Color, UV).

methods.name: add_weights
methods.description: Specify weight value for next Vertex to use.

methods.name: begin
methods.description: Called before adding any Vertices. Takes the primitive type as an argument (e.g. Mesh.PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLES).

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear all information passed into the surface tool so far.

methods.name: commit
methods.description: Returns a constructed [ArrayMesh] from current information passed in. If an existing [ArrayMesh] is passed in as an argument, will add an extra surface to the existing [ArrayMesh].

methods.name: deindex
methods.description: Removes index array by expanding Vertex array.

methods.name: generate_normals
methods.description: Generates normals from Vertices so you do not have to do it manually.

methods.name: index
methods.description: Shrinks Vertex array by creating an index array. Avoids reusing Vertices.

methods.name: set_material
methods.description: Sets [Material] to be used by the [Mesh] you are constructing.

Performance.name: Performance
Performance.description:
This class provides access to a number of different monitors related to performance, such as memory usage, draw calls, and FPS. These are the same as the values displayed in the [i]Monitor[/i] tab in the editor's [i]Debugger[/i] panel. By using the [method get_monitor] method of this class, you can access this data from your code. Note that a few of these monitors are only available in debug mode and will always return 0 when used in a release build.
		Many of these monitors are not updated in real-time, so there may be a short delay between changes.

methods.name: get_monitor
methods.description:
Returns the value of one of the available monitors. You should provide one of this class's constants as the argument, like this:
				[codeblock]
				print(Performance.get_monitor(Performance.TIME_FPS)) # Prints the FPS to the console
				[/codeblock]

constants.name: TIME_FPS
constants.description: Frames per second.

constants.name: TIME_PROCESS
constants.description: Time it took to complete one frame.

constants.name: TIME_PHYSICS_PROCESS
constants.description: Time it took to complete one physics frame.

constants.name: MEMORY_STATIC
constants.description: Static memory currently used, in bytes. Not available in release builds.

constants.name: MEMORY_DYNAMIC
constants.description: Dynamic memory currently used, in bytes. Not available in release builds.

constants.name: MEMORY_STATIC_MAX
constants.description: Available static memory. Not available in release builds.

constants.name: MEMORY_DYNAMIC_MAX
constants.description: Available dynamic memory. Not available in release builds.

constants.name: MEMORY_MESSAGE_BUFFER_MAX
constants.description: Largest amount of memory the message queue buffer has used, in bytes. The message queue is used for deferred functions calls and notifications.

constants.name: OBJECT_COUNT
constants.description: Number of objects currently instanced (including nodes).

constants.name: OBJECT_RESOURCE_COUNT
constants.description: Number of resources currently used.

constants.name: OBJECT_NODE_COUNT
constants.description: Number of nodes currently instanced. This also includes the root node, as well as any nodes not in the scene tree.

constants.name: RENDER_OBJECTS_IN_FRAME
constants.description: 3D objects drawn per frame.

constants.name: RENDER_VERTICES_IN_FRAME
constants.description: Vertices drawn per frame. 3D only.

constants.name: RENDER_MATERIAL_CHANGES_IN_FRAME
constants.description: Material changes per frame. 3D only

constants.name: RENDER_SHADER_CHANGES_IN_FRAME
constants.description: Shader changes per frame. 3D only.

constants.name: RENDER_SURFACE_CHANGES_IN_FRAME
constants.description: Render surface changes per frame. 3D only.

constants.name: RENDER_DRAW_CALLS_IN_FRAME
constants.description: Draw calls per frame. 3D only.

constants.name: RENDER_VIDEO_MEM_USED
constants.description: Video memory used. Includes both texture and vertex memory.

constants.name: RENDER_TEXTURE_MEM_USED
constants.description: Texture memory used.

constants.name: RENDER_VERTEX_MEM_USED
constants.description: Vertex memory used.

constants.name: PHYSICS_2D_ACTIVE_OBJECTS
constants.description: Number of active [RigidBody2D] nodes in the game.

constants.name: PHYSICS_2D_COLLISION_PAIRS
constants.description: Number of collision pairs in the 2D physics engine.

constants.name: PHYSICS_2D_ISLAND_COUNT
constants.description: Number of islands in the 2D physics engine.

constants.name: PHYSICS_3D_ACTIVE_OBJECTS
constants.description: Number of active [RigidBody] and [VehicleBody] nodes in the game.

constants.name: PHYSICS_3D_COLLISION_PAIRS
constants.description: Number of collision pairs in the 3D physics engine.

constants.name: PHYSICS_3D_ISLAND_COUNT
constants.description: Number of islands in the 3D physics engine.

ConcavePolygonShape.name: ConcavePolygonShape
ConcavePolygonShape.description: Concave polygon shape resource, which can be set into a [PhysicsBody] or area. This shape is created by feeding a list of triangles.

methods.name: get_faces
methods.description: Return the faces (an array of triangles).

methods.name: set_faces
methods.description: Set the faces (an array of triangles).

Line2D.name: Line2D
Line2D.description: A line through several points in 2D space.

methods.name: add_point
methods.description: Add a point at the [code]position[/code]. Appends the point at the end of the line.

methods.name: get_point_count
methods.description: Returns the Line2D's amount of points.

methods.name: get_point_position
methods.description: Returns point [code]i[/code]'s position.

methods.name: remove_point
methods.description: Remove the point at index [code]i[/code] from the line.

methods.name: set_point_position
methods.description: Overwites the position in point [code]i[/code] with the supplied [code]position[/code].

constants.name: LINE_JOINT_SHARP
constants.description: The line's joints will be pointy. If [code]sharp_limit[/code] is greater than the rotation of a joint, it becomes a bevel joint instead.

constants.name: LINE_JOINT_BEVEL
constants.description: The line's joints will be bevelled/chamfered.

constants.name: LINE_JOINT_ROUND
constants.description: The line's joints will be rounded.

constants.name: LINE_CAP_NONE
constants.description: Don't have a line cap.

constants.name: LINE_CAP_BOX
constants.description: Draws the line cap as a box.

constants.name: LINE_CAP_ROUND
constants.description: Draws the line cap as a circle.

constants.name: LINE_TEXTURE_NONE
constants.description: Takes the left pixels of the texture and renders it over the whole line.

constants.name: LINE_TEXTURE_TILE
constants.description: Tiles the texture over the line. The texture need to be imported with Repeat Enabled for it to work properly.

properties.name: begin_cap_mode
properties.description: Controls the style of the line's first point. Use [code]LINE_CAP_*[/code] constants. Default value: [code]LINE_CAP_NONE[/code].

properties.name: default_color
properties.description: The line's color. Will not be used if a gradient is set.

properties.name: end_cap_mode
properties.description: Controls the style of the line's last point. Use [code]LINE_CAP_*[/code] constants. Default value: [code]LINE_CAP_NONE[/code].

properties.name: gradient
properties.description: The gradient is drawn through the whole line from start to finish. The default color will not be used if a gradient is set.

properties.name: joint_mode
properties.description: The style for the points between the start and the end.

properties.name: points
properties.description: The points that form the lines. The line is drawn between every point set in this array.

properties.name: round_precision
properties.description: The smoothness of the rounded joints and caps. This is only used if a cap or joint is set as round.

properties.name: sharp_limit
properties.description: The direction difference in radians between vector points. This value is only used if [code]joint mode[/code] is set to [code]LINE_JOINT_SHARP[/code].

properties.name: texture
properties.description: The texture used for the line's texture. Uses [code]texture_mode[/code] for drawing style.

properties.name: texture_mode
properties.description: The style to render the [code]texture[/code] on the line. Use [code]LINE_TEXTURE_*[/code] constants. Default value: [code]LINE_TEXTURE_NONE[/code].

properties.name: width
properties.description: The line's width.

LightOccluder2D.name: LightOccluder2D
LightOccluder2D.brief_description: Occludes light cast by a Light2D, casting shadows.
LightOccluder2D.description: Occludes light cast by a Light2D, casting shadows. The LightOccluder2D must be provided with an [OccluderPolygon2D] in order for the shadow to be computed.

properties.name: light_mask
properties.description: The LightOccluder2D's light mask. The LightOccluder2D will cast shadows only from Light2D(s) that have the same light mask(s).

properties.name: occluder
properties.description: The [OccluderPolygon2D] used to compute the shadow.

AudioEffectPanner.name: AudioEffectPanner
AudioEffectPanner.brief_description: Adds a Panner audio effect to an Audio bus. Pans sound left or right.
AudioEffectPanner.description: Determines how much of an audio signal is sent to the left and right buses.

properties.name: pan
properties.description: Pan position. Value can range from -1 (fully left) to 1 (fully right).

AudioEffectEQ10.name: AudioEffectEQ10
AudioEffectEQ10.brief_description:
Adds a 10-band equalizer audio effect to an Audio bus. Gives you control over frequencies from 31 Hz to 16000 Hz.
		Each frequency can be modulated between -60/+24 dB.
AudioEffectEQ10.description:
Frequency bands :
		Band 1 : 31 Hz
		Band 2 : 62 Hz
		Band 3 : 125 Hz
		Band 4 : 250 Hz
		Band 5 : 500 Hz
		Band 6 : 1000 Hz
		Band 7 : 2000 Hz
		Band 8 : 4000 Hz
		Band 9 : 8000 Hz
		Band 10 : 16000 Hz

		See also [AudioEffectEQ], [AudioEffectEQ6], [AudioEffectEQ21].

CheckBox.name: CheckBox
CheckBox.description: A checkbox allows the user to make a binary choice (choosing only one of two possible options), for example Answer 'yes' or 'no'.

ImmediateGeometry.name: ImmediateGeometry
ImmediateGeometry.description: Draws simple geometry from code. Uses a drawing mode similar to OpenGL 1.x.

methods.name: add_sphere
methods.description: Simple helper to draw a uvsphere, with given latitudes, longitude and radius.

methods.name: add_vertex
methods.description: Adds a vertex with the currently set color/uv/etc.

methods.name: begin
methods.description:
Begin drawing (And optionally pass a texture override). When done call end(). For more information on how this works, search for glBegin() glEnd() references.
			For the type of primitive, use the [Mesh].PRIMITIVE_* enumerations.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clears everything that was drawn using begin/end.

methods.name: end
methods.description: Ends a drawing context and displays the results.

methods.name: set_color
methods.description: The current drawing color.

methods.name: set_normal
methods.description: The next vertex's normal.

methods.name: set_tangent
methods.description: The next vertex's tangent (and binormal facing).

methods.name: set_uv

methods.name: set_uv2
methods.description: The next vertex's second layer UV.

WorldEnvironment.name: WorldEnvironment
WorldEnvironment.brief_description: Default environment properties for the entire scene (post-processing effects, lightning and background settings).
WorldEnvironment.description:
The [code]WorldEnvironment[/code] node is used to configure the default [Environment] for the scene.
		The parameters defined in the [code]WorldEnvironment[/code] can be overridden by an [Environment] node set on the current [Camera]. Additionally, only one [code]WorldEnvironment[/code] may be instanced in a given scene at a time.
		The [code]WorldEnvironment[/code] allows the user to specify default lighting parameters (e.g. ambient lighting), various post-processing effects (e.g. SSAO, DOF, Tonemapping), and how to draw the background (e.g. solid color, skybox). Usually, these are added in order to improve the realism/color balance of the scene.

properties.name: environment
properties.description: The [Environment] resource used by this [code]WorldEnvironment[/code], defining the default properties.

QuadMesh.name: QuadMesh
QuadMesh.description: Class representing a square mesh with size (2,2,0). Consider using a [PlaneMesh] if you require a differently sized plane.

Curve2D.name: Curve2D
Curve2D.brief_description: Describes a Bezier curve in 2D space.
Curve2D.description:
This class describes a Bezier curve in 2D space. It is mainly used to give a shape to a [Path2D], but can be manually sampled for other purposes.
		It keeps a cache of precalculated points along the curve, to speed further calculations up.

methods.name: add_point
methods.description:
Adds a point to a curve, at "position", with control points "in" and "out".
				If "at_position" is given, the point is inserted before the point number "at_position", moving that point (and every point after) after the inserted point. If "at_position" is not given, or is an illegal value (at_position <0 or at_position >= [method get_point_count]), the point will be appended at the end of the point list.

methods.name: clear_points
methods.description: Removes all points from the curve.

methods.name: get_baked_length
methods.description: Returns the total length of the curve, based on the cached points. Given enough density (see [method set_bake_interval]), it should be approximate enough.

methods.name: get_baked_points
methods.description: Returns the cache of points as a [PoolVector2Array].

methods.name: get_point_count
methods.description: Returns the number of points describing the curve.

methods.name: get_point_in
methods.description: Returns the position of the control point leading to the vertex "idx". If the index is out of bounds, the function sends an error to the console, and returns (0, 0).

methods.name: get_point_out
methods.description: Returns the position of the control point leading out of the vertex "idx". If the index is out of bounds, the function sends an error to the console, and returns (0, 0).

methods.name: get_point_position
methods.description: Returns the position of the vertex "idx". If the index is out of bounds, the function sends an error to the console, and returns (0, 0).

methods.name: interpolate
methods.description:
Returns the position between the vertex "idx" and the vertex "idx"+1, where "t" controls if the point is the first vertex (t = 0.0), the last vertex (t = 1.0), or in between. Values of "t" outside the range (0.0 >= t  <=1) give strange, but predictable results.
				If "idx" is out of bounds it is truncated to the first or last vertex, and "t" is ignored. If the curve has no points, the function sends an error to the console, and returns (0, 0).

methods.name: interpolate_baked
methods.description:
Returns a point within the curve at position "offset", where "offset" is measured as a pixel distance along the curve.
				To do that, it finds the two cached points where the "offset" lies between, then interpolates the values. This interpolation is cubic if "cubic" is set to true, or linear if set to false.
				Cubic interpolation tends to follow the curves better, but linear is faster (and often, precise enough).

methods.name: interpolatef
methods.description: Returns the position at the vertex "fofs". It calls [method interpolate] using the integer part of fofs as "idx", and its fractional part as "t".

methods.name: remove_point
methods.description: Deletes the point "idx" from the curve. Sends an error to the console if "idx" is out of bounds.

methods.name: set_point_in
methods.description: Sets the position of the control point leading to the vertex "idx". If the index is out of bounds, the function sends an error to the console.

methods.name: set_point_out
methods.description: Sets the position of the control point leading out of the vertex "idx". If the index is out of bounds, the function sends an error to the console.

methods.name: set_point_position
methods.description: Sets the position for the vertex "idx". If the index is out of bounds, the function sends an error to the console.

methods.name: tessellate
methods.description:
Returns a list of points along the curve, with a curvature controlled point density. That is, the curvier parts will have more points than the straighter parts.
				This approximation makes straight segments between each point, then subdivides those segments until the resulting shape is similar enough.
				"max_stages" controls how many subdivisions a curve segment may face before it is considered approximate enough. Each subdivision splits the segment in half, so the default 5 stages may mean up to 32 subdivisions per curve segment. Increase with care!
				"tolerance_degrees" controls how many degrees the midpoint of a segment may deviate from the real curve, before the segment has to be subdivided.

properties.name: bake_interval
properties.description: The distance in pixels between two adjacent cached points. Changing it forces the cache to be recomputed the next time the [method get_baked_points] or [method get_baked_length] function is called. The smaller the distance, the more points in the cache and the more memory it will consume, so use with care.

FileDialog.name: FileDialog
FileDialog.brief_description: Dialog for selecting files or directories in the filesystem.
FileDialog.description: FileDialog is a preset dialog used to choose files and directories in the filesystem. It supports filter masks.

methods.name: add_filter
methods.description: Add a custom filter. Filter format is: "mask ; description", example (C++): dialog->add_filter("*.png ; PNG Images");

methods.name: clear_filters
methods.description: Clear all the added filters in the dialog.

methods.name: get_vbox
methods.description: Return the vertical box container of the dialog, custom controls can be added to it.

methods.name: invalidate
methods.description: Invalidate and update the current dialog content list.

signals.name: dir_selected
signals.description: Event emitted when the user selects a directory.

signals.name: file_selected
signals.description: Event emitted when the user selects a file (double clicks it or presses the OK button).

signals.name: files_selected
signals.description: Event emitted when the user selects multiple files.

constants.name: MODE_OPEN_FILE
constants.description: The dialog allows the selection of one, and only one file.

constants.name: MODE_OPEN_FILES
constants.description: The dialog allows the selection of multiple files.

constants.name: MODE_OPEN_DIR
