ARVROrigin.name: ARVROrigin
ARVROrigin.description:
This is a special node within the AR/VR system that maps the physical location of the center of our tracking space to the virtual location within our game world.
		There should be only one of these nodes in your scene and you must have one. All the ARVRCamera, ARVRController and ARVRAnchor nodes should be direct children of this node for spatial tracking to work correctly.
		It is the position of this node that you update when you're character needs to move through your game world while we're not moving in the real world. Movement in the real world is always in relation to this origin point.
		So say that your character is driving a car, the ARVROrigin node should be a child node of this car. If you implement a teleport system to move your character, you change the position of this node. Etc.

properties.name: world_scale
properties.description:
Allows you to adjust the scale to your game's units. Most AR/VR platforms assume a scale of 1 game world unit = 1 meter in the real world.
			Note that this method is a passthrough to the [ARVRServer] itself.

JSONParseResult.name: JSONParseResult
JSONParseResult.brief_description: Data class wrapper for decoded JSON.
JSONParseResult.description: Returned by [method JSON.parse], [code]JSONParseResult[/code] contains decoded JSON or error information if JSON source not successfully parsed. You can check if JSON source was successfully parsed with [code]if json_result.error == 0[/code].

properties.name: error
properties.description: The error type if JSON source was not successfully parsed. See [@GlobalScope] ERR_* constants.

properties.name: error_line
properties.description: The line number where the error occurred if JSON source was not successfully parsed.

properties.name: error_string
properties.description: The error message if JSON source was not successfully parsed. See [@GlobalScope] ERR_* constants.

properties.name: result
properties.description:
A [Variant] containing the parsed JSON. Use typeof() to check if it is what you expect. For example, if JSON source starts with curly braces ([code]{}[/code]) a [Dictionary] will be returned, if JSON source starts with braces ([code][][/code]) an [Array] will be returned.
			[i]Be aware that the JSON specification does not define integer or float types, but only a number type. Therefore, parsing a JSON text will convert all numerical values to float types.[/i]
			[codeblock]
			p = JSON.parse('["hello", "world", "!"]')
			if typeof(p) == TYPE_ARRAY:
			    print(p[0]) # prints 'hello'
			else:
			    print("unexpected results")
			[/codeblock]

SegmentShape2D.name: SegmentShape2D
SegmentShape2D.description: Segment shape for 2D collisions. Consists of two points, [code]a[/code] and [code]b[/code].

properties.name: a
properties.description: The segment's first point position.

properties.name: b
properties.description: The segment's second point position.

PhysicsBody.name: PhysicsBody
PhysicsBody.brief_description: Base class for all objects affected by physics in 3D space.
PhysicsBody.description: PhysicsBody is an abstract base class for implementing a physics body. All *Body types inherit from it.

methods.name: add_collision_exception_with
methods.description: Adds a body to the list of bodies that this body can't collide with.

methods.name: remove_collision_exception_with
methods.description: Removes a body from the list of bodies that this body can't collide with.

properties.name: collision_layer
properties.description:
The physics layers this area is in.
			Collidable objects can exist in any of 32 different layers. These layers work like a tagging system, and are not visual. A collidable can use these layers to select with which objects it can collide, using the collision_mask property.
			A contact is detected if object A is in any of the layers that object B scans, or object B is in any layer scanned by object A.

properties.name: collision_mask
properties.description: The physics layers this area can scan for collisions.

Camera.name: Camera
Camera.brief_description: Camera node, displays from a point of view.
Camera.description: Camera is a special node that displays what is visible from its current location. Cameras register themselves in the nearest [Viewport] node (when ascending the tree). Only one camera can be active per viewport. If no viewport is available ascending the tree, the Camera will register in the global viewport. In other words, a Camera just provides [i]3D[/i] display capabilities to a [Viewport], and, without one, a scene registered in that [Viewport] (or higher viewports) can't be displayed.

methods.name: clear_current
methods.description: If this is the current Camera, remove it from being current. If it is inside the node tree, request to make the next Camera current, if any.

methods.name: get_camera_transform
methods.description: Get the camera transform. Subclassed cameras (such as CharacterCamera) may provide different transforms than the [Node] transform.

methods.name: is_position_behind
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the given position is behind the Camera.

methods.name: make_current
methods.description: Make this camera the current Camera for the [Viewport] (see class description). If the Camera Node is outside the scene tree, it will attempt to become current once it's added.

methods.name: project_local_ray_normal
methods.description: Returns a normal vector from the screen point location directed along the camera. Orthogonal cameras are normalized. Perspective cameras account for perspective, screen width/height, etc.

methods.name: project_position
methods.description: Returns how a 2D coordinate in the Viewport rectangle maps to a 3D point in worldspace.

methods.name: project_ray_normal
methods.description: Returns a normal vector in worldspace, that is the result of projecting a point on the [Viewport] rectangle by the camera projection. This is useful for casting rays in the form of (origin, normal) for object intersection or picking.

methods.name: project_ray_origin
methods.description: Returns a 3D position in worldspace, that is the result of projecting a point on the [Viewport] rectangle by the camera projection. This is useful for casting rays in the form of (origin, normal) for object intersection or picking.

methods.name: set_orthogonal
methods.description: Set the camera projection to orthogonal mode, by specifying a width and the [i]near[/i] and [i]far[/i] clip planes in worldspace units. (As a hint, 2D games often use this projection, with values specified in pixels)

methods.name: set_perspective
methods.description: Set the camera projection to perspective mode, by specifying a [i]FOV[/i] Y angle in degrees (FOV means Field of View), and the [i]near[/i] and [i]far[/i] clip planes in worldspace units.

methods.name: unproject_position
methods.description: Returns how a 3D point in worldspace maps to a 2D coordinate in the [Viewport] rectangle.

constants.name: PROJECTION_PERSPECTIVE
constants.description: Perspective Projection (object's size on the screen becomes smaller when far away).

constants.name: PROJECTION_ORTHOGONAL
constants.description: Orthogonal Projection (objects remain the same size on the screen no matter how far away they are).

constants.name: KEEP_WIDTH
constants.description: Preserves the horizontal aspect ratio.

constants.name: KEEP_HEIGHT
constants.description: Preserves the vertical aspect ratio.

constants.name: DOPPLER_TRACKING_DISABLED
constants.description: Disable Doppler effect simulation (default).

constants.name: DOPPLER_TRACKING_IDLE_STEP
constants.description: Simulate Doppler effect by tracking positions of objects that are changed in [code]_process[/code]. Changes in the relative velocity of this Camera compared to those objects affect how Audio is perceived (changing the Audio's [code]pitch shift[/code]).

constants.name: DOPPLER_TRACKING_PHYSICS_STEP
constants.description: Simulate Doppler effect by tracking positions of objects that are changed in [code]_physics_process[/code]. Changes in the relative velocity of this Camera compared to those objects affect how Audio is perceived (changing the Audio's [code]pitch shift[/code]).

properties.name: cull_mask
properties.description: The culling mask that describes which 3D render layers are rendered by this camera.

properties.name: current
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the ancestor [Viewport] is currently using this Camera. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: doppler_tracking
properties.description: If not [code]DOPPLER_TRACKING_DISABLED[/code] this Camera will simulate the Doppler effect for objects changed in particular [code]_process[/code] methods. Default value: [code]DOPPLER_TRACKING_DISABLED[/code].

properties.name: environment
properties.description: Set the [Environment] to use for this Camera.

properties.name: far
properties.description: The distance to the far culling boundary for this Camera relative to its local z-axis.

properties.name: fov
properties.description: The camera's field of view angle (in degrees). Only applicable in perspective mode. Since [member keep_aspect] locks one axis, [code]fov[/code] sets the other axis' field of view angle.

properties.name: h_offset
properties.description: The horizontal (X) offset of the Camear viewport.

properties.name: keep_aspect
properties.description: The axis to lock during [member fov]/[member size] adjustments.

properties.name: near
properties.description: The distance to the near culling boundary for this Camera relative to its local z-axis.

properties.name: projection
properties.description: The camera's projection mode. In [code]PROJECTION_PERSPECTIVE[/code] mode, objects' z-distance from the camera's local space scales their perceived size.

properties.name: size
properties.description: The camera's size measured as 1/2 the width or height. Only applicable in orthogonal mode. Since [member keep_aspect] locks on axis, [code]size[/code] sets the other axis' size length.

properties.name: v_offset
properties.description: The horizontal (Y) offset of the Camear viewport.

VisualScriptVariableSet.name: VisualScriptVariableSet
VisualScriptVariableSet.description:
Changes a variable's value to the given input.
		[b]Input Ports:[/b]
		- Sequence
		- Data (variant): [code]set[/code]
		[b]Output Ports:[/b]
		- Sequence

properties.name: var_name
properties.description: The variable's name.

TextureButton.name: TextureButton
TextureButton.brief_description: Texture-based button. Supports Pressed, Hover, Disabled and Focused states.
TextureButton.description:
[code]TextureButton[/code] has the same functionality as [Button], except it uses sprites instead of Godot's [Theme] resource. It is faster to create, but it doesn't support localization like more complex Controls.
		The Normal state's texture is required. Others are optional.

constants.name: STRETCH_SCALE
constants.description: Scale to fit the node's bounding rectangle.

constants.name: STRETCH_TILE
constants.description: Tile inside the node's bounding rectangle.

constants.name: STRETCH_KEEP
constants.description: The texture keeps its original size and stays in the bounding rectangle's top-left corner.

constants.name: STRETCH_KEEP_CENTERED
constants.description: The texture keeps its original size and stays centered in the node's bounding rectangle.

constants.name: STRETCH_KEEP_ASPECT
constants.description: Scale the texture to fit the node's bounding rectangle, but maintain the texture's aspect ratio.

constants.name: STRETCH_KEEP_ASPECT_CENTERED
constants.description: Scale the texture to fit the node's bounding rectangle, center it, and maintain its aspect ratio.

constants.name: STRETCH_KEEP_ASPECT_COVERED
constants.description: Scale the texture so that the shorter side fits the bounding rectangle. The other side clips to the node's limits.

properties.name: expand
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the texture stretches to the edges of the node's bounding rectangle using the [member stretch_mode]. If [code]false[/code] the texture will not scale with the node. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: stretch_mode
properties.description: Controls the texture's behavior when you resize the node's bounding rectangle, [b]only if[/b] [member expand] is [code]true[/code]. Set it to one of the [code]STRETCH_*[/code] constants. See the constants to learn more.

properties.name: texture_click_mask
properties.description: Pure black and white [Bitmap] image to use for click detection. On the mask, white pixels represent the button's clickable area. Use it to create buttons with curved shapes.

properties.name: texture_disabled
properties.description: Texture to display when the node is disabled. See [member BaseButton.disabled].

properties.name: texture_focused
properties.description: Texture to display when the node has mouse or keyboard focus.

properties.name: texture_hover
properties.description: Texture to display when the mouse hovers the node.

properties.name: texture_normal
properties.description: Texture to display by default, when the node is [b]not[/b] in the disabled, focused, hover or pressed state.

properties.name: texture_pressed
properties.description: Texture to display on mouse down over the node, if the node has keyboard focus and the player presses the enter key or if the player presses the [member BaseButton.shortcut] key.

PoolColorArray.name: PoolColorArray
PoolColorArray.description: Array of Color, Contains colors. Optimized for memory usage, can't fragment the memory.

methods.name: PoolColorArray
methods.description: Create from a generic array.

methods.name: append
methods.description: Append an element at the end of the array (alias of [method push_back]).

methods.name: append_array
methods.description: Append a [code]PoolColorArray[/code] at the end of this array.

methods.name: insert
methods.description: Insert a new element at a given position in the array. The position must be valid, or at the end of the array (pos==size()).

methods.name: invert
methods.description: Reverse the order of the elements in the array (so first element will now be the last).

methods.name: push_back
methods.description: Append a value to the array.

methods.name: remove
methods.description: Remove an element from the array by index.

methods.name: resize
methods.description: Set the size of the array. If the array is grown reserve elements at the end of the array. If the array is shrunk truncate the array to the new size.

methods.name: set
methods.description: Change the [Color] at the given index.

methods.name: size
methods.description: Return the size of the array.

ParticlesMaterial.name: ParticlesMaterial
ParticlesMaterial.description:
ParticlesMaterial defines particle properties and behavior. It is used in the [code]process_material[/code] of [Particles] and [Particles2D] emitter nodes.
		Some of this material's properties are applied to each particle when emitted, while others can have a [CurveTexture] applied to vary values over the lifetime of the particle.

constants.name: PARAM_INITIAL_LINEAR_VELOCITY
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set initial velocity properties.

constants.name: PARAM_ANGULAR_VELOCITY
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set angular velocity properties.

constants.name: PARAM_ORBIT_VELOCITY
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set orbital_velocity properties.

constants.name: PARAM_LINEAR_ACCEL
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set linear acceleration properties.

constants.name: PARAM_RADIAL_ACCEL
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set radial acceleration properties.

constants.name: PARAM_TANGENTIAL_ACCEL
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set tangential acceleration properties.

constants.name: PARAM_DAMPING
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set damping properties.

constants.name: PARAM_ANGLE
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set angle properties.

constants.name: PARAM_SCALE
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set scale properties.

constants.name: PARAM_HUE_VARIATION
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set hue_variation properties.

constants.name: PARAM_ANIM_SPEED
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set animation speed properties.

constants.name: PARAM_ANIM_OFFSET
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set animation offset properties.

constants.name: FLAG_ALIGN_Y_TO_VELOCITY
constants.description: Use with [method set_flag] to set [member flag_align_y].

constants.name: FLAG_ROTATE_Y
constants.description: Use with [method set_flag] to set [member flag_rotate_y]

constants.name: EMISSION_SHAPE_POINT
constants.description: All particles will be emitted from a single point.

constants.name: EMISSION_SHAPE_SPHERE
constants.description: Particles will be emitted in the volume of a sphere.

constants.name: EMISSION_SHAPE_BOX
constants.description: Particles will be emitted in the volume of a box.

properties.name: angle
properties.description: Initial rotation applied to each particle.

properties.name: angle_curve
properties.description: Each particle's rotation will be animated along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: angle_random
properties.description: Rotation randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: angular_velocity
properties.description: Initial angular velocity applied to each particle.

properties.name: angular_velocity_curve
properties.description: Each particle's angular velocity will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: angular_velocity_random
properties.description: Angular velocity randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: anim_loop
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] animation will loop. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: anim_offset
properties.description: Particle animation offset.

properties.name: anim_offset_curve
properties.description: Each particle's animation offset will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: anim_offset_random
properties.description: Animation offset randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: anim_speed
properties.description: Particle animation speed.

properties.name: anim_speed_curve
properties.description: Each particle's animation speed will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: anim_speed_random
properties.description: Animation speed randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: color
properties.description: Each particle's initial color. If the [Particle2D]'s [code]texture[/code] is defined, it will be multiplied by this color.

properties.name: color_ramp
properties.description: Each particle's color will vary along this [GradientTexture].

properties.name: damping
properties.description: The rate at which particles lose velocity.

properties.name: damping_curve
properties.description: Damping will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: damping_random
properties.description: Damping randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: emission_box_extents
properties.description: The box's extents if [code]emission_shape[/code] is set to [code]EMISSION_SHAPE_BOX[/code].

properties.name: emission_point_count
properties.description: The number of emission points if [code]emission_shape[/code] is set to [code]EMISSION_SHAPE_POINTS[/code] or [code]EMISSION_SHAPE_DIRECTED_POINTS[/code].

properties.name: emission_shape
properties.description: Particles will be emitted inside this region. Use [code]EMISSION_SHAPE_*[/code] constants for values. Default value: [code]EMISSION_SHAPE_POINT[/code].

properties.name: emission_sphere_radius
properties.description: The sphere's radius if [code]emission_shape[/code] is set to [code]EMISSION_SHAPE_SPHERE[/code].

properties.name: flag_disable_z
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] particles will not move on the z axis. Default value: [code]true[/code] for [Particles2D], [code]false[/code] for [Particles].

properties.name: gravity
properties.description: Gravity applied to every particle. Default value: [code](0, 98, 0)[/code].

properties.name: hue_variation
properties.description: Initial hue variation applied to each particle.

properties.name: hue_variation_curve
properties.description: Each particle's hue will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: hue_variation_random
properties.description: Hue variation randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: initial_velocity
properties.description: Initial velocity for each particle.

properties.name: initial_velocity_random
properties.description: Initial velocity randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: linear_accel
properties.description: Linear acceleration applied to each particle.

properties.name: linear_accel_curve
properties.description: Each particle's linear acceleration will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: linear_accel_random
properties.description: Linear acceleration randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: orbit_velocity
properties.description: Orbital velocity applied to each particle.

properties.name: orbit_velocity_curve
properties.description: Each particle's orbital velocity will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: orbit_velocity_random
properties.description: Orbital velocity randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: radial_accel
properties.description: Linear acceleration applied to each particle.

properties.name: radial_accel_curve
properties.description: Each particle's radial acceleration will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: radial_accel_random
properties.description: Radial acceleration randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: scale
properties.description: Initial scale applied to each particle.

properties.name: scale_curve
properties.description: Each particle's scale will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: scale_random
properties.description: Scale randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: spread
properties.description: Each particle's initial direction range from [code]+spread[/code] to [code]-spread[/code] degrees. Default value: [code]45[/code].

properties.name: tangential_accel
properties.description: Tangential acceleration applied to each particle. Tangential acceleration is perpendicular to the particle's velocity.

properties.name: tangential_accel_curve
properties.description: Each particle's tangential acceleration will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: tangential_accel_random
properties.description: Tangential acceleration randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: trail_color_modifier
properties.description: Trail particles' color will vary along this [GradientTexture].

properties.name: trail_divisor
properties.description: Emitter will emit [code]amount[/code] divided by [code]trail_divisor[/code] particles. The remaining particles will be used as trail(s).

properties.name: trail_size_modifier
properties.description: Trail particles' size will vary along this [CurveTexture].

ARVRCamera.name: ARVRCamera
ARVRCamera.brief_description: A camera node with a few overrules for AR/VR applied such as location tracking.
ARVRCamera.description:
This is a helper spatial node for our camera, note that if stereoscopic rendering is applicable (VR-HMD) most of the camera properties are ignored as the HMD information overrides them. The only properties that can be trusted are the near and far planes.
		The position and orientation of this node is automatically updated by the ARVR Server to represent the location of the HMD if such tracking is available and can thus be used by game logic. Note that in contrast to the ARVR Controller the render thread has access to the most up to date tracking data of the HMD and the location of the ARVRCamera can lag a few milliseconds behind what is used for rendering as a result.

HSeparator.name: HSeparator
HSeparator.description: Horizontal separator. See [Separator]. It is used to separate objects vertically, though (but it looks horizontal!).

ScrollContainer.name: ScrollContainer
ScrollContainer.brief_description: A helper node for displaying scrollable elements (e.g. lists).
ScrollContainer.description: A ScrollContainer node with a [Control] child and scrollbar child ([HScrollbar], [VScrollBar], or both) will only draw the Control within the ScrollContainer area.  Scrollbars will automatically be drawn at the right (for vertical) or bottom (for horizontal) and will enable dragging to move the viewable Control (and its children) within the ScrollContainer.  Scrollbars will also automatically resize the grabber based on the minimum_size of the Control relative to the ScrollContainer.  Works great with a [Panel] control.  You can set EXPAND on children size flags, so they will upscale to ScrollContainer size if ScrollContainer size is bigger (scroll is invisible for chosen dimension).

properties.name: scroll_horizontal
properties.description: The current horizontal scroll value.

properties.name: scroll_horizontal_enabled
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], enables horizontal scrolling.

properties.name: scroll_vertical
properties.description: The current horizontal scroll value.

properties.name: scroll_vertical_enabled
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], enables vertical scrolling.

PackedScene.name: PackedScene
PackedScene.brief_description: An abstraction of a serialized scene.
PackedScene.description:
A simplified interface to a scene file. Provides access to operations and checks that can be performed on the scene resource itself.
		TODO: explain ownership, and that node does not need to own itself

methods.name: can_instance
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the scene file has nodes.

methods.name: get_state
methods.description: Returns the [code]SceneState[/code] representing the scene file contents.

methods.name: instance
methods.description: Instantiates the scene's node hierarchy. Triggers child scene instantiation(s). Triggers the [enum Object.NOTIFICATION_INSTANCED] notification on the root node.

methods.name: pack
methods.description: Pack will ignore any sub-nodes not owned by given node. See [method Node.set_owner].

constants.name: GEN_EDIT_STATE_DISABLED
constants.description: If passed to [method instance], blocks edits to the scene state.

constants.name: GEN_EDIT_STATE_INSTANCE
constants.description: If passed to [method instance], provides local scene resources to the local scene. Requires tools compiled.

constants.name: GEN_EDIT_STATE_MAIN
constants.description: If passed to [method instance], provides local scene resources to the local scene. Only the main scene should receive the main edit state. Requires tools compiled.

properties.name: _bundled
properties.description:
A dictionary representation of the scene contents.
			Available keys include "rnames" and "variants" for resources, "node_count", "nodes", "node_paths" for nodes, "editable_instances" for base scene children overrides, "conn_count" and "conns" for signal connections, and "version" for the format style of the PackedScene.

ScrollBar.name: ScrollBar
ScrollBar.description: Scrollbars are a [Range] based [Control], that display a draggable area (the size of the page). Horizontal ([HScrollBar]) and Vertical ([VScrollBar]) versions are available.

Mesh.name: Mesh
Mesh.brief_description: A [Resource] that contains vertex-array based geometry.
Mesh.description: Mesh is a type of [Resource] that contains vertex-array based geometry, divided in [i]surfaces[/i]. Each surface contains a completely separate array and a material used to draw it. Design wise, a mesh with multiple surfaces is preferred to a single surface, because objects created in 3D editing software commonly contain multiple materials.

methods.name: create_convex_shape
methods.description: Calculate a [ConvexPolygonShape] from the mesh.

methods.name: create_outline
methods.description: Calculate an outline mesh at a defined offset (margin) from the original mesh. Note: Typically returns the vertices in reverse order (e.g. clockwise to anti-clockwise).

methods.name: create_trimesh_shape
methods.description: Calculate a [ConcavePolygonShape] from the mesh.

methods.name: generate_triangle_mesh
methods.description: Generate a [TriangleMesh] from the mesh.

methods.name: get_faces
methods.description: Returns all the vertices that make up the faces of the mesh. Each three vertices represent one triangle.

constants.name: PRIMITIVE_POINTS
constants.description: Render array as points (one vertex equals one point).

constants.name: PRIMITIVE_LINES
constants.description: Render array as lines (every two vertices a line is created).

constants.name: PRIMITIVE_LINE_STRIP
constants.description: Render array as line strip.

constants.name: PRIMITIVE_LINE_LOOP
constants.description: Render array as line loop (like line strip, but closed).

constants.name: PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLES
constants.description: Render array as triangles (every three vertices a triangle is created).

constants.name: PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLE_STRIP
constants.description: Render array as triangle strips.

constants.name: PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLE_FAN
constants.description: Render array as triangle fans.

VisualScriptClassConstant.name: VisualScriptClassConstant
VisualScriptClassConstant.brief_description: Gets a constant from a given class.
VisualScriptClassConstant.description:
This node returns a constant from a given class, such as [@GlobalScope.TYPE_INT]. See the given class' documentation for available constants.
		[b]Input Ports:[/b]
		none
		[b]Output Ports:[/b]
		- Data (variant): [code]value[/code]

properties.name: base_type
properties.description: The constant's parent class.

properties.name: constant
properties.description: The constant to return. See the given class for its available constants.

Translation.name: Translation
Translation.description: Translations are resources that can be loaded/unloaded on demand. They map a string to another string.

methods.name: add_message
methods.description: Add a message for translation.

methods.name: erase_message
methods.description: Erase a message.

methods.name: get_message
methods.description: Return a message for translation.

methods.name: get_message_list
methods.description: Return all the messages (keys).

LinkButton.name: LinkButton
LinkButton.brief_description: Simple button used to represent a link to some resource
LinkButton.description: This kind of buttons are primarily used when the interaction with the button causes a context change (like linking to a web page).

constants.name: UNDERLINE_MODE_ALWAYS
constants.description: The LinkButton will always show an underline at the bottom of its text

constants.name: UNDERLINE_MODE_ON_HOVER
constants.description: The LinkButton will show an underline at the bottom of its text when the mouse cursor is over it.

constants.name: UNDERLINE_MODE_NEVER
constants.description: The LinkButton will never show an underline at the bottom of its text.

Range.name: Range
Range.brief_description: Abstract base class for range-based controls.
Range.description: Range is a base class for [Control] nodes that change a floating point [i]value[/i] between a [i]minimum[/i] and a [i]maximum[/i], using [i]step[/i] and [i]page[/i], for example a [ScrollBar].

methods.name: share
methods.description: Binds two Ranges together along with any Ranges previously grouped with either of them. When any of Range's member variables change, it will share the new value with all other Ranges in its group.

methods.name: unshare
methods.description: Stop Range from sharing its member variables with any other Range.

signals.name: changed
signals.description: This signal is emitted when min, max, range or step change.

signals.name: value_changed
signals.description: This signal is emitted when value changes.

properties.name: exp_edit
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] and [code]min_value[/code] is greater than 0, [code]value[/code] will be represented exponentially rather than linearly.

properties.name: max_value
properties.description: Maximum value. Range is clamped if [code]value[/code] is greater than [code]max_value[/code]. Default value: 100.

properties.name: min_value
properties.description: Minimum value. Range is clamped if [code]value[/code] is less than [code]min_value[/code]. Default value: 0.

properties.name: page
properties.description: Page size. Used mainly for [ScrollBar]. ScrollBar's length is its size multiplied by [code]page[/code] over the difference between [code]min_value[/code] and [code]max_value[/code].

properties.name: ratio
properties.description: The value mapped between 0 and 1.

properties.name: rounded
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], [code]value[/code] will always be rounded to the nearest integer.

properties.name: step
properties.description: If greater than 0, [code]value[/code] will always be rounded to a multiple of [code]step[/code]. If [code]rounded[/code] is also [code]true[/code], [code]value[/code] will first be rounded to a multiple of [code]step[/code] then rounded to the nearest integer.

properties.name: value
properties.description: Range's current value.

EditorFileSystemDirectory.name: EditorFileSystemDirectory
EditorFileSystemDirectory.brief_description: A diretory for the resource filesystem.
EditorFileSystemDirectory.description: A more generalized, low-level variation of the directory concept.

methods.name: find_dir_index
methods.description: Returns the index of the directory with name [code]name[/code] or [code]-1[/code] if not found.

methods.name: find_file_index
methods.description: Returns the index of the file with name [code]name[/code] or [code]-1[/code] if not found.

methods.name: get_file
methods.description: Returns the name of the file at index [code]idx[/code].

methods.name: get_file_count
methods.description: Returns the number of files in this directory.

methods.name: get_file_import_is_valid
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the file at index [code]idx[/code] imported properly.

methods.name: get_file_path
methods.description: Returns the path to the file at index [code]idx[/code].

methods.name: get_file_type
methods.description: Returns the file extension of the file at index [code]idx[/code].

methods.name: get_name
methods.description: Returns the name of this directory.

methods.name: get_parent
methods.description: Returns the parent directory for this directory or null if called on a directory at [code]res://[/code] or [code]user://[/code].

methods.name: get_path
methods.description: Returns the path to this directory.

methods.name: get_subdir
methods.description: Returns the subdirectory at index [code]idx[/code].

methods.name: get_subdir_count
methods.description: Returns the number of subdirectories in this directory.

OptionButton.name: OptionButton
OptionButton.brief_description: Button control that provides selectable options when pressed.
OptionButton.description: OptionButton is a type button that provides a selectable list of items when pressed. The item selected becomes the "current" item and is displayed as the button text.

methods.name: add_icon_item
methods.description: Add an item, with a "texture" icon, text "label" and (optionally) id. If no "id" is passed, "id" becomes the item index. New items are appended at the end.

methods.name: add_item
methods.description: Add an item, with text "label" and (optionally) id. If no "id" is passed, "id" becomes the item index. New items are appended at the end.

methods.name: add_separator
methods.description: Add a separator to the list of items. Separators help to group items. Separator also takes up an index and is appended at the end.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear all the items in the [code]OptionButton[/code].

methods.name: get_item_count
methods.description: Return the amount of items in the OptionButton.

methods.name: get_item_icon
methods.description: Return the icon of the item at index "idx".

methods.name: get_item_id
methods.description: Return the ID of the item at index "idx".

methods.name: get_item_text
methods.description: Return the text of the item at index "idx".

methods.name: get_popup
methods.description: Return the [PopupMenu] contained in this button.

methods.name: select
methods.description: Select an item by index and make it the current item.

methods.name: set_item_icon
methods.description: Set the icon of an item at index "idx".

methods.name: set_item_id
methods.description: Set the ID of an item at index "idx".

methods.name: set_item_text
methods.description: Set the text of an item at index "idx".

signals.name: item_selected
signals.description: This signal is emitted when the current item was changed by the user. ID of the item selected is passed as argument (if no IDs were added, ID will be just the item index).

ConvexPolygonShape.name: ConvexPolygonShape
ConvexPolygonShape.description: Convex polygon shape resource, which can be added to a [PhysicsBody] or area.

properties.name: points
properties.description: The list of 3D points forming the convex polygon shape.

Polygon2D.name: Polygon2D
Polygon2D.description: A Polygon2D is defined by a set of points. Each point is connected to the next, with the final point being connected to the first, resulting in a closed polygon. Polygon2Ds can be filled with color (solid or gradient) or filled with a given texture.

properties.name: antialiased
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] polygon edges will be anti-aliased. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: color
properties.description: The polygon's fill color. If [code]texture[/code] is defined, it will be multiplied by this color. It will also be the default color for vertices not set in [code]vertex_colors[/code].

properties.name: invert_border
properties.description: Added padding applied to the bounding box when using [code]invert[/code]. Setting this value too small may result in a "Bad Polygon" error. Default value: [code]100[/code].

properties.name: invert_enable
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] polygon will be inverted, containing the area outside the defined points and extending to the [code]invert_border[/code]. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: offset
properties.description: The offset applied to each vertex.

properties.name: polygon
properties.description: The polygon's list of vertices. The final point will be connected to the first.

properties.name: texture
properties.description: The polygon's fill texture. Use [code]uv[/code] to set texture coordinates.

properties.name: texture_offset
properties.description: Amount to offset the polygon's [code]texture[/code]. If [code](0, 0)[/code] the texture's origin (its top-left corner) will be placed at the polygon's [code]position[/code].

properties.name: texture_rotation
properties.description: The texture's rotation in radians.

properties.name: texture_rotation_degrees
properties.description: The texture's rotation in degrees.

properties.name: texture_scale
properties.description: Amount to multiply the [code]uv[/code] coordinates when using a [code]texture[/code]. Larger values make the texture smaller, and vice versa.

properties.name: uv
properties.description: Texture coordinates for each vertex of the polygon. There should be one [code]uv[/code] per polygon vertex. If there are fewer, undefined vertices will use [code](0, 0)[/code].

properties.name: vertex_colors
properties.description: Color for each vertex. Colors are interpolated between vertices, resulting in smooth gradients. There should be one per polygon vertex. If there are fewer, undefined vertices will use [code]color[/code].

Semaphore.name: Semaphore
Semaphore.description: A synchronization Semaphore. Element used to synchronize multiple [Thread]s. Initialized to zero on creation. Be careful to avoid deadlocks. For a binary version, see [Mutex].

methods.name: post
methods.description: Lowers the [code]Semaphore[/code], allowing one more thread in. Returns [OK] on success, [ERR_BUSY] otherwise.

methods.name: wait
methods.description: Tries to wait for the [code]Semaphore[/code], if its value is zero, blocks until non-zero. Returns [OK] on success, [ERR_BUSY] otherwise.

CollisionShape2D.name: CollisionShape2D
CollisionShape2D.brief_description: Node that represents collision shape data in 2D space.
CollisionShape2D.description: Editor facility for creating and editing collision shapes in 2D space. You can use this node to represent all sorts of collision shapes, for example, add this to an [Area2D] to give it a detection shape, or add it to a [PhysicsBody2D] to give create solid object. [b]IMPORTANT[/b]: this is an Editor-only helper to create shapes, use [method get_shape] to get the actual shape.

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: A disabled collision shape has no effect in the world.

properties.name: one_way_collision
properties.description: Sets whether this collision shape should only detect collision on one side (top or bottom).

properties.name: shape
properties.description: The actual shape owned by this collision shape.

methods.name: float
methods.description: Cast a [bool] value to a floating point value, [code]float(true)[/code] will be equals to 1.0 and [code]float(false)[/code] will be equals to 0.0.

methods.name: float
methods.description: Cast an [int] value to a floating point value, [code]float(1)[/code] will be equals to 1.0.

methods.name: float
methods.description: Cast a [String] value to a floating point value. This method accepts float value strings like [code] '1.23' [/code] and exponential notation strings for its parameter so calling [code] float('1e3') [/code] will return 1000.0 and calling [code] float('1e-3') [/code] will return -0.001.

Physics2DServer.name: Physics2DServer
Physics2DServer.description: Physics 2D Server is the server responsible for all 2D physics. It can create many kinds of physics objects, but does not insert them on the node tree.

methods.name: area_add_shape
methods.description: Adds a shape to the area, along with a transform matrix. Shapes are usually referenced by their index, so you should track which shape has a given index.

methods.name: area_attach_object_instance_id
methods.description: Assigns the area to a descendant of [Object], so it can exist in the node tree.

methods.name: area_clear_shapes
methods.description: Removes all shapes from an area. It does not delete the shapes, so they can be reassigned later.

methods.name: area_create
methods.description: Creates an [Area2D].

methods.name: area_get_object_instance_id
methods.description: Gets the instance ID of the object the area is assigned to.

methods.name: area_get_param
methods.description: Returns an area parameter value. A list of available parameters is on the AREA_PARAM_* constants.

methods.name: area_get_shape
methods.description: Returns the [RID] of the nth shape of an area.

methods.name: area_get_shape_count
methods.description: Returns the number of shapes assigned to an area.

methods.name: area_get_shape_transform
methods.description: Returns the transform matrix of a shape within an area.

methods.name: area_get_space
methods.description: Returns the space assigned to the area.

methods.name: area_get_space_override_mode
methods.description: Returns the space override mode for the area.

methods.name: area_get_transform
methods.description: Returns the transform matrix for an area.

methods.name: area_remove_shape
methods.description: Removes a shape from an area. It does not delete the shape, so it can be reassigned later.

methods.name: area_set_collision_layer
methods.description: Assigns the area to one or many physics layers.

methods.name: area_set_collision_mask
methods.description: Sets which physics layers the area will monitor.

methods.name: area_set_monitor_callback
methods.description:
Sets the function to call when any body/area enters or exits the area. This callback will be called for any object interacting with the area, and takes five parameters:
				1: AREA_BODY_ADDED or AREA_BODY_REMOVED, depending on whether the object entered or exited the area.
				2: [RID] of the object that entered/exited the area.
				3: Instance ID of the object that entered/exited the area.
				4: The shape index of the object that entered/exited the area.
				5: The shape index of the area where the object entered/exited.

methods.name: area_set_param
methods.description: Sets the value for an area parameter. A list of available parameters is on the AREA_PARAM_* constants.

methods.name: area_set_shape
methods.description: Substitutes a given area shape by another. The old shape is selected by its index, the new one by its [RID].

methods.name: area_set_shape_disabled
methods.description: Disables a given shape in an area.

methods.name: area_set_shape_transform
methods.description: Sets the transform matrix for an area shape.

methods.name: area_set_space
methods.description: Assigns a space to the area.

methods.name: area_set_space_override_mode
methods.description: Sets the space override mode for the area. The modes are described in the constants AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_*.

methods.name: area_set_transform
methods.description: Sets the transform matrix for an area.

methods.name: body_add_collision_exception
methods.description: Adds a body to the list of bodies exempt from collisions.

methods.name: body_add_force
methods.description: Adds a positioned force to the applied force and torque. As with [method body_apply_impulse], both the force and the offset from the body origin are in global coordinates. A force differs from an impulse in that, while the two are forces, the impulse clears itself after being applied.

methods.name: body_add_shape
methods.description: Adds a shape to the body, along with a transform matrix. Shapes are usually referenced by their index, so you should track which shape has a given index.

methods.name: body_apply_impulse
methods.description: Adds a positioned impulse to the applied force and torque. Both the force and the offset from the body origin are in global coordinates.

methods.name: body_attach_object_instance_id
methods.description: Assigns the area to a descendant of [Object], so it can exist in the node tree.

methods.name: body_clear_shapes
methods.description: Removes all shapes from a body.

methods.name: body_create
methods.description: Creates a physics body. The first parameter can be any value from constants BODY_MODE*, for the type of body created. Additionally, the body can be created in sleeping state to save processing time.

methods.name: body_get_collision_layer
methods.description: Returns the physics layer or layers a body belongs to.

methods.name: body_get_collision_mask
methods.description: Returns the physics layer or layers a body can collide with.

methods.name: body_get_continuous_collision_detection_mode
methods.description: Returns the continuous collision detection mode.

methods.name: body_get_direct_state
methods.description: Returns the [Physics2DDirectBodyState] of the body.

methods.name: body_get_max_contacts_reported
methods.description: Returns the maximum contacts that can be reported. See [method body_set_max_contacts_reported].

methods.name: body_get_mode
methods.description: Returns the body mode.

methods.name: body_get_object_instance_id
methods.description: Gets the instance ID of the object the area is assigned to.

methods.name: body_get_param
methods.description: Returns the value of a body parameter. A list of available parameters is on the BODY_PARAM_* constants.

methods.name: body_get_shape
methods.description: Returns the [RID] of the nth shape of a body.

methods.name: body_get_shape_count
methods.description: Returns the number of shapes assigned to a body.

methods.name: body_get_shape_metadata
methods.description: Returns the metadata of a shape of a body.

methods.name: body_get_shape_transform
methods.description: Returns the transform matrix of a body shape.

methods.name: body_get_space
methods.description: Returns the [RID] of the space assigned to a body.

methods.name: body_get_state
methods.description: Returns a body state.

methods.name: body_is_omitting_force_integration
methods.description: Returns whether a body uses a callback function to calculate its own physics (see [method body_set_force_integration_callback]).

methods.name: body_remove_collision_exception
methods.description: Removes a body from the list of bodies exempt from collisions.

methods.name: body_remove_shape
methods.description: Removes a shape from a body. The shape is not deleted, so it can be reused afterwards.

methods.name: body_set_axis_velocity
methods.description: Sets an axis velocity. The velocity in the given vector axis will be set as the given vector length. This is useful for jumping behavior.

methods.name: body_set_collision_layer
methods.description: Sets the physics layer or layers a body belongs to.

methods.name: body_set_collision_mask
methods.description: Sets the physics layer or layers a body can collide with.

methods.name: body_set_continuous_collision_detection_mode
methods.description:
Sets the continuous collision detection mode from any of the CCD_MODE_* constants.
				Continuous collision detection tries to predict where a moving body will collide, instead of moving it and correcting its movement if it collided.

methods.name: body_set_force_integration_callback
methods.description: Sets the function used to calculate physics for an object, if that object allows it (see [method body_set_omit_force integration]).

methods.name: body_set_max_contacts_reported
methods.description: Sets the maximum contacts to report. Bodies can keep a log of the contacts with other bodies, this is enabled by setting the maximum amount of contacts reported to a number greater than 0.

methods.name: body_set_mode
methods.description: Sets the body mode, from one of the constants BODY_MODE*.

methods.name: body_set_omit_force_integration
methods.description: Sets whether a body uses a callback function to calculate its own physics (see [method body_set_force_integration_callback]).

methods.name: body_set_param
methods.description: Sets a body parameter. A list of available parameters is on the BODY_PARAM_* constants.

methods.name: body_set_shape
methods.description: Substitutes a given body shape by another. The old shape is selected by its index, the new one by its [RID].

methods.name: body_set_shape_as_one_way_collision
methods.description: Enables one way collision on body if [code]enable[/code] is [code]true[/code].

methods.name: body_set_shape_disabled
methods.description: Disables shape in body if [code]disable[/code] is [code]true[/code].

methods.name: body_set_shape_metadata
methods.description: Sets metadata of a shape within a body. This metadata is different from [method Object.set_meta], and can be retrieved on shape queries.

methods.name: body_set_shape_transform
methods.description: Sets the transform matrix for a body shape.

methods.name: body_set_space
methods.description: Assigns a space to the body (see [method create_space]).

methods.name: body_set_state
methods.description: Sets a body state (see BODY_STATE* constants).

methods.name: body_test_motion
methods.description: Returns whether a body can move from a given point in a given direction. Apart from the boolean return value, a [Physics2DTestMotionResult] can be passed to return additional information in.

methods.name: damped_spring_joint_create
methods.description: Creates a damped spring joint between two bodies. If not specified, the second body is assumed to be the joint itself.

methods.name: damped_string_joint_get_param
methods.description: Returns the value of a damped spring joint parameter.

methods.name: damped_string_joint_set_param
methods.description: Sets a damped spring joint parameter. Parameters are explained in the DAMPED_STRING* constants.

methods.name: free_rid
methods.description: Destroys any of the objects created by Physics2DServer. If the [RID] passed is not one of the objects that can be created by Physics2DServer, an error will be sent to the console.

methods.name: get_process_info
methods.description: Returns information about the current state of the 2D physics engine. The states are listed under the INFO_* constants.

methods.name: groove_joint_create
methods.description: Creates a groove joint between two bodies. If not specified, the bodyies are assumed to be the joint itself.

methods.name: joint_get_param
methods.description: Returns the value of a joint parameter.

methods.name: joint_get_type
methods.description: Returns the type of a joint (see JOINT_* constants).

methods.name: joint_set_param
methods.description: Sets a joint parameter. Parameters are explained in the JOINT_PARAM* constants.

methods.name: pin_joint_create
methods.description: Creates a pin joint between two bodies. If not specified, the second body is assumed to be the joint itself.

methods.name: set_active
methods.description: Activates or deactivates the 2D physics engine.

methods.name: shape_get_data
methods.description: Returns the shape data.

methods.name: shape_get_type
methods.description: Returns the type of shape (see SHAPE_* constants).

methods.name: shape_set_data
methods.description: Sets the shape data that defines its shape and size. The data to be passed depends on the kind of shape created [method shape_get_type].

methods.name: space_create
methods.description: Creates a space. A space is a collection of parameters for the physics engine that can be assigned to an area or a body. It can be assigned to an area with [method area_set_space], or to a body with [method body_set_space].

methods.name: space_get_direct_state
methods.description: Returns the state of a space, a [Physics2DDirectSpaceState]. This object can be used to make collision/intersection queries.

methods.name: space_get_param
methods.description: Returns the value of a space parameter.

methods.name: space_is_active
methods.description: Returns whether the space is active.

methods.name: space_set_active
methods.description: Marks a space as active. It will not have an effect, unless it is assigned to an area or body.

methods.name: space_set_param
methods.description: Sets the value for a space parameter. A list of available parameters is on the SPACE_PARAM_* constants.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_CONTACT_RECYCLE_RADIUS
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum distance a pair of bodies has to move before their collision status has to be recalculated.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_CONTACT_MAX_SEPARATION
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum distance a shape can be from another before they are considered separated.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_BODY_MAX_ALLOWED_PENETRATION
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum distance a shape can penetrate another shape before it is considered a collision.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_BODY_LINEAR_VELOCITY_SLEEP_THRESHOLD
constants.description: Constant to set/get the threshold linear velocity of activity. A body marked as potentially inactive for both linear and angular velocity will be put to sleep after the time given.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_BODY_ANGULAR_VELOCITY_SLEEP_THRESHOLD
constants.description: Constant to set/get the threshold angular velocity of activity. A body marked as potentially inactive for both linear and angular velocity will be put to sleep after the time given.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_BODY_TIME_TO_SLEEP
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum time of activity. A body marked as potentially inactive for both linear and angular velocity will be put to sleep after this time.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_CONSTRAINT_DEFAULT_BIAS
constants.description: Constant to set/get the default solver bias for all physics constraints. A solver bias is a factor controlling how much two objects "rebound", after violating a constraint, to avoid leaving them in that state because of numerical imprecision.

constants.name: SHAPE_LINE
constants.description: This is the constant for creating line shapes. A line shape is an infinite line with an origin point, and a normal. Thus, it can be used for front/behind checks.

constants.name: SHAPE_SEGMENT
constants.description: This is the constant for creating segment shapes. A segment shape is a line from a point A to a point B. It can be checked for intersections.

constants.name: SHAPE_CIRCLE
constants.description: This is the constant for creating circle shapes. A circle shape only has a radius. It can be used for intersections and inside/outside checks.

constants.name: SHAPE_RECTANGLE
constants.description: This is the constant for creating rectangle shapes. A rectangle shape is defined by a width and a height. It can be used for intersections and inside/outside checks.

constants.name: SHAPE_CAPSULE
constants.description: This is the constant for creating capsule shapes. A capsule shape is defined by a radius and a length. It can be used for intersections and inside/outside checks.

constants.name: SHAPE_CONVEX_POLYGON
constants.description: This is the constant for creating convex polygon shapes. A polygon is defined by a list of points. It can be used for intersections and inside/outside checks. Unlike the method [method CollisionPolygon2D.set_polygon], polygons modified with [method shape_set_data] do not verify that the points supplied form is a convex polygon.

constants.name: SHAPE_CONCAVE_POLYGON
constants.description: This is the constant for creating concave polygon shapes. A polygon is defined by a list of points. It can be used for intersections checks, but not for inside/outside checks.

constants.name: SHAPE_CUSTOM
constants.description: This constant is used internally by the engine. Any attempt to create this kind of shape results in an error.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY
constants.description: Constant to set/get gravity strength in an area.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_VECTOR
constants.description: Constant to set/get gravity vector/center in an area.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_IS_POINT
constants.description: Constant to set/get whether the gravity vector of an area is a direction, or a center point.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_DISTANCE_SCALE
constants.description: Constant to set/get the falloff factor for point gravity of an area. The greater this value is, the faster the strength of gravity decreases with the square of distance.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_POINT_ATTENUATION
constants.description: This constant was used to set/get the falloff factor for point gravity. It has been superseded by AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_DISTANCE_SCALE.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_LINEAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get the linear dampening factor of an area.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_ANGULAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get the angular dampening factor of an area.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_PRIORITY
constants.description: Constant to set/get the priority (order of processing) of an area.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_DISABLED
constants.description: This area does not affect gravity/damp. These are generally areas that exist only to detect collisions, and objects entering or exiting them.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_COMBINE
constants.description: This area adds its gravity/damp values to whatever has been calculated so far. This way, many overlapping areas can combine their physics to make interesting effects.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_COMBINE_REPLACE
constants.description: This area adds its gravity/damp values to whatever has been calculated so far. Then stops taking into account the rest of the areas, even the default one.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_REPLACE
constants.description: This area replaces any gravity/damp, even the default one, and stops taking into account the rest of the areas.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_REPLACE_COMBINE
constants.description: This area replaces any gravity/damp calculated so far, but keeps calculating the rest of the areas, down to the default one.

constants.name: BODY_MODE_STATIC
constants.description: Constant for static bodies.

constants.name: BODY_MODE_KINEMATIC
constants.description: Constant for kinematic bodies.

constants.name: BODY_MODE_RIGID
constants.description: Constant for rigid bodies.

constants.name: BODY_MODE_CHARACTER
constants.description: Constant for rigid bodies in character mode. In this mode, a body can not rotate, and only its linear velocity is affected by physics.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_BOUNCE
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's bounce factor.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_FRICTION
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's friction.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_MASS
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's mass.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_INERTIA
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's inertia.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_GRAVITY_SCALE
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's gravity multiplier.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_LINEAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's linear dampening factor.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_ANGULAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's angular dampening factor.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_MAX
constants.description: This is the last ID for body parameters. Any attempt to set this property is ignored. Any attempt to get it returns 0.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_TRANSFORM
constants.description: Constant to set/get the current transform matrix of the body.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_LINEAR_VELOCITY
constants.description: Constant to set/get the current linear velocity of the body.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_ANGULAR_VELOCITY
constants.description: Constant to set/get the current angular velocity of the body.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_SLEEPING
constants.description: Constant to sleep/wake up a body, or to get whether it is sleeping.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_CAN_SLEEP
constants.description: Constant to set/get whether the body can sleep.

constants.name: JOINT_PIN
constants.description: Constant to create pin joints.

constants.name: JOINT_GROOVE
constants.description: Constant to create groove joints.

constants.name: JOINT_DAMPED_SPRING
constants.description: Constant to create damped spring joints.

constants.name: DAMPED_STRING_REST_LENGTH
constants.description: Set the resting length of the spring joint. The joint will always try to go to back this length when pulled apart.

constants.name: DAMPED_STRING_STIFFNESS
constants.description: Set the stiffness of the spring joint. The joint applies a force equal to the stiffness times the distance from its resting length.

constants.name: DAMPED_STRING_DAMPING
constants.description: Set the damping ratio of the spring joint. A value of 0 indicates an undamped spring, while 1 causes the system to reach equilibrium as fast as possible (critical damping).

constants.name: CCD_MODE_DISABLED
constants.description: Disables continuous collision detection. This is the fastest way to detect body collisions, but can miss small, fast-moving objects.

constants.name: CCD_MODE_CAST_RAY
constants.description: Enables continuous collision detection by raycasting. It is faster than shapecasting, but less precise.

constants.name: CCD_MODE_CAST_SHAPE
constants.description: Enables continuous collision detection by shapecasting. It is the slowest CCD method, and the most precise.

constants.name: AREA_BODY_ADDED
constants.description: The value of the first parameter and area callback function receives, when an object enters one of its shapes.

constants.name: AREA_BODY_REMOVED
constants.description: The value of the first parameter and area callback function receives, when an object exits one of its shapes.

constants.name: INFO_ACTIVE_OBJECTS
constants.description: Constant to get the number of objects that are not sleeping.

constants.name: INFO_COLLISION_PAIRS
constants.description: Constant to get the number of possible collisions.

constants.name: INFO_ISLAND_COUNT
constants.description: Constant to get the number of space regions where a collision could occur.

VisualScriptCondition.name: VisualScriptCondition
VisualScriptCondition.brief_description: A Visual Script node which branches the flow.
VisualScriptCondition.description:
A Visual Script node that checks a [bool] input port. If [code]true[/code] it will exit via the true sequence port. If [code]false[/code] it will exit via the "false" sequence port. After exiting either, it exits via the done port. Sequence ports may be left disconnected.
		[b]Input Ports:[/b]
		- Sequence: [code]if (cond) is[/code]
		- Data (boolean): [code]cond[/code]
		[b]Output Ports:[/b]
		- Sequence: [code]true[/code]
		- Sequence: [code]false[/code]
		- Sequence: [code]done[/code]

EditorInterface.name: EditorInterface
EditorInterface.description: Editor interface. Allows saving and (re-)loading scenes, rendering mesh previews, inspecting and editing resources and objects and provides access to [EditorSettings], [EditorFileSystem], [EditorResourcePreview]\ er, [ScriptEditor], the editor viewport, as well as information about scenes. Also see [EditorPlugin] and [EditorScript].

methods.name: edit_resource
methods.description: Edits the given [Resource].

methods.name: get_base_control
methods.description: Returns the base [Control].

methods.name: get_edited_scene_root
methods.description: Returns the edited scene's root [Node].

methods.name: get_editor_settings
methods.description: Returns the [EditorSettings].

methods.name: get_editor_viewport
methods.description: Returns the editor [Viewport].

methods.name: get_open_scenes
methods.description: Returns an [Array] of the currently opened scenes.

methods.name: get_resource_filesystem
methods.description: Returns the [EditorFileSystem].

methods.name: get_resource_previewer
methods.description: Returns the [EditorResourcePreview]\ er.

methods.name: get_script_editor
methods.description: Returns the [ScriptEditor].

methods.name: get_selection
methods.description: Returns the [EditorSelection].

methods.name: inspect_object
methods.description: Shows the given property on the given [code]object[/code] in the Editor's Inspector dock.

methods.name: make_mesh_previews
methods.description: Returns mesh previews rendered at the given size as an [Array] of [Texture]s.

methods.name: open_scene_from_path
methods.description: Opens the scene at the given path.

methods.name: reload_scene_from_path
methods.description: Reloads the scene at the given path.

methods.name: save_scene
methods.description: Saves the scene. Returns either OK or ERR_CANT_CREATE. See [@GlobalScope] constants.

methods.name: save_scene_as
methods.description: Saves the scene as a file at [code]path[/code].

PopupPanel.name: PopupPanel
PopupPanel.brief_description: Class for displaying popups with a panel background.
PopupPanel.description: Class for displaying popups with a panel background. In some cases it might be simpler to use than [Popup], since it provides a configurable background. If you are making windows, better check [WindowDialog].

ProgressBar.name: ProgressBar
ProgressBar.description: General purpose progress bar. Shows fill percentage from right to left.

AudioEffectHighPassFilter.name: AudioEffectHighPassFilter
AudioEffectHighPassFilter.brief_description: Adds a high pass filter to the Audio Bus.
AudioEffectHighPassFilter.description: Cuts frequencies lower than the [member cutoff_hz] and allows higher frequencies to pass.

VisualScriptVariableGet.name: VisualScriptVariableGet
VisualScriptVariableGet.description:
Returns a variable's value. "Var Name" must be supplied, with an optional type.
		[b]Input Ports:[/b]
		none
		[b]Output Ports:[/b]
		- Data (variant): [code]value[/code]

properties.name: var_name
properties.description: The variable's name.

Texture.name: Texture
Texture.description: A texture works by registering an image in the video hardware, which then can be used in 3D models or 2D [Sprite] or GUI [Control].

methods.name: get_height
methods.description: Return the texture height.

methods.name: get_size
methods.description: Return the texture size.

methods.name: get_width
methods.description: Return the texture width.

constants.name: FLAGS_DEFAULT
constants.description: Default flags. Generate mipmaps, repeat, and filter are enabled.

constants.name: FLAG_MIPMAPS
constants.description: Generate mipmaps, which are smaller versions of the same texture to use when zoomed out, keeping the aspect ratio.

constants.name: FLAG_REPEAT
constants.description: Repeats texture (instead of clamp to edge).

constants.name: FLAG_FILTER
constants.description: Magnifying filter, to enable smooth zooming in of the texture.

constants.name: FLAG_ANISOTROPIC_FILTER
constants.description:
Anisotropic mipmap filtering. Generates smaller versions of the same texture with different aspect ratios.
			More effective on planes often shown going to the horrizon as those textures (Walls or Ground for example) get squashed in the viewport to different aspect ratios and regular mipmaps keep the aspect ratio so they don't optimize storage that well in those cases.

constants.name: FLAG_CONVERT_TO_LINEAR
constants.description: Converts texture to SRGB color space.

constants.name: FLAG_MIRRORED_REPEAT
constants.description: Repeats texture with alternate sections mirrored.

constants.name: FLAG_VIDEO_SURFACE
constants.description: Texture is a video surface.

properties.name: flags
properties.description: The texture's flags.

Container.name: Container
Container.description:
Base node for containers. A [code]Container[/code] contains other controls and automatically arranges them in a certain way.
		A Control can inherit this to create custom container classes.

methods.name: fit_child_in_rect
methods.description: Fit a child control in a given rect. This is mainly a helper for creating custom container classes.

methods.name: queue_sort
methods.description: Queue resort of the contained children. This is called automatically anyway, but can be called upon request.

signals.name: sort_children
signals.description: Emitted when sorting the children is needed.

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_SORT_CHILDREN
constants.description: Notification for when sorting the children, it must be obeyed immediately.

VisualScriptLocalVar.name: VisualScriptLocalVar
VisualScriptLocalVar.description:
Returns a local variable's value. "Var Name" must be supplied, with an optional type.
		[b]Input Ports:[/b]
		none
		[b]Output Ports:[/b]
		- Data (variant): [code]get[/code]

properties.name: type
properties.description: The local variable's type.

properties.name: var_name
properties.description: The local variable's name.

VisualServer.name: VisualServer
VisualServer.description:
Server for anything visible. The visual server is the API backend for everything visible. The whole scene system mounts on it to display.
		The visual server is completely opaque, the internals are entirely implementation specific and cannot be accessed.

methods.name: black_bars_set_images
methods.description: Sets images to be rendered in the window margin.

methods.name: black_bars_set_margins
methods.description: Sets margin size, where black bars (or images, if [method black_bars_set_images] was used) are rendered.

Adds a nine patch image to the [CanvasItem]'s draw commands.

Control.name: Control
Control.brief_description: All User Interface nodes inherit from Control. Features anchors and margins to adapt its position and size to its parent.
Control.description:
Base class for all User Interface or [i]UI[/i] related nodes. [code]Control[/code] features a bounding rectangle that defines its extents, an anchor position relative to its parent and margins that represent an offset to the anchor. The margins update automatically when the node, any of its parents, or the screen size change.
		For more information on Godot's UI system, anchors, margins, and containers, see the related tutorials in the manual. To build flexible UIs, you'll need a mix of UI elements that inherit from [code]Control[/code] and [Container] nodes.
		[b]User Interface nodes and input[/b]
		Godot sends input events to the scene's root node first, by calling [method Node._input]. [method Node._input] forwards the event down the node tree to the nodes under the mouse cursor, or on keyboard focus. To do so, it calls [method MainLoop._input_event]. Call [method accept_event] so no other node receives the event. Once you accepted an input, it becomes handled so [method Node._unhandled_input] will not process it.
		Only one [code]Control[/code] node can be in keyboard focus. Only the node in focus will receive keyboard events. To get the focus, call [method set_focus_mode]. [code]Control[/code] nodes lose focus when another node grabs it, or if you hide the node in focus.
		Call [method set_ignore_mouse] to tell a [code]Control[/code] node to ignore mouse or touch events. You'll need it if you place an icon on top of a button.
		[Theme] resources change the Control's appearance. If you change the [Theme] on a [code]Control[/code] node, it affects all of its children. To override some of the theme's parameters, call one of the [code]add_*_override[/code] methods, like [method add_font_override]. You can override the theme with the inspector.

methods.name: _get_minimum_size
methods.description: Returns the minimum size this Control can shrink to. The node can never be smaller than this minimum size.

methods.name: _gui_input
methods.description:
The node's parent forwards input events to this method. Use it to process and accept inputs on UI elements. See [method accept_event].
				Replaces Godot 2's [code]_input_event[/code].

methods.name: accept_event
methods.description: Marks an input event as handled. Once you accept an input event, it stops propagating, even to nodes listening to [method Node._unhandled_input] or [method Node._unhandled_key_input].
