constants.description: Show the system's vertical resize mouse cursor when the user hovers the node. A double headed vertical arrow. It tells the user they can resize the window or the panel vertically.

constants.name: CURSOR_HSIZE
constants.description: Show the system's horizontal resize mouse cursor when the user hovers the node. A double headed horizontal arrow. It tells the user they can resize the window or the panel horizontally.

constants.name: CURSOR_BDIAGSIZE
constants.description: Show the system's window resize mouse cursor when the user hovers the node. The cursor is a double headed arrow that goes from the bottom left to the top right. It tells the user they can resize the window or the panel both horizontally and vertically.

constants.name: CURSOR_FDIAGSIZE
constants.description: Show the system's window resize mouse cursor when the user hovers the node. The cursor is a double headed arrow that goes from the top left to the bottom right, the opposite of [code]CURSOR_BDIAGSIZE[/code]. It tells the user they can resize the window or the panel both horizontally and vertically.

constants.name: CURSOR_MOVE
constants.description: Show the system's move mouse cursor when the user hovers the node. It shows 2 double-headed arrows at a 90 degree angle. It tells the user they can move a UI element freely.

constants.name: CURSOR_VSPLIT
constants.description: Show the system's vertical split mouse cursor when the user hovers the node. On Windows, it's the same as [code]CURSOR_VSIZE[/code].

constants.name: CURSOR_HSPLIT
constants.description: Show the system's horizontal split mouse cursor when the user hovers the node. On Windows, it's the same as [code]CURSOR_HSIZE[/code].

constants.name: CURSOR_HELP
constants.description: Show the system's help mouse cursor when the user hovers the node, a question mark.

constants.name: PRESET_TOP_LEFT
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to the top-left of the parent container's bounds. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: PRESET_TOP_RIGHT
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to the top-right of the parent container's bounds. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: PRESET_BOTTOM_LEFT
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to the bottom-left of the parent container's bounds. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: PRESET_BOTTOM_RIGHT
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to the bottom-right of the parent container's bounds. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: PRESET_CENTER_LEFT
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to the center of the left edge of the parent container's bounds. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: PRESET_CENTER_TOP
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to the center of the top edge of the parent container's bounds. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: PRESET_CENTER_RIGHT
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to the center of the right edge of the parent container's bounds. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: PRESET_CENTER_BOTTOM
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to the center of the bottom edge of the parent container's bounds. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: PRESET_CENTER
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to the center of the parent container's bounds. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: PRESET_LEFT_WIDE
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to the left edge of the parent container. The left margin becomes relative to the left edge and the top margin relative to the top left corner of the node's parent. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: PRESET_TOP_WIDE
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to the top edge of the parent container. The left margin becomes relative to the top left corner, the top margin relative to the top edge, and the right margin relative to the top right corner of the node's parent. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: PRESET_RIGHT_WIDE
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to the right edge of the parent container. The right margin becomes relative to the right edge and the top margin relative to the top right corner of the node's parent. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: PRESET_BOTTOM_WIDE
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to the bottom edge of the parent container. The left margin becomes relative to the bottom left corner, the bottom margin relative to the bottom edge, and the right margin relative to the bottom right corner of the node's parent. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: PRESET_VCENTER_WIDE
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to a vertical line that cuts the parent container in half. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: PRESET_HCENTER_WIDE
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to a horizontal line that cuts the parent container in half. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: PRESET_WIDE
constants.description: Snap all 4 anchors to the respective corners of the parent container. Set all 4 margins to 0 after you applied this preset and the [code]Control[/code] will fit its parent container. Use with [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: SIZE_FILL
constants.description: Tells the parent [Container] to expand the bounds of this node to fill all the available space without pushing any other node. Use with [member size_flags_horizontal] and [member size_flags_vertical].

constants.name: SIZE_EXPAND
constants.description: Tells the parent [Container] to let this node take all the available space on the axis you flag. If multiple neighboring nodes are set to expand, they'll share the space based on their stretch ratio. See [member size_flags_stretch_ratio]. Use with [member size_flags_horizontal] and [member size_flags_vertical].

constants.name: SIZE_EXPAND_FILL
constants.description: Sets the node's size flags to both fill and expand. See the 2 constants above for more information.

constants.name: SIZE_SHRINK_CENTER
constants.description: Tells the parent [Container] to center the node in itself. It centers the [code]Control[/code] based on its bounding box, so it doesn't work with the fill or expand size flags. Use with [member size_flags_horizontal] and [member size_flags_vertical].

constants.name: SIZE_SHRINK_END
constants.description: Tells the parent [Container] to align the node with its end, either the bottom or the right edge. It doesn't work with the fill or expand size flags. Use with [member size_flags_horizontal] and [member size_flags_vertical].

constants.name: MOUSE_FILTER_STOP
constants.description: The control will receive mouse button input events through [method _gui_input] if clicked on. These events are automatically marked as handled and they will not propagate further to other controls.

constants.name: MOUSE_FILTER_PASS
constants.description: The control will receive mouse button input events through [method _gui_input] if clicked on. If this control does not handle the event, the parent control (if any) will be considered for a mouse click, and so on until there is no more parent control to potentially handle it. Even if no control handled it at all, the event will still be handled automatically.

constants.name: MOUSE_FILTER_IGNORE
constants.description: The control will not receive mouse button input events through [method _gui_input] and will not block other controls from receiving these events. These events will also not be handled automatically.

constants.name: ANCHOR_BEGIN
constants.description: Snaps one of the 4 anchor's sides to the origin of the node's [code]Rect[/code], in the top left. Use it with one of the [code]anchor_*[/code] member variables, like [member anchor_left]. To change all 4 anchors at once, use [method set_anchors_preset].

constants.name: ANCHOR_END
constants.description: Snaps one of the 4 anchor's sides to the end of the node's [code]Rect[/code], in the bottom right. Use it with one of the [code]anchor_*[/code] member variables, like [member anchor_left]. To change all 4 anchors at once, use [method set_anchors_preset].

properties.name: anchor_bottom
properties.description: Anchors the bottom edge of the node to the origin, the center, or the end of its parent container. It changes how the bottom margin updates when the node moves or changes size. Use one of the [code]ANCHOR_*[/code] constants. Default value: [code]ANCHOR_BEGIN[/code].

properties.name: anchor_left
properties.description: Anchors the left edge of the node to the origin, the center or the end of its parent container. It changes how the left margin updates when the node moves or changes size. Use one of the [code]ANCHOR_*[/code] constants. Default value: [code]ANCHOR_BEGIN[/code].

properties.name: anchor_right
properties.description: Anchors the right edge of the node to the origin, the center or the end of its parent container. It changes how the right margin updates when the node moves or changes size. Use one of the [code]ANCHOR_*[/code] constants. Default value: [code]ANCHOR_BEGIN[/code].

properties.name: anchor_top
properties.description: Anchors the top edge of the node to the origin, the center or the end of its parent container. It changes how the top margin updates when the node moves or changes size. Use one of the [code]ANCHOR_*[/code] constants. Default value: [code]ANCHOR_BEGIN[/code].

properties.name: focus_mode
properties.description: The focus access mode for the control (None, Click or All). Only one Control can be focused at the same time, and it will receive keyboard signals.

properties.name: focus_neighbour_bottom
properties.description:
Tells Godot which node it should give keyboard focus to if the user presses Tab, the down arrow on the keyboard, or down on a gamepad. The node must be a [code]Control[/code]. If this property is not set, Godot will give focus to the closest [code]Control[/code] to the bottom of this one.
			If the user presses Tab, Godot will give focus to the closest node to the right first, then to the bottom. If the user presses Shift+Tab, Godot will look to the left of the node, then above it.

properties.name: focus_neighbour_left
properties.description: Tells Godot which node it should give keyboard focus to if the user presses Shift+Tab, the left arrow on the keyboard or left on a gamepad. The node must be a [code]Control[/code]. If this property is not set, Godot will give focus to the closest [code]Control[/code] to the left of this one.

properties.name: focus_neighbour_right
properties.description: Tells Godot which node it should give keyboard focus to if the user presses Tab, the right arrow on the keyboard or right on a gamepad. The node must be a [code]Control[/code]. If this property is not set, Godot will give focus to the closest [code]Control[/code] to the bottom of this one.

properties.name: focus_neighbour_top
properties.description: Tells Godot which node it should give keyboard focus to if the user presses Shift+Tab, the top arrow on the keyboard or top on a gamepad. The node must be a [code]Control[/code]. If this property is not set, Godot will give focus to the closest [code]Control[/code] to the bottom of this one.

properties.name: hint_tooltip
properties.description: Changes the tooltip text. The tooltip appears when the user's mouse cursor stays idle over this control for a few moments.

properties.name: margin_bottom
properties.description:
Distance between the node's bottom edge and its parent container, based on [member anchor_bottom].
			Margins are often controlled by one or multiple parent [Container] nodes. Margins update automatically when you move or resize the node.

properties.name: margin_left
properties.description: Distance between the node's left edge and its parent container, based on [member anchor_left].

properties.name: margin_right
properties.description: Distance between the node's right edge and its parent container, based on [member anchor_right].

properties.name: margin_top
properties.description: Distance between the node's top edge and its parent container, based on [member anchor_top].

properties.name: mouse_default_cursor_shape
properties.description: The default cursor shape for this control. Useful for Godot plugins and applications or games that use the system's mouse cursors.

properties.name: mouse_filter
properties.description: Controls whether the control will be able to receive mouse button input events through [method _gui_input] and how these events should be handled. Use one of the [code]MOUSE_FILTER_*[/code] constants. See the constants to learn what each does.

properties.name: rect_global_position
properties.description: The node's global position, relative to the world (usually to the top-left corner of the window).

properties.name: rect_min_size
properties.description: The minimum size of the node's bounding rectangle. If you set it to a value greater than (0, 0), the node's bounding rectangle will always have at least this size, even if its content is smaller. If it's set to (0, 0), the node sizes automatically to fit its content, be it a texture or child nodes.

properties.name: rect_pivot_offset
properties.description: By default, the node's pivot is its top-left corner. When you change its [member rect_scale], it will scale around this pivot. Set this property to [member rect_size] / 2 to center the pivot in the node's rectangle.

properties.name: rect_position
properties.description: The node's position, relative to its parent. It corresponds to the rectangle's top-left corner. The property is not affected by [member rect_pivot_offset].

properties.name: rect_rotation
properties.description: The node's rotation around its pivot, in degrees. See [member rect_pivot_offset] to change the pivot's position.

properties.name: rect_scale
properties.description: The node's scale, relative to its [member rect_size]. Change this property to scale the node around its [member rect_pivot_offset].

properties.name: rect_size
properties.description: The size of the node's bounding rectangle, in pixels. [Container] nodes update this property automatically.

properties.name: size_flags_horizontal
properties.description: Tells the parent [Container] nodes how they should resize and place the node on the X axis. Use one of the [code]SIZE_*[/code] constants to change the flags. See the constants to learn what each does.

properties.name: size_flags_stretch_ratio
properties.description: If the node and at least one of its neighbours uses the [code]SIZE_EXPAND[/code] size flag, the parent [Container] will let it take more or less space depending on this property. If this node has a stretch ratio of 2 and its neighbour a ratio of 1, this node will take two thirds of the available space.

properties.name: size_flags_vertical
properties.description: Tells the parent [Container] nodes how they should resize and place the node on the Y axis. Use one of the [code]SIZE_*[/code] constants to change the flags. See the constants to learn what each does.

properties.name: theme
properties.description: Changing this property replaces the current [Theme] resource this node and all its [code]Control[/code] children use.

InputEventJoypadButton.name: InputEventJoypadButton
InputEventJoypadButton.description: Input event type for gamepad buttons. For joysticks see [InputEventJoypadMotion].

properties.name: button_index
properties.description: Button identifier. One of the [code]JOY_BUTTON_*[/code] constants from [@global Scope].

properties.name: pressed
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the button's state is pressed. If [code]false[/code] the button's state is released.

properties.name: pressure
properties.description: Represents the pressure the user puts on the button with his finger, if the controller supports it. Ranges from [code]0[/code] to [code]1[/code].

Thread.name: Thread
Thread.brief_description: A unit of execution in a process.
Thread.description: A unit of execution in a process. Can run methods on [Object]s simultaneously. The use of synchronization via [Mutex], [Semaphore] is advised if working with shared objects.

methods.name: get_id
methods.description: Returns the current [code]Thread[/code]s id, uniquely identifying it among all threads.

methods.name: is_active
methods.description: Returns true if this [code]Thread[/code] is currently active. An active [code]Thread[/code] cannot start work on a new method but can be joined with [method wait_to_finish].

methods.name: start
methods.description:
Starts a new [code]Thread[/code] that runs "method" on object "instance" with "userdata" passed as an argument. The "priority" of the [code]Thread[/code] can be changed by passing a PRIORITY_* enum.
				Returns OK on success, or ERR_CANT_CREATE on failure.

methods.name: wait_to_finish
methods.description: Joins the [code]Thread[/code] and waits for it to finish. Returns what the method called returned.

OmniLight.name: OmniLight
OmniLight.brief_description: OmniDirectional Light, such as a light bulb or a candle.
OmniLight.description: An OmniDirectional light is a type of [Light] node that emits lights in all directions. The light is attenuated through the distance and this attenuation can be configured by changing the energy, radius and attenuation parameters of [Light].

ARVRInterfaceGDNative.name: ARVRInterfaceGDNative
ARVRInterfaceGDNative.brief_description: GDNative wrapper for an ARVR interface
ARVRInterfaceGDNative.description: This is a wrapper class for GDNative implementations of the ARVR interface. To use a GDNative ARVR interface simply instantiate this object and set your GDNative library containing the ARVR interface implementation.

ItemList.name: ItemList
ItemList.brief_description: Control that provides a list of selectable items (and/or icons) in a single column, or optionally in multiple columns.
ItemList.description:
This control provides a selectable list of items that may be in a single (or multiple columns) with option of text, icons,
		or both text and icon.  Tooltips are supported and may be different for every item in the list.  Selectable items in the list
		may be selected or deselected and multiple selection may be enabled.  Selection with right mouse button may also be enabled
		to allow use of popup context menus.  Items may also be 'activated' with a double click (or Enter key).

methods.name: add_icon_item
methods.description: Adds an item to the item list with no text, only an icon.

methods.name: add_item
methods.description:
Adds an item to the item list with specified text.  Specify an icon of null for a list item with no icon.
				If selectable is true the list item will be selectable.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Remove all items from the list.

methods.name: ensure_current_is_visible
methods.description: Ensure selection is visible, adjusting the scroll position as necessary.

methods.name: get_item_at_position
methods.description: Given a position within the control return the item (if any) at that point.

methods.name: get_item_count
methods.description: Return count of items currently in the item list.

methods.name: get_item_text
methods.description: Return the text for specified item index.

methods.name: get_item_tooltip
methods.description: Return tooltip hint for specified item index.

methods.name: get_selected_items
methods.description: Returns the list of selected indexes.

methods.name: get_v_scroll
methods.description: Returns the current vertical scroll bar for the List.

methods.name: is_item_disabled
methods.description: Returns whether or not the item at the specified index is disabled

methods.name: is_item_selectable
methods.description: Returns whether or not the item at the specified index is selectable.

methods.name: is_item_tooltip_enabled
methods.description: Returns whether the tooltip is enabled for specified item index.

methods.name: is_selected
methods.description: Returns whether or not item at the specified index is currently selected.

methods.name: remove_item
methods.description: Remove item at specified index from the list.

methods.name: select
methods.description:
Select the item at the specified index.
				Note:  This method does not trigger the item selection signal.

methods.name: set_item_disabled
methods.description:
Disable (or enable) item at specified index.
				Disabled items are not be selectable and do not fire activation (Enter or double-click) signals.

methods.name: set_item_icon
methods.description: Set (or replace) icon of the item at the specified index.

methods.name: set_item_metadata
methods.description: Sets a value (of any type) to be stored with the item at the specified index.

methods.name: set_item_selectable
methods.description: Allow or disallow selection of the item at the specified index.

methods.name: set_item_text
methods.description: Sets text of item at specified index.

methods.name: set_item_tooltip
methods.description: Sets tooltip hint for item at specified index.

methods.name: set_item_tooltip_enabled
methods.description: Sets whether the tooltip is enabled for specified item index.

methods.name: sort_items_by_text
methods.description: Sorts items in the list by their text.

methods.name: unselect
methods.description: Ensure item at specified index is not selected.

signals.name: item_activated
signals.description: Fired when specified list item is activated via double click or Enter.

signals.name: item_rmb_selected
signals.description:
Fired when specified list item has been selected via right mouse clicking.
				The click position is also provided to allow appropriate popup of context menus
				at the correct location.

signals.name: item_selected
signals.description: Fired when specified item has been selected.

signals.name: multi_selected
signals.description: Fired when a multiple selection is altered on a list allowing multiple selection.

Font.name: Font
Font.brief_description: Internationalized font and text drawing support.
Font.description: Font contains a unicode compatible character set, as well as the ability to draw it with variable width, ascent, descent and kerning. For creating fonts from TTF files (or other font formats), see the editor support for fonts. TODO check wikipedia for graph of ascent/baseline/descent/height/etc.

methods.name: draw
methods.description: Draw "string" into a canvas item using the font at a given position, with "modulate" color, and optionally clipping the width. "position" specifies the baseline, not the top. To draw from the top, [i]ascent[/i] must be added to the Y axis.

methods.name: draw_char
methods.description: Draw character "char" into a canvas item using the font at a given position, with "modulate" color, and optionally kerning if "next" is passed. clipping the width. "position" specifies the baseline, not the top. To draw from the top, [i]ascent[/i] must be added to the Y axis. The width used by the character is returned, making this function useful for drawing strings character by character.

methods.name: get_ascent
methods.description: Return the font ascent (number of pixels above the baseline).

methods.name: get_descent
methods.description: Return the font descent (number of pixels below the baseline).

methods.name: get_height
methods.description: Return the total font height (ascent plus descent) in pixels.

methods.name: get_string_size
methods.description: Return the size of a string, taking kerning and advance into account.

methods.name: update_changes
methods.description: After editing a font (changing size, ascent, char rects, etc.). Call this function to propagate changes to controls that might use it.

AudioEffectFilter.name: AudioEffectFilter
AudioEffectFilter.brief_description: Adds a filter to the Audio Bus.
AudioEffectFilter.description: Allows frequencies other than the [member cutoff_hz] to pass.

properties.name: cutoff_hz
properties.description: Threshold frequency for the filter.

properties.name: gain
properties.description: Gain amount of the frequencies after the filter.

properties.name: resonance
properties.description: Amount of boost in the overtones near the cutoff frequency.

RayShape.name: RayShape
RayShape.description: Ray shape for 3D collisions, which can be set into a [PhysicsBody] or [Area]. A ray is not really a collision body, instead it tries to separate itself from whatever is touching its far endpoint. It's often useful for characters.

properties.name: length
properties.description: The ray's length.

KinematicCollision.name: KinematicCollision
KinematicCollision.description:
Contains collision data for KinematicBody collisions. When a [KinematicBody] is moved using [method KinematicBody.move_and_collide], it stops if it detects a collision with another body. If a collision is detected, a KinematicCollision object is returned.
		This object contains information about the collision, including the colliding object, the remaining motion, and the collision position. This information can be used to calculate a collision response.

properties.name: collider
properties.description: The colliding body.

properties.name: collider_id
properties.description: The colliding body's unique [RID].

properties.name: collider_metadata
properties.description: The colliding body's metadata. See [Object].

properties.name: collider_shape
properties.description: The colliding body's shape.

properties.name: collider_shape_index
properties.description: The colliding shape's index. See [CollisionObject].

properties.name: collider_velocity
properties.description: The colliding object's velocity.

properties.name: local_shape
properties.description: The moving object's colliding shape.

properties.name: normal
properties.description: The colliding body's shape's normal at the point of collision.

properties.name: position
properties.description: The point of collision.

properties.name: remainder
properties.description: The moving object's remaining movement vector.

properties.name: travel
properties.description: The distance the moving object traveled before collision.

VisualScriptComment.name: VisualScriptComment
VisualScriptComment.brief_description: A Visual Script node used to annotate the script.
VisualScriptComment.description:
A Visual Script node used to display annotations in the script, so that code may be documented.
		Comment nodes can be resized so they encompass a group of nodes.

properties.name: description
properties.description: The text inside the comment node.

properties.name: size
properties.description: The comment node's size (in pixels).

properties.name: title
properties.description: The comment node's title.

EditorResourcePreviewGenerator.name: EditorResourcePreviewGenerator
EditorResourcePreviewGenerator.description: Custom code to generate previews. Please check "file_dialog/thumbnail_size" in EditorSettings to find out the right size to do previews at.

methods.name: generate
methods.description:
Generate a preview from a given resource. This must be always implemented.
			Returning an empty texture is an OK way to fail and let another generator take care.
			Care must be taken because this function is always called from a thread (not the main thread).

methods.name: generate_from_path
methods.description:
Generate a preview directly from a path, implementing this is optional, as default code will load and call generate()
			Returning an empty texture is an OK way to fail and let another generator take care.
			Care must be taken because this function is always called from a thread (not the main thread).

methods.name: handles
methods.description: Return if your generator supports this resource type.

ColorRect.name: ColorRect
ColorRect.description: An object that is represented on the canvas as a rect with color. [Color] is used to set or get color info for the rect.

properties.name: color
properties.description:
The color to fill the [code]ColorRect[/code].
			[codeblock]
			$ColorRect.color = Color(1, 0, 0, 1) # Set ColorRect node's color to red
			[/codeblock]

File.name: File
File.brief_description: Type to handle file reading and writing operations.

methods.name: close
methods.description: Closes the currently opened file.

methods.name: eof_reached
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the file cursor has reached the end of the file.

methods.name: file_exists
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the file exists in the given path.

methods.name: get_16
methods.description: Returns the next 16 bits from the file as an integer.

methods.name: get_32
methods.description: Returns the next 32 bits from the file as an integer.

methods.name: get_64
methods.description: Returns the next 64 bits from the file as an integer.

methods.name: get_8
methods.description: Returns the next 8 bits from the file as an integer.

methods.name: get_as_text
methods.description: Returns the whole file as a [String].

methods.name: get_buffer
methods.description: Returns next [code]len[/code] bytes of the file as a [PoolByteArray].

methods.name: get_csv_line
methods.description: Returns the next value of the file in CSV (Comma Separated Values) format. You can pass a different delimiter to use other than the default "," (comma).

methods.name: get_double
methods.description: Returns the next 64 bits from the file as a floating point number.

methods.name: get_error
methods.description: Returns the last error that happened when trying to perform operations. Compare with the [code]ERR_FILE_*[/code] constants from [@GlobalScope].

methods.name: get_float
methods.description: Returns the next 32 bits from the file as a floating point number.

methods.name: get_len
methods.description: Returns the size of the file in bytes.

methods.name: get_line
methods.description: Returns the next line of the file as a [String].

methods.name: get_md5
methods.description: Returns an MD5 String representing the file at the given path or an empty [String] on failure.

methods.name: get_modified_time
methods.description: Returns the last time the [code]file[/code] was modified in unix timestamp format or returns a [String] "ERROR IN [code]file[/code]". This unix timestamp can be converted to datetime by using [method OS.get_datetime_from_unix_time].

methods.name: get_pascal_string
methods.description: Returns a [String] saved in Pascal format from the file.

methods.name: get_position
methods.description: Returns the file cursor's position.

methods.name: get_real
methods.description: Returns the next bits from the file as a floating point number.

methods.name: get_sha256
methods.description: Returns a SHA-256 [String] representing the file at the given path or an empty [String] on failure.

methods.name: get_var
methods.description: Returns the next [Variant] value from the file.

methods.name: is_open
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the file is currently opened.

methods.name: open
methods.description: Opens the file for writing or reading, depending on the flags.

methods.name: open_compressed
methods.description: Opens a compressed file for reading or writing. Use COMPRESSION_* constants to set [code]compression_mode[/code].

methods.name: open_encrypted
methods.description: Opens an encrypted file in write or read mode. You need to pass a binary key to encrypt/decrypt it.

methods.name: open_encrypted_with_pass
methods.description: Opens an encrypted file in write or read mode. You need to pass a password to encrypt/decrypt it.

methods.name: seek
methods.description: Change the file reading/writing cursor to the specified position (in bytes from the beginning of the file).

methods.name: seek_end
methods.description: Changes the file reading/writing cursor to the specified position (in bytes from the end of the file). Note that this is an offset, so you should use negative numbers or the cursor will be at the end of the file.

methods.name: store_16
methods.description: Stores an integer as 16 bits in the file.

methods.name: store_32
methods.description: Stores an integer as 32 bits in the file.

methods.name: store_64
methods.description: Stores an integer as 64 bits in the file.

methods.name: store_8
methods.description: Stores an integer as 8 bits in the file.

methods.name: store_buffer
methods.description: Stores the given array of bytes in the file.

methods.name: store_double
methods.description: Stores a floating point number as 64 bits in the file.

methods.name: store_float
methods.description: Stores a floating point number as 32 bits in the file.

methods.name: store_line
methods.description: Stores the given [String] as a line in the file.

methods.name: store_pascal_string
methods.description: Stores the given [String] as a line in the file in Pascal format (i.e. also store the length of the string).

methods.name: store_real
methods.description: Stores a floating point number in the file.

methods.name: store_string
methods.description: Stores the given [String] in the file.

methods.name: store_var
methods.description: Stores any Variant value in the file.

constants.name: READ
constants.description: Opens the file for read operations.

constants.name: WRITE
constants.description: Opens the file for write operations. Create it if the file does not exist and truncate if it exists.

constants.name: READ_WRITE
constants.description: Opens the file for read and write operations. Does not truncate the file.

constants.name: WRITE_READ
constants.description: Opens the file for read and write operations. Create it if the file does not exist and truncate if it exists.

constants.name: COMPRESSION_FASTLZ
constants.description: Uses the FastLZ compression method.

constants.name: COMPRESSION_DEFLATE
constants.description: Uses the Deflate compression method.

constants.name: COMPRESSION_ZSTD
constants.description: Uses the Zstd compression method.

constants.name: COMPRESSION_GZIP
constants.description: Uses the gzip compression method.

properties.name: endian_swap
properties.description:
If [code]true[/code] the file's endianness is swapped. Use this if you're dealing with files written in big endian machines.
			Note that this is about the file format, not CPU type. This is always reseted to [code]false[/code] whenever you open the file.

StreamPeer.name: StreamPeer
StreamPeer.brief_description: Abstraction and base class for stream-based protocols.
StreamPeer.description: StreamPeer is an abstraction and base class for stream-based protocols (such as TCP or Unix Sockets). It provides an API for sending and receiving data through streams as raw data or strings.

methods.name: get_16
methods.description: Get a signed 16 bit value from the stream.

methods.name: get_32
methods.description: Get a signed 32 bit value from the stream.

methods.name: get_64
methods.description: Get a signed 64 bit value from the stream.

methods.name: get_8
methods.description: Get a signed byte from the stream.

methods.name: get_available_bytes
methods.description: Return the amount of bytes this [code]StreamPeer[/code] has available.

methods.name: get_data
methods.description: Return a chunk data with the received bytes. The amount of bytes to be received can be requested in the "bytes" argument. If not enough bytes are available, the function will block until the desired amount is received. This function returns two values, an Error code and a data array.

methods.name: get_double
methods.description: Get a double-precision float from the stream.

methods.name: get_float
methods.description: Get a single-precision float from the stream.

methods.name: get_partial_data
methods.description: Return a chunk data with the received bytes. The amount of bytes to be received can be requested in the "bytes" argument. If not enough bytes are available, the function will return how many were actually received. This function returns two values, an Error code, and a data array.

methods.name: get_string
methods.description: Get a string with byte-length "bytes" from the stream.

methods.name: get_u16
methods.description: Get an unsigned 16 bit value from the stream.

methods.name: get_u32
methods.description: Get an unsigned 32 bit value from the stream.

methods.name: get_u64
methods.description: Get an unsigned 64 bit value from the stream.

methods.name: get_u8
methods.description: Get an unsigned byte from the stream.

methods.name: get_utf8_string
methods.description: Get a utf8 string with byte-length "bytes" from the stream (this decodes the string sent as utf8).

methods.name: get_var
methods.description: Get a Variant from the stream.

methods.name: put_16
methods.description: Put a signed 16 bit value into the stream.

methods.name: put_32
methods.description: Put a signed 32 bit value into the stream.

methods.name: put_64
methods.description: Put a signed 64 bit value into the stream.

methods.name: put_8
methods.description: Put a signed byte into the stream.

methods.name: put_data
methods.description: Send a chunk of data through the connection, blocking if necessary until the data is done sending. This function returns an Error code.

methods.name: put_double
methods.description: Put a double-precision float into the stream.

methods.name: put_float
methods.description: Put a single-precision float into the stream.

methods.name: put_partial_data
methods.description: Send a chunk of data through the connection, if all the data could not be sent at once, only part of it will. This function returns two values, an Error code and an integer, describing how much data was actually sent.

methods.name: put_u16
methods.description: Put an unsigned 16 bit value into the stream.

methods.name: put_u32
methods.description: Put an unsigned 32 bit value into the stream.

methods.name: put_u64
methods.description: Put an unsigned 64 bit value into the stream.

methods.name: put_u8
methods.description: Put an unsigned byte into the stream.

methods.name: put_utf8_string
methods.description: Put a zero-terminated utf8 string into the stream.

methods.name: put_var
methods.description: Put a Variant into the stream.

properties.name: big_endian
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], this [code]StreamPeer[/code] will using big-endian format for encoding and decoding.

Vector3.name: Vector3
Vector3.brief_description: Vector class, which performs basic 3D vector math operations.
Vector3.description: Vector3 is one of the core classes of the engine, and includes several built-in helper functions to perform basic vector math operations.

methods.name: Vector3
methods.description: Returns a Vector3 with the given components.

methods.name: abs
methods.description: Returns a new vector with all components in absolute values (i.e. positive).

methods.name: angle_to
methods.description: Returns the vector's minimum angle to the vector [code]to[/code].

methods.name: bounce
methods.description: Bounce returns the vector "bounced off" from the given plane, specified by its normal vector.

methods.name: ceil
methods.description: Returns a new vector with all components rounded up.

methods.name: cross
methods.description: Returns the cross product with [code]b[/code].

methods.name: cubic_interpolate
methods.description: Performs a cubic interpolation between vectors [code]pre_a[/code], [code]a[/code], [code]b[/code], [code]post_b[/code] ([code]a[/code] is current), by the given amount (t). (t) should be a float of 0.0-1.0, a percentage of how far along the interpolation is.

methods.name: distance_squared_to
methods.description: Returns the squared distance to [code]b[/code]. Prefer this function over distance_to if you need to sort vectors or need the squared distance for some formula.

methods.name: distance_to
methods.description: Returns the distance to b.

methods.name: dot
methods.description: Returns the dot product with b.

methods.name: floor
methods.description: Returns a new vector with all components rounded down.

methods.name: inverse
methods.description: Returns the inverse of the vector. This is the same as Vector3( 1.0 / v.x, 1.0 / v.y, 1.0 / v.z )

methods.name: is_normalized
methods.description: Returns whether the vector is normalized or not.

methods.name: length
methods.description: Returns the length of the vector.

methods.name: length_squared
methods.description: Returns the length of the vector, squared. Prefer this function over "length" if you need to sort vectors or need the squared length for some formula.

methods.name: linear_interpolate
methods.description: Linearly interpolates the vector to a given one (b), by the given amount (t). (t) should be a float of 0.0-1.0, a percentage of how far along the interpolation is.

methods.name: max_axis
methods.description: Returns AXIS_X, AXIS_Y or AXIS_Z depending on which axis is the largest.

methods.name: min_axis
methods.description: Returns AXIS_X, AXIS_Y or AXIS_Z depending on which axis is the smallest.

methods.name: normalized
methods.description: Returns a copy of the normalized vector to unit length. This is the same as v / v.length().

methods.name: outer
methods.description: Returns the outer product with b.

methods.name: reflect
methods.description: Reflects the vector along the given plane, specified by its normal vector.

methods.name: rotated
methods.description: Rotates the vector around some axis by phi radians. The axis must be a normalized vector.

methods.name: slide
methods.description: Slide returns the component of the vector along the given plane, specified by its normal vector.

methods.name: snapped
methods.description: Returns a copy of the vector, snapped to the lowest neared multiple.

methods.name: to_diagonal_matrix
methods.description: Returns a diagonal matrix with the vector as main diagonal.

constants.name: AXIS_X
constants.description: Enumerated value for the X axis. Returned by functions like max_axis or min_axis.

constants.name: AXIS_Y
constants.description: Enumerated value for the Y axis.

constants.name: AXIS_Z
constants.description: Enumerated value for the Z axis.

properties.name: x
properties.description: X component of the vector.

properties.name: y
properties.description: Y component of the vector.

properties.name: z
properties.description: Z component of the vector.

PrimitiveMesh.name: PrimitiveMesh
PrimitiveMesh.brief_description: Base class for all primitive meshes. Handles applying a [Material] to a primitive mesh.
PrimitiveMesh.description: Base class for all primitive meshes. Handles applying a [Material] to a primitive mesh.

properties.name: material
properties.description: The current [Material] of the primitive mesh.

Node2D.name: Node2D
Node2D.brief_description: A 2D game object, parent of all 2D related nodes. Has a position, rotation, scale and Z-index.
Node2D.description: A 2D game object, with a position, rotation and scale. All 2D physics nodes and sprites inherit from Node2D. Use Node2D as a parent node to move, scale and rotate children in a 2D project. Also gives control on the node's render order.

methods.name: apply_scale
methods.description: Multiplies the current scale by the 'ratio' vector.

methods.name: get_angle_to
methods.description: Returns the angle between the node and the 'point' in radians.

methods.name: get_relative_transform_to_parent
methods.description: Returns the [Transform2D] relative to this node's parent.

methods.name: global_translate
methods.description: Adds the 'offset' vector to the node's global position.

methods.name: look_at
methods.description: Rotates the node so it points towards the 'point'.

methods.name: move_local_x
methods.description: Applies a local translation on the node's X axis based on the [method Node._process]'s [code]delta[/code]. If [code]scaled[/code] is false, normalizes the movement.

methods.name: move_local_y
methods.description: Applies a local translation on the node's Y axis based on the [method Node._process]'s [code]delta[/code]. If [code]scaled[/code] is false, normalizes the movement.

methods.name: rotate
methods.description: Applies a rotation to the node, in radians, starting from its current rotation.

methods.name: to_global
methods.description: Converts a local point's coordinates to global coordinates.

methods.name: to_local
methods.description: Converts a global point's coordinates to local coordinates.

methods.name: translate
methods.description: Translates the node by the given [code]offset[/code] in local coordinates.

properties.name: global_position
properties.description: Global position.

properties.name: global_rotation
properties.description: Global rotation in radians.

properties.name: global_rotation_degrees
properties.description: Global rotation in degrees.

properties.name: global_scale
properties.description: Global scale.

properties.name: global_transform
properties.description: Global [Transform2D].

properties.name: position
properties.description: Position, relative to the node's parent.

properties.name: rotation
properties.description: Rotation in radians, relative to the node's parent.

properties.name: rotation_degrees
properties.description: Rotation in degrees, relative to the node's parent.

properties.name: scale
properties.description: The node's scale. Unscaled value: [code](1, 1)[/code]

properties.name: transform
properties.description: Local [Transform2D].

properties.name: z_as_relative
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the node's Z-index is relative to its parent's Z-index. If this node's Z-index is 2 and its parent's effective Z-index is 3, then this node's effective Z-index will be 2 + 3 = 5.

properties.name: z_index
properties.description: Z-index. Controls the order in which the nodes render. A node with a higher Z-index will display in front of others.

StyleBoxEmpty.name: StyleBoxEmpty
StyleBoxEmpty.description: Empty stylebox (really does not display anything).

Vector2.name: Vector2
Vector2.description: 2-element structure that can be used to represent positions in 2d-space, or any other pair of numeric values.

methods.name: Vector2
methods.description: Constructs a new Vector2 from the given x and y.

methods.name: abs
methods.description: Returns a new vector with all components in absolute values (i.e. positive).

methods.name: angle
methods.description:
Returns the result of atan2 when called with the Vector's x and y as parameters (Math::atan2(x,y)).
				Be aware that it therefore returns an angle oriented clockwise with regard to the (0, 1) unit vector, and not an angle oriented counter-clockwise with regard to the (1, 0) unit vector (which would be the typical trigonometric representation of the angle when calling Math::atan2(y,x)).

methods.name: angle_to
methods.description: Returns the angle in radians between the two vectors.

methods.name: angle_to_point
methods.description: Returns the angle in radians between the line connecting the two points and the x coordinate.

methods.name: aspect
methods.description: Returns the ratio of X to Y.

methods.name: bounce
methods.description: Bounce returns the vector "bounced off" from the given plane, specified by its normal vector.

methods.name: clamped
methods.description: Returns the vector with a maximum length.

methods.name: cubic_interpolate
methods.description: Cubicly interpolates between this Vector and "b", using "pre_a" and "post_b" as handles, and returning the result at position "t". "t" should be a float of 0.0-1.0, a percentage of how far along the interpolation is.

methods.name: distance_squared_to
methods.description: Returns the squared distance to vector "b". Prefer this function over "distance_to" if you need to sort vectors or need the squared distance for some formula.

methods.name: distance_to
methods.description: Returns the distance to vector "b".

methods.name: dot
methods.description: Returns the dot product with vector "b".

methods.name: floor
methods.description: Remove the fractional part of x and y.

methods.name: is_normalized
methods.description: Returns whether the vector is normalized or not.

methods.name: length
methods.description: Returns the length of the vector.

methods.name: length_squared
methods.description: Returns the squared length of the vector. Prefer this function over "length" if you need to sort vectors or need the squared length for some formula.

methods.name: linear_interpolate
methods.description: Returns the result of the linear interpolation between this vector and "b", by amount "t". "t" should be a float of 0.0-1.0, a percentage of how far along the interpolation is.

methods.name: normalized
methods.description: Returns a normalized vector to unit length.

methods.name: reflect
methods.description: Reflects the vector along the given plane, specified by its normal vector.

methods.name: rotated
methods.description: Rotates the vector by "phi" radians.

methods.name: slide
methods.description: Slide returns the component of the vector along the given plane, specified by its normal vector.

methods.name: snapped
methods.description: Snaps the vector to a grid with the given size.

methods.name: tangent
methods.description: Returns a perpendicular vector.

properties.name: x
properties.description: X component of the vector.

properties.name: y
properties.description: Y component of the vector.

HScrollBar.name: HScrollBar
HScrollBar.description: Horizontal scroll bar. See [ScrollBar]. This one goes from left (min) to right (max).

StyleBox.name: StyleBox
StyleBox.brief_description: Base class for drawing stylized boxes for the UI.
StyleBox.description: StyleBox is [Resource] that provides an abstract base class for drawing stylized boxes for the UI. StyleBoxes are used for drawing the styles of buttons, line edit backgrounds, tree backgrounds, etc. and also for testing a transparency mask for pointer signals. If mask test fails on a StyleBox assigned as mask to a control, clicks and motion signals will go through it to the one below.

methods.name: get_margin
methods.description: Return the offset of margin "margin" (see MARGIN_* enum).

methods.name: get_minimum_size
methods.description: Return the minimum size that this stylebox can be shrunk to.

methods.name: get_offset
methods.description: Return the "offset" of a stylebox, this is a helper function, like writing [code]Vector2(style.get_margin(MARGIN_LEFT), style.get_margin(MARGIN_TOP))[/code].

methods.name: test_mask
methods.description: Test a position in a rectangle, return whether it passes the mask test.

Dictionary.name: Dictionary
Dictionary.description: Dictionary type. Associative container which contains values referenced by unique keys. Dictionaries are always passed by reference.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear the dictionary, removing all key/value pairs.

methods.name: empty
methods.description: Return true if the dictionary is empty.

methods.name: erase
methods.description: Erase a dictionary key/value pair by key.

methods.name: has
methods.description: Return true if the dictionary has a given key.

methods.name: has_all
methods.description: Return true if the dictionary has all of the keys in the given array.

methods.name: hash
methods.description: Return a hashed integer value representing the dictionary contents.

methods.name: keys
methods.description: Return the list of keys in the [code]Dictionary[/code].

methods.name: size
methods.description: Return the size of the dictionary (in pairs).

methods.name: values
methods.description: Return the list of values in the [code]Dictionary[/code].

ProjectSettings.name: ProjectSettings
ProjectSettings.brief_description: Contains global variables accessible from everywhere.
ProjectSettings.description: Contains global variables accessible from everywhere. Use "ProjectSettings.get_setting(variable)", "ProjectSettings.set_setting(variable,value)" or "ProjectSettings.has_setting(variable)" to access them. Variables stored in project.godot are also loaded into ProjectSettings, making this object very useful for reading custom game configuration options.

methods.name: add_property_info
methods.description:
Add a custom property info to a property. The dictionary must contain: name:[String](the name of the property) and type:[int](see TYPE_* in [@GlobalScope]), and optionally hint:[int](see PROPERTY_HINT_* in [@GlobalScope]), hint_string:[String].
				Example:
				[codeblock]
				ProjectSettings.set("category/property_name", 0)

				var property_info = {
				    "name": "category/property_name",
				    "type": TYPE_INT,
				    "hint": PROPERTY_HINT_ENUM,
				    "hint_string": "one,two,three"
				}

				ProjectSettings.add_property_info(property_info)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear the whole configuration (not recommended, may break things).

methods.name: get_order
methods.description: Return the order of a configuration value (influences when saved to the config file).

methods.name: globalize_path
methods.description: Convert a localized path (res://) to a full native OS path.

methods.name: has_setting
methods.description: Return true if a configuration value is present.

methods.name: localize_path
methods.description: Convert a path to a localized path (res:// path).

methods.name: set_order
methods.description: Set the order of a configuration value (influences when saved to the config file).

InputEventScreenTouch.name: InputEventScreenTouch
InputEventScreenTouch.brief_description:
Input event type for screen touch events.
		(only available on mobile devices)
InputEventScreenTouch.description: Stores multi-touch press/release information. Supports touch press, touch release and [member index] for multi-touch count and order.

properties.name: index
properties.description: Touch index in the case of a multi-touch event. One index = one finger.

properties.name: position
properties.description: Touch position.

properties.name: pressed
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the touch's state is pressed. If [code]false[/code] the touch's state is released.

IP.name: IP
IP.brief_description: Internet protocol (IP) support functions like DNS resolution.
IP.description: IP contains support functions for the Internet Protocol (IP). TCP/IP support is in different classes (see [StreamPeerTCP] and [TCP_Server]). IP provides DNS hostname resolution support, both blocking and threaded.

methods.name: clear_cache
methods.description: Removes all of a "hostname"'s cached references. If no "hostname" is given then all cached IP addresses are removed.

methods.name: erase_resolve_item
methods.description: Removes a given item "id" from the queue. This should be used to free a queue after it has completed to enable more queries to happen.

methods.name: get_local_addresses
methods.description: Returns all of the user's current IPv4 and IPv6 addresses as an array.

methods.name: get_resolve_item_address
methods.description: Returns a queued hostname's IP address, given its queue "id". Returns an empty string on error or if resolution hasn't happened yet (see [method get_resolve_item_status]).

methods.name: get_resolve_item_status
methods.description: Returns a queued hostname's status as a RESOLVER_STATUS_* constant, given its queue "id".

methods.name: resolve_hostname
methods.description: Returns a given hostname's IPv4 or IPv6 address when resolved (blocking-type method). The address type returned depends on the TYPE_* constant given as "ip_type".

methods.name: resolve_hostname_queue_item
methods.description: Creates a queue item to resolve a hostname to an IPv4 or IPv6 address depending on the TYPE_* constant given as "ip_type". Returns the queue ID if successful, or RESOLVER_INVALID_ID on error.

constants.name: RESOLVER_STATUS_NONE
constants.description: DNS hostname resolver status: No status.

constants.name: RESOLVER_STATUS_WAITING
constants.description: DNS hostname resolver status: Waiting.

constants.name: RESOLVER_STATUS_DONE
constants.description: DNS hostname resolver status: Done.

constants.name: RESOLVER_STATUS_ERROR
constants.description: DNS hostname resolver status: Error.

constants.name: RESOLVER_MAX_QUERIES
constants.description: Maximum number of concurrent DNS resolver queries allowed, [code]RESOLVER_INVALID_ID[/code] is returned if exceeded.

constants.name: RESOLVER_INVALID_ID
constants.description: Invalid ID constant. Returned if [code]RESOLVER_MAX_QUERIES[/code] is exceeded.

constants.name: TYPE_NONE
constants.description: Address type: None.

constants.name: TYPE_IPV4
constants.description: Address type: Internet protocol version 4 (IPv4).

constants.name: TYPE_IPV6
constants.description: Address type: Internet protocol version 6 (IPv6).

constants.name: TYPE_ANY
constants.description: Address type: Any.

EditorSelection.name: EditorSelection
EditorSelection.brief_description: Manages the SceneTree selection in the editor.
EditorSelection.description: This object manages the SceneTree selection in the editor.

methods.name: add_node
methods.description: Add a node to the selection.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear the selection.

methods.name: get_selected_nodes
methods.description: Get the list of selected nodes.

methods.name: get_transformable_selected_nodes
methods.description: Get the list of selected nodes, optimized for transform operations (ie, moving them, rotating, etc). This list avoids situations where a node is selected and also chid/grandchild.

methods.name: remove_node
methods.description: Remove a node from the selection.

signals.name: selection_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the selection changes.

InputEventAction.name: InputEventAction
InputEventAction.description: Contains a generic action which can be targeted from several type of inputs. Actions can be created from the project settings menu [code]Project > Project Settings > Input Map[/code]. See [method Node._input].

properties.name: action
properties.description: The action's name. Actions are accessed via this [String].

properties.name: pressed
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the action's state is pressed. If [code]false[/code] the action's state is released.

Plane.name: Plane
Plane.description: Plane represents a normalized plane equation. Basically, "normal" is the normal of the plane (a,b,c normalized), and "d" is the distance from the origin to the plane (in the direction of "normal"). "Over" or "Above" the plane is considered the side of the plane towards where the normal is pointing.

methods.name: Plane
methods.description: Creates a plane from the three parameters "a", "b", "c" and "d".

methods.name: Plane
methods.description: Creates a plane from three points.

methods.name: Plane
methods.description: Creates a plane from the normal and the plane's distance to the origin.

methods.name: center
methods.description: Returns the center of the plane.

methods.name: distance_to
methods.description: Returns the shortest distance from the plane to the position "point".

methods.name: get_any_point
methods.description: Returns a point on the plane.

methods.name: has_point
methods.description: Returns true if "point" is inside the plane (by a very minimum threshold).

methods.name: intersect_3
methods.description: Returns the intersection point of the three planes "b", "c" and this plane. If no intersection is found null is returned.

methods.name: intersects_ray
methods.description: Returns the intersection point of a ray consisting of the position "from" and the direction normal "dir" with this plane. If no intersection is found null is returned.

methods.name: intersects_segment
methods.description: Returns the intersection point of a segment from position "begin" to position "end" with this plane. If no intersection is found null is returned.

methods.name: is_point_over
methods.description: Returns true if "point" is located above the plane.

methods.name: normalized
methods.description: Returns a copy of the plane, normalized.

methods.name: project
methods.description: Returns the orthogonal projection of point "p" into a point in the plane.

PoolByteArray.name: PoolByteArray
PoolByteArray.description: Raw byte array. Contains bytes. Optimized for memory usage, can't fragment the memory.

methods.name: PoolByteArray
methods.description: Create from a generic array.

methods.name: append
methods.description: Append an element at the end of the array (alias of [method push_back]).

methods.name: append_array
methods.description: Append a [code]PoolByteArray[/code] at the end of this array.

methods.name: compress
methods.description: Returns a new [code]PoolByteArray[/code] with the data compressed. Set the compression mode using one of [File]'s COMPRESS_* constants.

methods.name: decompress
methods.description: Returns a new [code]PoolByteArray[/code] with the data decompressed. Set buffer_size to the size of the uncompressed data. Set the compression mode using one of [File]'s COMPRESS_* constants.

methods.name: get_string_from_ascii
methods.description: Returns a copy of the array's contents as [String]. Fast alternative to [method PoolByteArray.get_string_from_utf8] if the content is ASCII-only. Unlike the UTF-8 function this function maps every byte to a character in the array. Multibyte sequences will not be interpreted correctly. For parsing user input always use [method PoolByteArray.get_string_from_utf8].

methods.name: get_string_from_utf8
methods.description: Returns a copy of the array's contents as [String]. Slower than [method PoolByteArray.get_string_from_ascii] but supports UTF-8 encoded data. Use this function if you are unsure about the source of the data. For user input this function should always be preferred.

methods.name: insert
methods.description: Insert a new element at a given position in the array. The position must be valid, or at the end of the array (pos==size()).

methods.name: invert
methods.description: Reverse the order of the elements in the array (so first element will now be the last).

methods.name: push_back
methods.description: Append an element at the end of the array.

methods.name: remove
methods.description: Remove an element from the array by index.

methods.name: resize
methods.description: Set the size of the array. If the array is grown reserve elements at the end of the array. If the array is shrunk truncate the array to the new size.

methods.name: set
methods.description: Change the byte at the given index.

methods.name: size
methods.description: Return the size of the array.

methods.name: subarray
methods.description: Returns the slice of the [code]PoolByteArray[/code] between indices (inclusive) as a new [code]PoolByteArray[/code].  Any negative index is considered to be from the end of the array.

GraphEdit.name: GraphEdit
GraphEdit.brief_description: GraphEdit is an area capable of showing various GraphNodes. It manages connection events between them.
GraphEdit.description:
GraphEdit manages the showing of GraphNodes it contains, as well as connections and disconnections between them. Signals are sent for each of these two events. Disconnection between GraphNodes slots is disabled by default.
		It is greatly advised to enable low processor usage mode (see [method OS.set_low_processor_usage_mode]) when using GraphEdits.

methods.name: connect_node
methods.description: Create a connection between 'from_port' slot of 'from' GraphNode and 'to_port' slot of 'to' GraphNode. If the connection already exists, no connection is created.

methods.name: disconnect_node
methods.description: Remove the connection between 'from_port' slot of 'from' GraphNode and 'to_port' slot of 'to' GraphNode, if connection exists.

methods.name: get_connection_list
methods.description: Return an Array containing the list of connections. A connection consists in a structure of the form {from_slot: 0, from: "GraphNode name 0", to_slot: 1, to: "GraphNode name 1" }

methods.name: is_node_connected
methods.description: Return true if the 'from_port' slot of 'from' GraphNode is connected to the 'to_port' slot of 'to' GraphNode.

signals.name: _begin_node_move
signals.description: Signal sent at the beginning of a GraphNode movement.

signals.name: _end_node_move
signals.description: Signal sent at the end of a GraphNode movement.

signals.name: connection_request
signals.description: Signal sent to the GraphEdit when the connection between 'from_slot' slot of 'from' GraphNode and 'to_slot' slot of 'to' GraphNode is attempted to be created.

signals.name: delete_nodes_request
signals.description: Signal sent when a GraphNode is attempted to be removed from the GraphEdit.

signals.name: disconnection_request
signals.description: Signal sent to the GraphEdit when the connection between 'from_slot' slot of 'from' GraphNode and 'to_slot' slot of 'to' GraphNode is attempted to be removed.

signals.name: duplicate_nodes_request
signals.description: Signal sent when a GraphNode is attempted to be duplicated in the GraphEdit.

signals.name: popup_request
signals.description: Signal sent when a popup is requested. Happens on right-clicking in the GraphEdit. 'p_position' is the position of the mouse pointer when the signal is sent.

properties.name: right_disconnects
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], enables disconnection of existing connections in the GraphEdit by dragging the right end.

properties.name: scroll_offset
properties.description: The scroll offset.

properties.name: snap_distance
properties.description: The snapping distance in pixels.

properties.name: use_snap
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], enables snapping.

PhysicsDirectSpaceState.name: PhysicsDirectSpaceState
PhysicsDirectSpaceState.brief_description: Direct access object to a space in the [PhysicsServer].
PhysicsDirectSpaceState.description: Direct access object to a space in the [PhysicsServer]. It's used mainly to do queries against objects and areas residing in a given space.

methods.name: cast_motion
methods.description:
Checks whether the shape can travel to a point. The method will return an array with two floats between 0 and 1, both representing a fraction of [code]motion[/code]. The first is how far the shape can move without triggering a collision, and the second is the point at which a collision will occur. If no collision is detected, the returned array will be [1, 1].
				If the shape can not move, the array will be empty ([code]dir.empty()==true[/code]).

methods.name: collide_shape
methods.description: Checks the intersections of a shape, given through a [PhysicsShapeQueryParameters] object, against the space. The resulting array contains a list of points where the shape intersects another. Like with [method intersect_shape], the number of returned results can be limited to save processing time.

methods.name: get_rest_info
methods.description:
Checks the intersections of a shape, given through a [PhysicsShapeQueryParameters] object, against the space. If it collides with more than a shape, the nearest one is selected. The returned object is a dictionary containing the following fields:
				[code]collider_id[/code]: The colliding object's ID.
				[code]linear_velocity[/code]: The colliding object's velocity [Vector3]. If the object is an [Area], the result is [code](0, 0, 0)[/code].
				[code]normal[/code]: The object's surface normal at the intersection point.
				[code]point[/code]: The intersection point.
				[code]rid[/code]: The intersecting object's [RID].
				[code]shape[/code]: The shape index of the colliding shape.
				If the shape did not intersect anything, then an empty dictionary ([code]dir.empty()==true[/code]) is returned instead.

methods.name: intersect_ray
methods.description:
Intersects a ray in a given space. The returned object is a dictionary with the following fields:
				[code]collider[/code]: The colliding object.
				[code]collider_id[/code]: The colliding object's ID.
				[code]normal[/code]: The object's surface normal at the intersection point.
				[code]position[/code]: The intersection point.
				[code]rid[/code]: The intersecting object's [RID].
				[code]shape[/code]: The shape index of the colliding shape.
				If the ray did not intersect anything, then an empty dictionary ([code]dir.empty()==true[/code]) is returned instead.
				Additionally, the method can take an array of objects or [RID]s that are to be excluded from collisions, or a bitmask representing the physics layers to check in.

methods.name: intersect_shape
methods.description:
Checks the intersections of a shape, given through a [PhysicsShapeQueryParameters] object, against the space. The intersected shapes are returned in an array containing dictionaries with the following fields:
				[code]collider[/code]: The colliding object.
				[code]collider_id[/code]: The colliding object's ID.
				[code]rid[/code]: The intersecting object's [RID].
				[code]shape[/code]: The shape index of the colliding shape.
				The number of intersections can be limited with the second parameter, to reduce the processing time.

MobileVRInterface.description:
This is a generic mobile VR implementation where you need to provide details about the phone and HMD used. It does not rely on any existing framework. This is the most basic interface we have. For the best effect you do need a mobile phone with a gyroscope and accelerometer.
		Note that even though there is no positional tracking the camera will assume the headset is at a height of 1.85 meters.

properties.name: oversample
