constants.description: Return the input raised to a given power.

constants.name: MATH_LOG
constants.description: Return the natural logarithm of the input. Note that this is not the typical base-10 logarithm function calculators use.

constants.name: MATH_EXP
constants.description: Return [b]e[/b] raised to the power of the input. [b]e[/b] sometimes called "Euler's number" is a mathematical constant whose value is approximately 2.71828.

constants.name: MATH_ISNAN
constants.description: Return whether the input is NaN (Not a Number) or not. NaN is usually produced by dividing 0 by 0, though other ways exist.

constants.name: MATH_ISINF
constants.description: Return whether the input is an infinite floating-point number or not. Infinity is usually produced by dividing a number by 0, though other ways exist.

constants.name: MATH_EASE
constants.description: Easing function, based on exponent. 0 is constant, 1 is linear, 0 to 1 is ease-in, 1+ is ease out. Negative values are in-out/out in.

constants.name: MATH_DECIMALS
constants.description: Return the number of digit places after the decimal that the first non-zero digit occurs.

constants.name: MATH_STEPIFY
constants.description: Return the input snapped to a given step.

constants.name: MATH_LERP
constants.description: Return a number linearly interpolated between the first two inputs, based on the third input. Uses the formula [code]a + (a - b) * t[/code].

constants.name: MATH_DECTIME
constants.description: Return the result of 'value' decreased by 'step' * 'amount'.

constants.name: MATH_RANDOMIZE
constants.description: Randomize the seed (or the internal state) of the random number generator. Current implementation reseeds using a number based on time.

constants.name: MATH_RAND
constants.description: Return a random 32 bits integer value. To obtain a random value between 0 to N (where N is smaller than 2^32 - 1), you can use it with the remainder function.

constants.name: MATH_RANDF
constants.description: Return a random floating-point value between 0 and 1. To obtain a random value between 0 to N, you can use it with multiplication.

constants.name: MATH_RANDOM
constants.description: Return a random floating-point value between the two inputs.

constants.name: MATH_SEED
constants.description: Set the seed for the random number generator.

constants.name: MATH_RANDSEED
constants.description: Return a random value from the given seed, along with the new seed.

constants.name: MATH_DEG2RAD
constants.description: Convert the input from degrees to radians.

constants.name: MATH_RAD2DEG
constants.description: Convert the input from radians to degrees.

constants.name: MATH_LINEAR2DB
constants.description: Convert the input from linear volume to decibel volume.

constants.name: MATH_DB2LINEAR
constants.description: Convert the input from decibel volume to linear volume.

constants.name: MATH_POLAR2CARTESIAN
constants.description: Converts a 2D point expressed in the polar coordinate system (a distance from the origin [code]r[/code] and an angle [code]th[/code]) to the cartesian coordinate system (x and y axis).

constants.name: MATH_CARTESIAN2POLAR
constants.description: Converts a 2D point expressed in the cartesian coordinate system (x and y axis) to the polar coordinate system (a distance from the origin and an angle).

constants.name: LOGIC_MAX
constants.description: Return the greater of the two numbers, also known as their maximum.

constants.name: LOGIC_MIN
constants.description: Return the lesser of the two numbers, also known as their minimum.

constants.name: LOGIC_CLAMP
constants.description: Return the input clamped inside the given range, ensuring the result is never outside it. Equivalent to `min(max(input, range_low), range_high)`

constants.name: LOGIC_NEAREST_PO2
constants.description: Return the nearest power of 2 to the input.

constants.name: OBJ_WEAKREF
constants.description: Create a [WeakRef] from the input.

constants.name: FUNC_FUNCREF
constants.description: Create a [FuncRef] from the input.

constants.name: TYPE_CONVERT
constants.description: Convert between types.

constants.name: TYPE_OF
constants.description: Return the type of the input as an integer. Check [enum Variant.Type] for the integers that might be returned.

constants.name: TYPE_EXISTS
constants.description: Checks if a type is registered in the [ClassDB].

constants.name: TEXT_CHAR
constants.description: Return a character with the given ascii value.

constants.name: TEXT_STR
constants.description: Convert the input to a string.

constants.name: TEXT_PRINT
constants.description: Print the given string to the output window.

constants.name: TEXT_PRINTERR
constants.description: Print the given string to the standard error output.

constants.name: TEXT_PRINTRAW
constants.description: Print the given string to the standard output, without adding a newline.

constants.name: VAR_TO_STR
constants.description: Serialize a [Variant] to a string.

constants.name: STR_TO_VAR
constants.description: Deserialize a [Variant] from a string serialized using [VAR_TO_STR].

constants.name: VAR_TO_BYTES
constants.description: Serialize a [Variant] to a [PoolByteArray].

constants.name: BYTES_TO_VAR
constants.description: Deserialize a [Variant] from a [PoolByteArray] serialized using [VAR_TO_BYTES].

constants.name: COLORN
constants.description: Return the [Color] with the given name and alpha ranging from 0 to 1. Note: names are defined in color_names.inc.

constants.name: FUNC_MAX
constants.description: The maximum value the [member function] property can have.

properties.name: function
properties.description: The function to be executed.

Particles2D.name: Particles2D
Particles2D.description:
2D particle node used to create a variety of particle systems and effects. [code]Particles2D[/code] features an emitter that generates some number of particles at a given rate.
		Use the [code]process_material[/code] property to add a [ParticlesMaterial] to configure particle appearance and behavior. Alternatively, you can add a [ShaderMaterial] which will be applied to all particles.

constants.name: DRAW_ORDER_INDEX
constants.description: Particles are drawn in the order emitted.

constants.name: DRAW_ORDER_LIFETIME
constants.description: Particles are drawn in order of remaining lifetime.

properties.name: amount
properties.description: Number of particles emitted in one emission cycle.

properties.name: draw_order
properties.description: Particle draw order. Uses [code]DRAW_ORDER_*[/code] values. Default value: [code]DRAW_ORDER_INDEX[/code].

properties.name: emitting
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] particles are being emitted. Default value: [code]true[/code].

properties.name: explosiveness
properties.description: How rapidly particles in an emission cycle are emitted. If greater than [code]0[/code], there will be a gap in emissions before the next cycle begins. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: h_frames
properties.description: Number of horizontal frames in [code]texture[/code].

properties.name: lifetime
properties.description: Amount of time each particle will exist. Default value: [code]1[/code].

properties.name: local_coords
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] particles use the parent node's coordinate space. If [code]false[/code] they use global coordinates. Default value: [code]true[/code].

properties.name: one_shot
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] only one emission cycle occurs. If set [code]true[/code] during a cycle, emission will stop at the cycle's end. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: preprocess
properties.description: Particle system starts as if it had already run for this many seconds.

properties.name: process_material
properties.description: [Material] for processing particles. Can be a [ParticlesMaterial] or a [ShaderMaterial].

properties.name: randomness
properties.description: Emission lifetime randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: speed_scale
properties.description: Particle system's running speed scaling ratio. Default value: [code]1[/code].

properties.name: texture
properties.description: Particle texture. If [code]null[/code] particles will be squares.

properties.name: v_frames
properties.description: Number of vertical frames in [code]texture[/code].

properties.name: visibility_rect
properties.description: Editor visibility helper.

ToolButton.name: ToolButton
ToolButton.description:
This is a helper class to generate a flat [Button] (see [method Button.set_flat]), creating a ToolButton is equivalent to:

		[codeblock]
		var btn = Button.new()
		btn.set_flat(true)
		[/codeblock]

CheckButton.name: CheckButton
CheckButton.description: CheckButton is a toggle button displayed as a check field.

constants.name: FORMAT_8_BITS
constants.description: Audio codec 8 bit.

constants.name: FORMAT_16_BITS
constants.description: Audio codec 16 bit.

constants.name: FORMAT_IMA_ADPCM
constants.description: Audio codec IMA ADPCM.

constants.name: LOOP_DISABLED
constants.description: Audio does not loop.

constants.name: LOOP_FORWARD
constants.description: Audio loops the data between loop_begin and loop_end playing forward only.

constants.name: LOOP_PING_PONG
constants.description: Audio loops the data between loop_begin and loop_end playing back and forth.

properties.name: format
properties.description: Audio format. See FORMAT_* constants for values.

properties.name: loop_begin
properties.description: Loop start in bytes.

properties.name: loop_end
properties.description: Loop end in bytes.

properties.name: loop_mode
properties.description: Loop mode. See LOOP_* constants for values.

properties.name: mix_rate
properties.description: The sample rate for mixing this audio.

properties.name: stereo
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], audio is stereo. Default value: [code]false[/code].

methods.name: add_surface_from_arrays
methods.description:
Create a new surface ([method get_surface_count] that will become surf_idx for this.
				Surfaces are created to be rendered using a "primitive", which may be PRIMITIVE_POINTS, PRIMITIVE_LINES, PRIMITIVE_LINE_STRIP, PRIMITIVE_LINE_LOOP, PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLES, PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLE_STRIP, PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLE_FAN. (As a note, when using indices, it is recommended to only use just points, lines or triangles).

methods.name: get_surface_count
methods.description: Return the amount of surfaces that the [code]ArrayMesh[/code] holds.

methods.name: surface_get_array_index_len
methods.description: Return the length in indices of the index array in the requested surface (see [method add_surface]).

methods.name: surface_get_array_len
methods.description: Return the length in vertices of the vertex array in the requested surface (see [method add_surface]).

methods.name: surface_get_format
methods.description: Return the format mask of the requested surface (see [method add_surface]).

methods.name: surface_get_material
methods.description: Return a [Material] in a given surface. Surface is rendered using this material.

methods.name: surface_get_primitive_type
methods.description: Return the primitive type of the requested surface (see [method add_surface]).

methods.name: surface_remove
methods.description: Remove a surface at position surf_idx, shifting greater surfaces one surf_idx slot down.

methods.name: surface_set_name
methods.description: Set a [Material] for a given surface. Surface will be rendered using this material.

constants.name: NO_INDEX_ARRAY
constants.description: Default value used for index_array_len when no indices are present.

constants.name: ARRAY_WEIGHTS_SIZE
constants.description: Amount of weights/bone indices per vertex (always 4).

constants.name: ARRAY_VERTEX
constants.description: Vertex array (array of [Vector3] vertices).

constants.name: ARRAY_NORMAL
constants.description: Normal array (array of [Vector3] normals).

constants.name: ARRAY_TANGENT
constants.description: Tangent array, array of groups of 4 floats. first 3 floats determine the tangent, and the last the binormal direction as -1 or 1.

constants.name: ARRAY_COLOR
constants.description: Vertex array (array of [Color] colors).

constants.name: ARRAY_TEX_UV
constants.description: UV array (array of [Vector3] UVs or float array of groups of 2 floats (u,v)).

constants.name: ARRAY_TEX_UV2
constants.description: Second UV array (array of [Vector3] UVs or float array of groups of 2 floats (u,v)).

constants.name: ARRAY_BONES
constants.description: Array of bone indices, as a float array. Each element in groups of 4 floats.

constants.name: ARRAY_WEIGHTS
constants.description: Array of bone weights, as a float array. Each element in groups of 4 floats.

constants.name: ARRAY_INDEX
constants.description: Array of integers, used as indices referencing vertices. No index can be beyond the vertex array size.

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_VERTEX
constants.description: Array format will include vertices (mandatory).

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_NORMAL
constants.description: Array format will include normals

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_TANGENT
constants.description: Array format will include tangents

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_COLOR
constants.description: Array format will include a color array.

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_TEX_UV
constants.description: Array format will include UVs.

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_TEX_UV2
constants.description: Array format will include another set of UVs.

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_BONES
constants.description: Array format will include bone indices.

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_WEIGHTS
constants.description: Array format will include bone weights.

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_INDEX
constants.description: Index array will be used.

Array.name: Array
Array.description: Generic array, contains several elements of any type, accessible by numerical index starting at 0. Negative indices can be used to count from the right, like in Python. Arrays are always passed by reference.

methods.name: Array
methods.description: Construct an array from a [PoolColorArray].

methods.name: Array
methods.description: Construct an array from a [PoolVector3Array].

methods.name: Array
methods.description: Construct an array from a [PoolVector2Array].

methods.name: Array
methods.description: Construct an array from a [PoolStringArray].

methods.name: Array
methods.description: Construct an array from a [PoolRealArray].

methods.name: Array
methods.description: Construct an array from a [PoolIntArray].

methods.name: Array
methods.description: Construct an array from a [PoolByteArray].

methods.name: append
methods.description: Append an element at the end of the array (alias of [method push_back]).

methods.name: back
methods.description: Returns the last element of the array if the array is not empty (size>0).

methods.name: bsearch
methods.description: Finds the index of an existing value (or the insertion index that maintains sorting order, if the value is not yet present in the array) using binary search. Optionally, a before specifier can be passed. If false, the returned index comes after all existing entries of the value in the array. Note that calling bsearch on an unsorted array results in unexpected behavior.

methods.name: bsearch_custom
methods.description: Finds the index of an existing value (or the insertion index that maintains sorting order, if the value is not yet present in the array) using binary search and a custom comparison method. Optionally, a before specifier can be passed. If false, the returned index comes after all existing entries of the value in the array.  The custom method receives two arguments (an element from the array and the value searched for) and must return true if the first argument is less than the second, and return false otherwise. Note that calling bsearch on an unsorted array results in unexpected behavior.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear the array (resize to 0).

methods.name: count
methods.description: Return the amount of times an element is in the array.

methods.name: duplicate
methods.description: Returns a copy of this [code]Array[/code].

methods.name: empty
methods.description: Return true if the array is empty (size==0).

methods.name: erase
methods.description: Remove the first occurrence of a value from the array.

methods.name: find
methods.description: Searches the array for a value and returns its index or -1 if not found. Optionally, the initial search index can be passed.

methods.name: find_last
methods.description: Searches the array in reverse order for a value and returns its index or -1 if not found.

methods.name: front
methods.description: Returns the first element of the array if the array is not empty (size>0).

methods.name: has
methods.description:
Return true if the array contains given value.
				[codeblock]
				[ "inside", 7 ].has("inside") == true
				[ "inside", 7 ].has("outside") == false
				[ "inside", 7 ].has(7) == true
				[ "inside", 7 ].has("7") == false
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: hash
methods.description: Return a hashed integer value representing the array contents.

methods.name: insert
methods.description: Insert a new element at a given position in the array. The position must be valid, or at the end of the array (pos==size()).

methods.name: invert
methods.description: Reverse the order of the elements in the array (so first element will now be the last) and return reference to the array.

methods.name: pop_back
methods.description: Remove the last element of the array.

methods.name: pop_front
methods.description: Remove the first element of the array.

methods.name: push_back
methods.description: Append an element at the end of the array.

methods.name: push_front
methods.description: Add an element at the beginning of the array.

methods.name: remove
methods.description: Remove an element from the array by index.

methods.name: resize
methods.description: Resize the array to contain a different number of elements. If the array size is smaller, elements are cleared, if bigger, new elements are Null.

methods.name: rfind
methods.description: Searches the array in reverse order. Optionally, a start search index can be passed. If negative, the start index is considered relative to the end of the array.

methods.name: size
methods.description: Return the amount of elements in the array.

methods.name: sort
methods.description: Sort the array using natural order and return reference to the array.

methods.name: sort_custom
methods.description:
Sort the array using a custom method and return reference to the array. The arguments are an object that holds the method and the name of such method. The custom method receives two arguments (a pair of elements from the array) and must return true if the first argument is less than the second, and return false otherwise. Note: you cannot randomize the return value as the heapsort algorithm expects a deterministic result. Doing so will result in unexpected behavior.
				[codeblock]
				class MyCustomSorter:
				    static func sort(a, b):
				        if a[0] < b[0]:
				            return true
				    return false

				var my_items = [[5, "Potato"], [9, "Rice"], [4, "Tomato"]]
				my_items.sort_custom(MyCustomSorter, "sort")
				[/codeblock]

HTTPRequest.name: HTTPRequest
HTTPRequest.brief_description: A node with the ability to send HTTP requests.
HTTPRequest.description:
A node with the ability to send HTTP requests. Uses [HTTPClient] internally.
		Can be used to make HTTP requests, i.e. download or upload files or web content via HTTP.

methods.name: cancel_request
methods.description: Cancels the current request.

methods.name: get_body_size
methods.description: Returns the response body length.

methods.name: get_downloaded_bytes
methods.description: Returns the amount of bytes this HTTPRequest downloaded.

methods.name: get_http_client_status
methods.description: Returns the current status of the underlying [HTTPClient]. See [code]STATUS_*[/code] enum on [HTTPClient].

signals.name: request_completed
signals.description: This signal is emitted upon request completion.

constants.name: RESULT_SUCCESS
constants.description: Request successful.

constants.name: RESULT_CANT_CONNECT
constants.description: Request failed while connecting.

constants.name: RESULT_CANT_RESOLVE
constants.description: Request failed while resolving.

constants.name: RESULT_CONNECTION_ERROR
constants.description: Request failed due to connection(read/write) error.

constants.name: RESULT_SSL_HANDSHAKE_ERROR
constants.description: Request failed on SSL handshake.

constants.name: RESULT_NO_RESPONSE
constants.description: Request does not have a response(yet).

constants.name: RESULT_BODY_SIZE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED
constants.description: Request exceeded its maximum size limit, see [method set_body_size_limit].

constants.name: RESULT_REQUEST_FAILED
constants.description: Request failed. (Unused)

constants.name: RESULT_DOWNLOAD_FILE_CANT_OPEN
constants.description: HTTPRequest couldn't open the download file.

constants.name: RESULT_DOWNLOAD_FILE_WRITE_ERROR
constants.description: HTTPRequest couldn't write to the download file.

constants.name: RESULT_REDIRECT_LIMIT_REACHED
constants.description: Request reached its maximum redirect limit, see [method set_max_redirects].

properties.name: body_size_limit
properties.description: Maximum allowed size for response bodies.

properties.name: download_file
properties.description: The file to download into. Will output any received file into it.

properties.name: max_redirects
properties.description: Maximum number of allowed redirects.

properties.name: use_threads
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] multithreading is used to improve performance.

VisualScriptMathConstant.name: VisualScriptMathConstant
VisualScriptMathConstant.description:
Provides common math constants, such as Pi or Euler's constant, on an output Data port.
		[b]Input Ports:[/b]
		none
		[b]Output Ports:[/b]
		- Data (variant): [code]get[/code]

constants.name: MATH_CONSTANT_ONE
constants.description: Unity: [code]1[/code]

constants.name: MATH_CONSTANT_PI
constants.description: Pi: [code]3.141593[/code]

constants.name: MATH_CONSTANT_HALF_PI
constants.description: Pi divided by two: [code]1.570796[/code]

constants.name: MATH_CONSTANT_TAU
constants.description: Tau: [code]6.283185[/code]

constants.name: MATH_CONSTANT_E
constants.description: Natural log: [code]2.718282[/code]

constants.name: MATH_CONSTANT_SQRT2
constants.description: Square root of two: [code]1.414214[/code]

constants.name: MATH_CONSTANT_INF
constants.description: Infinity: [code]inf[/code]

constants.name: MATH_CONSTANT_NAN
constants.description: Not a number: [code]nan[/code]

properties.name: constant
properties.description: The math constant.

TabContainer.name: TabContainer
TabContainer.description:
Sets the active tab's [code]visible[/code] property to the value [code]true[/code]. Sets all other children's to [code]false[/code].
		Ignores non-[Control] children.
		Individual tabs are always visible unless you use [method set_tab_disabled] and [method set_tab_title] to hide it.
		To hide only a tab's content, nest the content inside a child [Control], so it receives the [code]TabContainer[/code]'s visibility setting instead.

methods.name: get_current_tab_control
methods.description: Returns the child [Control] node located at the active tab index.

methods.name: get_popup
methods.description: Returns the [Popup] node instance if one has been set already with [method set_popup].

methods.name: get_previous_tab
methods.description: Returns the previously active tab index.

methods.name: get_tab_control
methods.description: Returns the currently visible tab's [Control] node.

methods.name: get_tab_count
methods.description: Returns the number of tabs.

methods.name: get_tab_disabled
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the tab at index [code]tab_idx[/code] is disabled.

methods.name: get_tab_icon
methods.description: Returns the [Texture] for the tab at index [code]tab_idx[/code] or null if the tab has no [Texture].

methods.name: get_tab_title
methods.description: Returns the title of the tab at index [code]tab_idx[/code]. Tab titles default to the name of the indexed child node, but this can be overridden with [method set_tab_title].

methods.name: set_popup
methods.description: If set on a [Popup] node instance, a popup menu icon appears in the top-right corner of the [code]TabContainer[/code]. Clicking it will expand the [Popup] node.

methods.name: set_tab_disabled
methods.description: If [code]disabled[/code] is false, hides the tab at index [code]tab_idx[/code]. Note that its title text will remain, unless also removed with [method set_tab_title].

methods.name: set_tab_icon
methods.description: Sets an icon for the tab at index [code]tab_idx[/code].

methods.name: set_tab_title
methods.description: Sets a title for the tab at index [code]tab_idx[/code]. Tab titles default to the name of the indexed child node, but this can be overridden with [method set_tab_title].

signals.name: pre_popup_pressed
signals.description: Emitted when the [code]TabContainer[/code]'s [Popup] button is clicked. See [method set_popup] for details.

signals.name: tab_changed
signals.description: Emitted when switching to another tab.

signals.name: tab_selected
signals.description: Emitted when a tab is selected, even if it is the current tab.

properties.name: current_tab
properties.description: The current tab index. When set, this index's [Control] node's [code]visible[/code] property is set to [code]true[/code] and all others are set to [code]false[/code].

properties.name: tab_align
properties.description: The alignment of all tabs in the tab container. See the [code]ALIGN_*[/code] constants for details.

properties.name: tabs_visible
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] tabs are visible. If [code]false[/code] tabs' content and titles are hidden. Default value: [code]true[/code].

BitMap.name: BitMap
BitMap.description: A two-dimensional array of boolean values, can be used to efficiently store a binary matrix (every matrix element takes only one bit) and query the values using natural cartesian coordinates.

methods.name: create
methods.description: Creates a bitmap with the specified size, filled with false.

methods.name: create_from_image_alpha
methods.description: Creates a bitmap that matches the given image dimensions, every element of the bitmap is set to false if the alpha value of the image at that position is 0, and true in other case.

methods.name: get_bit
methods.description: Returns bitmap's value at the specified position.

methods.name: get_size
methods.description: Returns bitmap's dimensions.

methods.name: get_true_bit_count
methods.description: Returns the amount of bitmap elements that are set to true.

methods.name: set_bit
methods.description: Sets the bitmap's element at the specified position, to the specified value.

methods.name: set_bit_rect
methods.description: Sets a rectangular portion of the bitmap to the specified value.

DirectionalLight.name: DirectionalLight
DirectionalLight.brief_description: Directional Light, such as the Sun or the Moon.
DirectionalLight.description: A DirectionalLight is a type of [Light] node that emits light constantly in one direction (the negative z axis of the node). It is used lights with strong intensity that are located far away from the scene to model sunlight or moonlight. The worldspace location of the DirectionalLight transform (origin) is ignored, only the basis is used do determine light direction.

AcceptDialog.name: AcceptDialog
AcceptDialog.description: This dialog is useful for small notifications to the user about an event. It can only be accepted or closed, with the same result.

methods.name: add_button
methods.description:
Adds a button with label [i]text[/i] and a custom [i]action[/i] to the dialog and returns the created button. [i]action[/i] will be passed to the [custom_action] signal when pressed.
				If [code]true[/code], [i]right[/i] will place the button to the right of any sibling buttons. Default value: [code]false[/code].

methods.name: add_cancel
methods.description: Adds a button with label [i]name[/i] and a cancel action to the dialog and returns the created button.

methods.name: get_label
methods.description: Return the label used for built-in text.

methods.name: get_ok
methods.description: Return the OK Button.

methods.name: register_text_enter
methods.description: Registers a [LineEdit] in the dialog. When the enter key is pressed, the dialog will be accepted.

signals.name: confirmed
signals.description: Emitted when the dialog is accepted.

signals.name: custom_action
signals.description: Emitted when a custom button is pressed. See [method add_button].

properties.name: dialog_hide_on_ok
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the dialog is hidden when accepted. Default value: [code]true[/code].

properties.name: dialog_text
properties.description: The text displayed by this dialog.

Basis.name: Basis
Basis.description:
3x3 matrix used for 3D rotation and scale. Contains 3 vector fields x,y and z as its columns, which can be interpreted as the local basis vectors of a transformation. Can also be accessed as array of 3D vectors. These vectors are orthogonal to each other, but are not necessarily normalized. Almost always used as orthogonal basis for a [Transform].
		For such use, it is composed of a scaling and a rotation matrix, in that order (M = R.S).

methods.name: Basis
methods.description: Create a rotation matrix from the given quaternion.

methods.name: Basis
methods.description: Create a rotation matrix (in the YXZ convention: first Z, then X, and Y last) from the specified Euler angles, given in the vector format as (X-angle, Y-angle, Z-angle).

methods.name: Basis
methods.description: Create a rotation matrix which rotates around the given axis by the specified angle, in radians. The axis must be a normalized vector.

methods.name: Basis
methods.description: Create a matrix from 3 axis vectors.

methods.name: determinant
methods.description: Return the determinant of the matrix.

methods.name: get_euler
methods.description: Assuming that the matrix is a proper rotation matrix (orthonormal matrix with determinant +1), return Euler angles (in the YXZ convention: first Z, then X, and Y last). Returned vector contains the rotation angles in the format (X-angle, Y-angle, Z-angle).

methods.name: get_orthogonal_index
methods.description: This function considers a discretization of rotations into 24 points on unit sphere, lying along the vectors (x,y,z) with each component being either -1,0 or 1, and returns the index of the point best representing the orientation of the object. It is mainly used by the grid map editor. For further details, refer to Godot source code.

methods.name: get_scale
methods.description: Assuming that the matrix is the combination of a rotation and scaling, return the absolute value of scaling factors along each axis.

methods.name: inverse
methods.description: Return the inverse of the matrix.

methods.name: orthonormalized
methods.description: Return the orthonormalized version of the matrix (useful to call from time to time to avoid rounding error for orthogonal matrices). This performs a Gram-Schmidt orthonormalization on the basis of the matrix.

methods.name: rotated
methods.description: Introduce an additional rotation around the given axis by phi (radians). Only relevant when the matrix is being used as a part of [Transform]. The axis must be a normalized vector.

methods.name: scaled
methods.description: Introduce an additional scaling specified by the given 3D scaling factor. Only relevant when the matrix is being used as a part of [Transform].

methods.name: tdotx
methods.description: Transposed dot product with the x axis of the matrix.

methods.name: tdoty
methods.description: Transposed dot product with the y axis of the matrix.

methods.name: tdotz
methods.description: Transposed dot product with the z axis of the matrix.

methods.name: transposed
methods.description: Return the transposed version of the matrix.

methods.name: xform
methods.description: Return a vector transformed (multiplied) by the matrix.

methods.name: xform_inv
methods.description: Return a vector transformed (multiplied) by the transposed matrix. Note that this results in a multiplication by the inverse of the matrix only if it represents a rotation-reflection.

properties.name: x
properties.description: The basis matrix's x vector.

properties.name: y
properties.description: The basis matrix's y vector.

properties.name: z
properties.description: The basis matrix's z vector.

Area.name: Area
Area.brief_description: General purpose area node for detection and 3D physics influence.
Area.description: 3D area that detects [CollisionObject] nodes overlapping, entering, or exiting. Can also alter or override local physics parameters (gravity, damping).

methods.name: get_collision_layer_bit
methods.description: Returns an individual bit on the layer mask.

methods.name: get_collision_mask_bit
methods.description: Returns an individual bit on the collision mask.

methods.name: get_overlapping_areas
methods.description: Returns a list of intersecting [code]Area[/code]s. For performance reasons (collisions are all processed at the same time) this list is modified once during the physics step, not immediately after objects are moved. Consider using signals instead.

methods.name: get_overlapping_bodies
methods.description: Returns a list of intersecting [PhysicsBody]s. For performance reasons (collisions are all processed at the same time) this list is modified once during the physics step, not immediately after objects are moved. Consider using signals instead.

methods.name: overlaps_area
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the given area overlaps the Area. Note that the result of this test is not immediate after moving objects. For performance, list of overlaps is updated once per frame and before the physics step. Consider using signals instead.

methods.name: overlaps_body
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the given body overlaps the Area. Note that the result of this test is not immediate after moving objects. For performance, list of overlaps is updated once per frame and before the physics step. Consider using signals instead.

methods.name: set_collision_layer_bit
methods.description: Set/clear individual bits on the layer mask. This simplifies editing this [code]Area[code]'s layers.

methods.name: set_collision_mask_bit
methods.description: Set/clear individual bits on the collision mask. This simplifies editing which [code]Area[/code] layers this [code]Area[/code] scans.

signals.name: area_entered
signals.description: Emitted when another area enters.

signals.name: area_exited
signals.description: Emitted when another area exits.

signals.name: area_shape_entered
signals.description: Emitted when another area enters, reporting which areas overlapped.

signals.name: area_shape_exited
signals.description: Emitted when another area exits, reporting which areas were overlapping.

signals.name: body_entered
signals.description: Emitted when a [PhysicsBody] object enters.

signals.name: body_exited
signals.description: Emitted when a [PhysicsBody2D] object exits.

signals.name: body_shape_entered
signals.description: Emitted when a [PhysicsBody2D] object enters, reporting which shapes overlapped.

signals.name: body_shape_exited
signals.description: Emitted when a [PhysicsBody2D] object exits, reporting which shapes were overlapping.

constants.name: SPACE_OVERRIDE_DISABLED
constants.description: This area does not affect gravity/damping.

constants.name: SPACE_OVERRIDE_COMBINE
constants.description: This area adds its gravity/damping values to whatever has been calculated so far (in [code]priority[/code] order).

constants.name: SPACE_OVERRIDE_COMBINE_REPLACE
constants.description: This area adds its gravity/damping values to whatever has been calculated so far (in [code]priority[/code] order), ignoring any lower priority areas.

constants.name: SPACE_OVERRIDE_REPLACE
constants.description: This area replaces any gravity/damping, even the defaults, ignoring any lower priority areas.

constants.name: SPACE_OVERRIDE_REPLACE_COMBINE
constants.description: This area replaces any gravity/damping calculated so far (in [code]priority[/code] order), but keeps calculating the rest of the areas.

properties.name: angular_damp
properties.description: The rate at which objects stop spinning in this area. Represents the angular velocity lost per second. Values range from [code]0[/code] (no damping) to [code]1[/code] (full damping).

properties.name: audio_bus_name
properties.description: The name of the area's audio bus.

properties.name: audio_bus_override
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the area's audio bus overrides the default audio bus. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: collision_layer
properties.description: The area's physics layer(s). Collidable objects can exist in any of 32 different layers. A contact is detected if object A is in any of the layers that object B scans, or object B is in any layers that object A scans. See also [code]collision_mask[/code].

properties.name: collision_mask
properties.description: The physics layers this area scans to determine collision detection.

properties.name: gravity
properties.description: The area's gravity intensity (ranges from -1024 to 1024). This value multiplies the gravity vector. This is useful to alter the force of gravity without altering its direction.

properties.name: gravity_distance_scale
properties.description: The falloff factor for point gravity. The greater the value, the faster gravity decreases with distance.

properties.name: gravity_point
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] gravity is calculated from a point (set via [code]gravity_vec[/code]). Also see [code]space_override[/code]. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: gravity_vec
properties.description: The area's gravity vector (not normalized). If gravity is a point (see [method is_gravity_a_point]), this will be the point of attraction.

properties.name: linear_damp
properties.description: The rate at which objects stop moving in this area. Represents the linear velocity lost per second. Values range from [code]0[/code] (no damping) to [code]1[/code] (full damping).

properties.name: monitorable
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] other monitoring areas can detect this area. Default value: [code]true[/code].

properties.name: monitoring
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the area detects bodies or areas entering and exiting it. Default value: [code]true[/code].

properties.name: priority
properties.description: The area's priority. Higher priority areas are processed first. Default value: 0.

properties.name: reverb_bus_amount
properties.description: The degree to which this area applies reverb to its associated audio. Ranges from [code]0[/code] to [code]1[/code] with [code]0.1[/code] precision.

properties.name: reverb_bus_enable
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the area applies reverb to its associated audio.

properties.name: reverb_bus_name
properties.description: The reverb bus name to use for this area's associated audio.

properties.name: reverb_bus_uniformity
properties.description: The degree to which this area's reverb is a uniform effect. Ranges from [code]0[/code] to [code]1[/code] with [code]0.1[/code] precision.

properties.name: space_override
properties.description: Override mode for gravity and damping calculations within this area. See the SPACE_OVERRIDE_* constants for values.

AudioEffectBandPassFilter.name: AudioEffectBandPassFilter
AudioEffectBandPassFilter.brief_description: Adds a band pass filter to the Audio Bus.
AudioEffectBandPassFilter.description: Attenuates the frequencies inside of a range around the [member cutoff_hz] and cuts frequencies outside of this band.

String.name: String
String.description: This is the built-in string class (and the one used by GDScript). It supports Unicode and provides all necessary means for string handling. Strings are reference counted and use a copy-on-write approach, so passing them around is cheap in resources.

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [bool].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [int].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [float].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [Vector2].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [Rect2].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [Vector3].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [Transform2D].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [Plane].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [Quat].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [AABB].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [Basis].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [Transform].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [Color].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [NodePath].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [RID].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [Dictionary].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [Array].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [PoolByteArray].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [PoolIntArray].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [PoolRealArray].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [PoolStringArray].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [PoolVector2Array].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [PoolVector3Array].

methods.name: String
methods.description: Constructs a new String from the given [PoolColorArray].

methods.name: begins_with
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the string begins with the given string.

methods.name: bigrams
methods.description: Returns the bigrams (pairs of consecutive letters) of this string.

methods.name: c_escape
methods.description: Returns a copy of the string with special characters escaped using the C language standard.

methods.name: c_unescape
methods.description: Returns a copy of the string with escaped characters replaced by their meanings according to the C language standard.

methods.name: capitalize
methods.description: Changes the case of some letters. Replaces underscores with spaces, converts all letters to lowercase, then capitalizes first and every letter following the space character. For [code]capitalize camelCase mixed_with_underscores[/code] it will return [code]Capitalize Camelcase Mixed With Underscores[/code].

methods.name: casecmp_to
methods.description: Performs a case-sensitive comparison to another string. Returns [code]-1[/code] if less than, [code]+1[/code] if greater than, or [code]0[/code] if equal.

methods.name: dedent
methods.description: Removes indentation from string.

methods.name: empty
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the string is empty.

methods.name: ends_with
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the string ends with the given string.

methods.name: erase
methods.description: Erases [code]chars[/code] characters from the string starting from [code]position[/code].

methods.name: find
methods.description: Finds the first occurrence of a substring. Returns the starting position of the substring or -1 if not found. Optionally, the initial search index can be passed.

methods.name: find_last
methods.description: Finds the last occurrence of a substring. Returns the starting position of the substring or -1 if not found.

methods.name: findn
methods.description: Finds the first occurrence of a substring, ignoring case. Returns the starting position of the substring or -1 if not found. Optionally, the initial search index can be passed.

methods.name: format
methods.description: Formats the string by replacing all occurrences of [code]placeholder[/code] with [code]values[/code].

methods.name: get_base_dir
methods.description: If the string is a valid file path, returns the base directory name.

methods.name: get_basename
methods.description: If the string is a valid file path, returns the full file path without the extension.

methods.name: get_extension
methods.description: If the string is a valid file path, returns the extension.

methods.name: get_file
methods.description: If the string is a valid file path, returns the filename.

methods.name: hash
methods.description: Hashes the string and returns a 32-bit integer.

methods.name: hex_to_int
methods.description: Converts a string containing a hexadecimal number into an integer.

methods.name: insert
methods.description: Inserts a substring at a given position.

methods.name: is_abs_path
methods.description: If the string is a path to a file or directory, returns [code]true[/code] if the path is absolute.

methods.name: is_rel_path
methods.description: If the string is a path to a file or directory, returns [code]true[/code] if the path is relative.

methods.name: is_subsequence_of
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if this string is a subsequence of the given string.

methods.name: is_subsequence_ofi
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if this string is a subsequence of the given string, without considering case.

methods.name: is_valid_float
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if this string contains a valid float.

methods.name: is_valid_html_color
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if this string contains a valid color in HTML notation.

methods.name: is_valid_identifier
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if this string is a valid identifier. A valid identifier may contain only letters, digits and underscores (_) and the first character may not be a digit.

methods.name: is_valid_integer
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if this string contains a valid integer.

methods.name: is_valid_ip_address
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if this string contains a valid IP address.

methods.name: json_escape
methods.description: Returns a copy of the string with special characters escaped using the JSON standard.

methods.name: left
methods.description: Returns a number of characters from the left of the string.

methods.name: length
methods.description: Returns the string's amount of characters.

methods.name: match
methods.description: Does a simple expression match, where '*' matches zero or more arbitrary characters and '?' matches any single character except '.'.

methods.name: matchn
methods.description: Does a simple case insensitive expression match, using ? and * wildcards (see [method match]).

methods.name: md5_buffer
methods.description: Returns the MD5 hash of the string as an array of bytes.

methods.name: md5_text
methods.description: Returns the MD5 hash of the string as a string.

methods.name: nocasecmp_to
methods.description: Performs a case-insensitive comparison to another string. Returns [code]-1[/code] if less than, [code]+1[/code] if greater than, or [code]0[/code] if equal.

methods.name: ord_at
methods.description: Returns the character code at position [code]at[/code].

methods.name: pad_decimals
methods.description: Formats a number to have an exact number of [code]digits[/code] after the decimal point.

methods.name: pad_zeros
methods.description: Formats a number to have an exact number of [code]digits[/code] before the decimal point.

methods.name: percent_decode
methods.description: Decode a percent-encoded string. See [method percent_encode].

methods.name: percent_encode
methods.description: Percent-encodes a string. Encodes parameters in a URL when sending a HTTP GET request (and bodies of form-urlencoded POST requests).

methods.name: plus_file
methods.description: If the string is a path, this concatenates [code]file[/code] at the end of the string as a subpath. E.g. [code]"this/is".plus_file("path") == "this/is/path"[/code].

methods.name: replace
methods.description: Replaces occurrences of a substring with the given one inside the string.

methods.name: replacen
methods.description: Replaces occurrences of a substring with the given one inside the string. Ignores case.

methods.name: rfind
methods.description: Performs a search for a substring, but starts from the end of the string instead of the beginning.

methods.name: rfindn
methods.description: Performs a search for a substring, but starts from the end of the string instead of the beginning. Ignores case.

methods.name: right
methods.description: Returns the right side of the string from a given position.

methods.name: sha256_text
methods.description: Returns the SHA-256 hash of the string as a string.

methods.name: similarity
methods.description: Returns the similarity index of the text compared to this string. 1 means totally similar and 0 means totally dissimilar.

methods.name: split
methods.description:
Splits the string by a divisor string and returns an array of the substrings. Example "One,Two,Three" will return ["One","Two","Three"] if split by ",".
				If [code]maxsplit[/code] is given, at most maxsplit number of splits occur, and the remainder of the string is returned as the final element of the list (thus, the list will have at most maxsplit+1 elements)

methods.name: split_floats
methods.description: Splits the string in floats by using a divisor string and returns an array of the substrings. Example "1,2.5,3" will return [1,2.5,3] if split by ",".

methods.name: strip_edges
methods.description: Returns a copy of the string stripped of any non-printable character at the beginning and the end. The optional arguments are used to toggle stripping on the left and right edges respectively.

methods.name: substr
methods.description: Returns part of the string from the position [code]from[/code] with length [code]len[/code].

methods.name: to_ascii
methods.description: Converts the String (which is a character array) to [PoolByteArray] (which is an array of bytes). The conversion is sped up in comparison to to_utf8() with the assumption that all the characters the String contains are only ASCII characters.

methods.name: to_float
methods.description: Converts a string containing a decimal number into a [code]float[/code].

methods.name: to_int
methods.description: Converts a string containing an integer number into an [code]int[/code].

methods.name: to_lower
methods.description: Returns the string converted to lowercase.

methods.name: to_upper
methods.description: Returns the string converted to uppercase.

methods.name: to_utf8
methods.description: Converts the String (which is an array of characters) to [PoolByteArray] (which is an array of bytes). The conversion is a bit slower than to_ascii(), but supports all UTF-8 characters. Therefore, you should prefer this function over to_ascii().

methods.name: xml_escape
methods.description: Returns a copy of the string with special characters escaped using the XML standard.

methods.name: xml_unescape
methods.description: Returns a copy of the string with escaped characters replaced by their meanings according to the XML standard.

TextureProgress.name: TextureProgress
TextureProgress.brief_description: Texture-based progress bar. Useful for loading screens and life or stamina bars.
TextureProgress.description: TextureProgress works like [ProgressBar] but it uses up to 3 textures instead of Godot's [Theme] resource. Works horizontally, vertically, and radially.

constants.name: FILL_LEFT_TO_RIGHT
constants.description: The [member texture_progress] fills from left to right.

constants.name: FILL_RIGHT_TO_LEFT
constants.description: The [member texture_progress] fills from right to left.

constants.name: FILL_TOP_TO_BOTTOM
constants.description: The [member texture_progress] fills from top to bototm.

constants.name: FILL_BOTTOM_TO_TOP
constants.description: The [member texture_progress] fills from bottom to top.

constants.name: FILL_CLOCKWISE
constants.description: Turns the node into a radial bar. The [member texture_progress] fills clockwise. See [member radial_center_offset], [member radial_initial_angle] and [member radial_fill_degrees] to refine its behavior.

constants.name: FILL_COUNTER_CLOCKWISE
constants.description: Turns the node into a radial bar. The [member texture_progress] fills counter-clockwise. See [member radial_center_offset], [member radial_initial_angle] and [member radial_fill_degrees] to refine its behavior.

properties.name: fill_mode
properties.description: The fill direction. Uses FILL_* constants.

properties.name: nine_patch_stretch
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] Godot treats the bar's textures like [NinePatchRect]. Use [code]stretch_margin_*[/code], like [member stretch_margin_bottom], to set up the nine patch's 3x3 grid. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: radial_center_offset
properties.description: Offsets [member texture_progress] if [member fill_mode] is [code]FILL_CLOCKWISE[/code] or [code]FILL_COUNTER_CLOCKWISE[/code].

properties.name: radial_fill_degrees
properties.description:
Upper limit for the fill of [member texture_progress] if [member fill_mode] is [code]FILL_CLOCKWISE[/code] or [code]FILL_COUNTER_CLOCKWISE[/code]. When the node's [code]value[/code] is equal to its [code]max_value[/code], the texture fills up to this angle.
			See [member Range.value], [member Range.max_value].

properties.name: radial_initial_angle
properties.description: Starting angle for the fill of [member texture_progress] if [member fill_mode] is [code]FILL_CLOCKWISE[/code] or [code]FILL_COUNTER_CLOCKWISE[/code]. When the node's [code]value[/code] is equal to its [code]min_value[/code], the texture doesn't show up at all. When the [code]value[/code] increases, the texture fills and tends towards [member radial_fill_degrees].

properties.name: stretch_margin_bottom
properties.description: The height of the 9-patch's bottom row. A margin of 16 means the 9-slice's bottom corners and side will have a height of 16 pixels. You can set all 4 margin values individually to create panels with non-uniform borders.

properties.name: stretch_margin_left
properties.description: The width of the 9-patch's left column.

properties.name: stretch_margin_right
properties.description: The width of the 9-patch's right column.

properties.name: stretch_margin_top
properties.description: The height of the 9-patch's top row.

properties.name: texture_over
properties.description: [Texture] that draws over the progress bar. Use it to add highlights or an upper-frame that hides part of [member texture_progress].

properties.name: texture_progress
properties.description:
[Texture] that clips based on the node's [code]value[/code] and [member fill_mode]. As [code]value[/code] increased, the texture fills up. It shows entirely when [code]value[/code] reaches [code]max_value[/code]. It doesn't show at all if [code]value[/code] is equal to [code]min_value[/code].
			The [code]value[/code] property comes from [Range]. See [member Range.value], [member Range.min_value], [member Range.max_value].

properties.name: texture_under
properties.description: [Texture] that draws under the progress bar. The bar's background.

FuncRef.name: FuncRef
FuncRef.brief_description: Reference to a function in an object.
FuncRef.description:
In GDScript, functions are not [i]first-class objects[/i]. This means it is impossible to store them directly as variables, return them from another function, or pass them as arguments.
		However, by creating a [code]FuncRef[/code] using the [method @GDScript.funcref] function, a reference to a function in a given object can be created, passed around and called.

methods.name: call_func
methods.description: Calls the referenced function previously set by [method set_function] or [method @GDScript.funcref].

methods.name: set_function
methods.description: The name of the referenced function to call on the object, without parentheses or any parameters.

methods.name: set_instance
methods.description: The object containing the referenced function. This object must be of a type actually inheriting from [Object], not a built-in type such as [int], [Vector2] or [Dictionary].

PacketPeerStream.name: PacketPeerStream
PacketPeerStream.brief_description: Wrapper to use a PacketPeer over a StreamPeer.
PacketPeerStream.description: PacketStreamPeer provides a wrapper for working using packets over a stream. This allows for using packet based code with StreamPeers. PacketPeerStream implements a custom protocol over the StreamPeer, so the user should not read or write to the wrapped StreamPeer directly.

properties.name: stream_peer
properties.description: The wrapped [StreamPeer] object.

DynamicFontData.name: DynamicFontData
DynamicFontData.brief_description: Used with [DynamicFont] to describe the location of a font file.
DynamicFontData.description: Used with [DynamicFont] to describe the location of a vector font file for dynamic rendering at runtime.

properties.name: font_path
properties.description: The path to the vector font file.

methods.name: add_custom_node
methods.description: Add a custom Visual Script node to the editor. It'll be placed under "Custom Nodes" with the [code]category[/code] as the parameter.

methods.name: remove_custom_node
methods.description: Remove a custom Visual Script node from the editor. Custom nodes already placed on scripts won't be removed.

signals.name: custom_nodes_updated
signals.description: Emitted when a custom Visual Script node is added or removed.

RegExMatch.name: RegExMatch
RegExMatch.brief_description: Contains the results of a regex search.
RegExMatch.description: Contains the results of a single regex match returned by [method RegEx.search] and [method RegEx.search_all]. It can be used to find the position and range of the match and its capturing groups, and it can extract its sub-string for you.

methods.name: get_end
methods.description:
Returns the end position of the match within the source string. The end position of capturing groups can be retrieved by providing its group number as an integer or its string name (if it's a named group). The default value of 0 refers to the whole pattern.
				Returns -1 if the group did not match or doesn't exist.

methods.name: get_group_count
methods.description: Returns the number of capturing groups.

methods.name: get_start
methods.description:
Returns the starting position of the match within the source string. The starting position of capturing groups can be retrieved by providing its group number as an integer or its string name (if it's a named group). The default value of 0 refers to the whole pattern.
				Returns -1 if the group did not match or doesn't exist.

methods.name: get_string
methods.description:
Returns the substring of the match from the source string. Capturing groups can be retrieved by providing its group number as an integer or its string name (if it's a named group). The default value of 0 refers to the whole pattern.
				Returns an empty string if the group did not match or doesn't exist.

properties.name: names
properties.description: A dictionary of named groups and its corresponding group number. Only groups with that were matched are included. If multiple groups have the same name, that name would refer to the first matching one.

properties.name: strings
properties.description: An [Array] of the match and its capturing groups.

properties.name: subject
properties.description: The source string used with the search pattern to find this matching result.
